title: ice tea
directions: Boil water and put in 2-quart container; add 8 tea bags and let sit to brew for 2 hours.
Remove tea bags; add 1 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons lemon juice and stir completely.
Refrigerate until cold.

title: pepper steak and rice
directions: Partially freeze steak; slice diagonally across the grain into 3 x 1/2-inch strips.
Cook steak in vegetable oil, stirring frequently until brown.
Combine 1 cup water, soy sauce, molasses, ground ginger, garlic and salt; mix well and pour over steak. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add onion; cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add green peppers; cover and simmer for 10 minutes. Combine 1/4 cup water with cornstarch; add to steak and cook on medium heat, stirring until smooth and thickened.
Serve over cooked rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: date nut balls
directions: Cook dates, margarine and sugar until margarine is absorbed. Pour in nuts.
Pour all over Rice Krispies.
Shape into balls and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: beef or veal stew(serves 50)
directions: Dredge meat with flour.
Brown slowly on all sides in shortening.
Add seasonings and water to cover.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add whole vegetables, cover again and continue cooking slowly until meat and vegetables are done, about 30 minutes.
Thicken stock for gravy.
Garnish with cooked peas, if desired.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove from bones.
Chop and layer in casserole dish.
Slice egg over chicken.
Layer biscuits (separated in thin layers for dumplings) over eggs and sprinkle with black pepper.
Cover with chicken stock.
Repeat layers beginning with chicken, etc.
Bake about 30 minutes at 325°.

title: tribbles torrid taco salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook 30 minutes on stove and put in jars and seal.

title: oreo cookie pie
directions: Let ice cream soften.
Crush cookies in a bowl.
Add ice cream.
Mix well.
Pour into cookie crust.
Freeze.

title: egg nut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except lettuce.
Cover and refrigerate 1 1/2 hours.
Mound mixture onto lettuce cups.
Serve with party crackers.
Yields 4 servings.
Calories:
257 per serving.

title: five cup fruit salad
directions: Blend all together.
Refrigerate the day before using.

title: onion rings
directions: Mix all ingredients together except onion.
Dip sliced onion into the batter.

title: no-bake peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Put sugar and milk into medium-large saucepan.
Stir over medium-low heat until boiling.
After coming to full boil, boil for 1 minute.
Add butter and peanut butter; mix well.
Add oats; mix well.
Spoon drop onto wax paper or foil; allow to harden.

title: one dish meal
directions: Layer raw meat, then sliced potatoes, then macaroni, then peas and then onions.
Make as many layers as you want.
Put tomato soup over top and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: low-fat fiesta supper
directions: Saute meat in a skillet with liquid Butter Buds and chopped onions until onion is tender.
Add tomatoes, chili powder, oregano, salt and rice.
Stir in taco sauce.
Heat through and sprinkle on cheese.
Stir lightly.

title: creamy broccoli casserole
directions: Place 1-inch of water and broccoli in a large saucepan; bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 5 to 8 minutes or until crisp-tender.

title: bacon pineapple tidbits
directions: Cook bacon until limp and partially cooked but not brown. Drain pineapple.
Lay bacon on paper towels and cool.
Cut each slice of bacon into thirds and wrap each piece around a pineapple tidbit, securing with a toothpick.
Cook on a baking sheet for 5 minutes or until bacon is crisp at 400°.

title: pecan roll
directions: Crush vanilla wafers and chop pecans.
Mix thoroughly with milk, saving about 3/4 cup of crumbs.
Make mixture into a roll, covering with remaining crumbs.
Wrap in wax paper and place in refrigerator overnight.
When ready to serve, slice thinly.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on box.
In 2-quart casserole dish, mix macaroni, mushroom soup, mushrooms, mayonnaise and cheese.
Crumble crackers over top.
Pour margarine over top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or microwave until bubbly.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients as package directs.
Bake in a greased 9 x 12-inch pan at 350°.
Cool completely.

title: turtles
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers.
In saucepan, mix sugar and butter.
Boil mixture for 3 minutes.
Add nuts. Spread hot mixture over crackers.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top. When chocolate is melted, spread evenly with knife.
Sprinkle if desired, with chopped nuts.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: summertime strawberry pie
directions: *Cheat and use the ones which come in the refrigerator section in the red box; they are excellent!

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Combine egg and 1/4 cup soup.
Stir in rice, onion, parsley flakes, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
(Put some Worcestershire sauce in meat mixture, also).
Add meat and mix well.
Shape into balls.
Place in a 10-inch skillet.
Mix remaining soup with Worcestershire sauce and 1/2 cup water.
Pour over meatballs.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 35 to 40 minutes.
Turn over halfway through.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain off fat.
Heat soups in saucepan, until cheese soup melts.
Add meat to soups and Ro-Tel tomatoes; mix well.
Spread Doritos in pan; pour meat and soup mixture on top.
Top with grated cheese.
Heat in oven at 350° until cheese melts.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large mixing bowl, beat eggs on high speed until they are foamy, around 2 to 3 minutes.
Beat in flour, sugar and brown sugar until well blended.
Beat in softened butter.
Stir in the nuts and chips.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until a toothpick that is inserted halfway between edge and center comes out clean and the top is brown.

title: broccoli, rice and cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain and while hot, add Cheez Whiz.
Saute onion in butter until soft.
Add onion mixture and rice to broccoli and cheese mixture.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.

title: grannys special secret chocolate pie
directions: In a large sauce pan, mix above dry ingredients together; add eggs and 1/4 c. milk.
Mix until well blended, then add remainder of milk.
Cook over low to medium heat until it bubbles.
Stir constantly and when it starts to thicken, stir hard.
If it begins to lump. turn heat down and stir hard.
Lumps will beat out.
When finished, add margarine, vanilla and chocolate chips.
Stir until butter and chocolate chips are melted.
Cool, pour into baked pie shell or graham cracker crust.
Use only egg yolks if you use meringue on the pie.
Cool Whip topping is also good.
This is our familys favorite pie and we all fight over it, when mom makes it.

title: oatmeal crunchies
directions: Cream shortening with sugars.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla. Sift flour, baking soda and salt.
Add dry ingredients and oatmeal to creamed mixture.
Shape into roll and chill.
Slice into thin pieces.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: louisiana "dirty" rice
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage in a large skillet (cut sausage in small pieces). Add chopped onion.
When onion is tender, add rice, salt and pepper.
Stir well and serve while hot. Serves 12.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper. Add milk all at once.
Cook and stir over medium heat.
Add cubed Velveeta.
Continue cooking until thick and bubbly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Mix with cooked macaroni.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Grease a dish and put a thin layer of herb mix on bottom. Saute onions in butter.
Mix together all ingredients except herb mix.
Pour in a casserole dish.
Top with herb mix.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: gazpacho
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Refrigerate, covered, at least 6 to 8 hours.
Serve chilled and garnish each bowl with thinly sliced cucumbers.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry mousse(1 mg. cholesterol)
directions: Set out serving bowl or six individual stemmed dessert glasses.
In small microwave dish or saucepan, combine gelatin and orange juice.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Then microwave on 50% power for 30 seconds or warm over low heat until gelatin dissolves.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix together thoroughly, cake mix, margarine and 2 eggs.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Spread evenly.
Then mix together powdered sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs.
Pour over batter and bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken with potatoes and peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large skillet, heat Italian dressing and brown chicken over medium high heat; set aside.
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, combine remaining ingredients; add chicken and turn to coat.
Bake, uncovered, stirring occasionally, 50 minutes or until chicken is done and vegetables are tender. Serve, if desired, with French or Italian bread.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: old fashion pound cake
directions: Mix all
ingredients
well.
Put in tube pan lined with wax paper.
Bake for one hour on 350°.

title: grandma lena holland's eggless, milkless cake
directions: Put apples, raisins, water, brown sugar, white sugar and lard in a large pot and cook 5 minutes.
Cool until cold.
Sift the rest in a large bowl.
Add apple/raisin stuff.
Mix well.
Add 1 cup pecans or walnuts.
Pour into a greased and floured long cake pan.
Bake for 1 hour at about 350° or until cake is done.

title: low-fat oven fried chicken
directions: Mix bread crumbs and desired herbs on a sheet of wax paper. Set aside.

title: smothered chicken
directions: Add all ingredients together.
Place chicken in baking pan. Pour sauce over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours covered. Remove cover for last 1/2 hour.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, onion and celery in a pot of water.
Fill little more than half the pot with water.
Add salt.
After potatoes, celery and onion are soft, take off burner.
Add evaporated milk. Rinse can out with regular milk and add to pot.
Add 3 to 4 pats of butter on top.
Let melt.
Add more butter, if needed.
Let soup heat through on low heat.
Add paprika when finished.

title: apple butter bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and brown sugar in mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Blend in egg.
Combine flour and spices in a bowl.
Mix soda and buttermilk in a cup.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk mixture, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in apple butter and pecans.
Pour into greased 5x9 inch loaf pan.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
Reduce temperature to 325° and bake for additional 20 minutes or until the loaf tests done.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.

title: chicken and vegetable casserole
directions: Put chicken and vegetables in a casserole dish.
Mix soup, sour cream and cheese.
Pour over chicken and vegetables.
Mix Stove Top according to directions on box.
Put on top of chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: angel nut pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar and baking powder. Fold in graham cracker crumbs and pecans.
Pour into a greased pie pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
When cool, frost with Cool Whip.

title: beefed-up biscuit casserole
directions: Brown meat, onions and bell peppers in large skillet, drain well.
Stir in tomato sauce, chili powder and garlic powder. Simmer while preparing dough. Separate 5 biscuits making 10; press into 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Combine 1/2 cup cheese, sour cram and egg in bowl; mix well. Remove meat from heat; stir in cheese mixture.
Pour over dough.
Separate other 5 biscuits making 10; cover meat mixture.
Sprinkle rest of cheese over top of biscuits. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cut eggplant into cubes.
Boil until tender and drain.
Saute onion.
Fry bacon and crumble into small pieces.
Mix together. Add eggs, Cheddar cheese, softened butter and cornflakes.
Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and pats of butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mints
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add water and flavoring.
Add food coloring if desired.
Press into molds that are lightly coated with granulated sugar.
Press down on wax paper.
Allow to dry.

title: easy stuffed mushrooms
directions: Soak mushrooms and pull stems out.
Dry on paper towels. Prepare stuffing according to the directions.
Squirt small amount of cheese in the bottom of the mushroom.
With your fingers, pack the stuffing in the mushroom until it is full.
Lay out on a cookie sheet (stuffing up).
Broil until the tops are brown.
Take cheese and put a "dollop" in the center of the stuffing and serve warm.

title: super nacho dip
directions: Fry meat and onion.
Drain.
Spread beans in 10 x 15-inch pan. Top with meat and onion.
Sprinkle chilies over meat.
Cover with cheese.
Top with taco sauce or salsa.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Garnish with green onion, and black olives.
Spread avocado dip to cover and sour cream.
Serve with taco chips.

title: barbecued short ribs
directions: Cut ribs into serving pieces; brown ribs and onion in 2 tablespoons hot fat in skillet.
Combine remaining ingredients; add to ribs.
Cover; cook over low heat for 1 hour and 30 minutes to 2 hours or until tender.

title: baked cod with tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Arrange fillets in baking dish.
In medium size pan, saute onion and garlic for 3 to 5 minutes until softened. Add drained and chopped tomatoes and balance of ingredients.
Simmer 8 to 10 minutes. Spoon sauce over fish. Bake in
a 450° oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until cooked through. Serves 4.
Less than 200 calories per person.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Pour half of batter in pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Combine milk and candy in top of double boiler.
Heat until candy has melted.
Pour over baked half of cake.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over candy mixture.
Add remaining cake batter.
Press pecans into raw batter.
Return to oven 30 to 35 minutes.

title: blueberry pecan cheesecake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients except the blueberries and nuts.
Pour into pie crust and refrigerate over night.
Add the blueberries and nuts before serving.
(You can use any kind of fruit pie filling.)

title: autumn apple cakes
directions: *Instead of apples, you may use 1 cup chunky applesauce.

title: pasta salad
directions: Boil broken spaghetti. Drain. Clean and cut vegetables. Mix all vegetables together.
Mix together dressing and sugar. Mix all together.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Can use fresh mushrooms that have been sauteed.

title: angel food cake
directions: Slice cake into 3 slices.
Mix Cool Whip, pudding and pie mix and pineapple with juice together with a wooden spoon.
Set aside for 5 minutes.
Spread mixture between layers; cover cake with remainder.
You will have plenty of icing mixture so put as much as you like between layers.

title: bobby's favorite chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, flour and egg yolks. Mix in milk gradually.
Add salt and cook until thick, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add vanilla and butter.
Pour into shell.

title: chicken curry in a hurry
directions: In a small bowl, stir together the yogurt, mayonnaise, onions, ginger and curry powder; set aside.
Place chicken in a medium bowl.
Combine the paprika and pepper.
Sprinkle over the chicken and toss until cooked.
Spray an unheated, large nonstick skillet with non-stick spray.
Heat the skillet over medium-high heat.
Add the chicken.
Cook and stir for 3 to 4 minutes or until the chicken is no longer pink.
Stir in the yogurt mixture.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes.
Serve over the rice.

title: spiced orange jello salad
directions: Add water to the mandarin orange syrup to make 1 3/4 cups. Combine syrup mix, salt, cinnamon and whole cloves.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Strain.
Add the jello, cold water and lemon juice.
Chill.
Add oranges and walnuts or pecans.

title: kindergarten pizza
directions: Spread 2 teaspoons spaghetti sauce on split muffin.
Spread 2 teaspoons cheese on top of sauce.
Put pepperoni slices on top of cheese.
Bake in a 400° oven for 5 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: quick oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Add milk and margarine and cook for 2 minutes and 30 seconds.
Add peanut butter and oats.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Can use nuts or coconut also.
Makes about 20 pieces.

title: marinade for vegetables
directions: Cut vegetables into pieces.
Combine all ingredients to your taste.
I start with about a cup of olive oil.
Pour over vegetables.
Let sit for about an hour, more or less.
Prepare grill.
Place on grill and cook until tender.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Beat first 6 ingredients with electric mixer until smooth. Spoon into greased 2-quart shallow casserole.
Combine last four ingredients then sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: saucy apple swirl cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 12-inch fluted pan or a 10-inch tube pan.
In a small bowl, combine the sugar and cinnamon.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, blend cake mix, applesauce and eggs until moistened.
Beat for two minutes at highest speed. Pour 1/2 of the batter into a prepared pan.
Sprinkle with the sugar mixture.
Cover with the remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Cool for 25 minutes; turn onto a serving plate. Cool completely; dust with powdered sugar.

title: monkey cake
directions: Mix 2/3 cup sugar and cinnamon together.
Cut biscuits into quarters and shake them in the cinnamon and sugar mixture to coat completely.
Put coated pieces in a tube pan.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Microwave whole cabbage for 1 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes or until 8 outer leaves can be removed easily.
Refrigerate remaining cabbage for other use.
Cut out hard center rib from each cabbage leaf. Place leaves in an 8 x 12-inch microwave-safe baking dish.
Cover with plastic wrap and vent 1 corner.
Microwave on High power for 1 1/2 to 3 minutes until leaves are pliable.

title: potato puffs
directions: Mix everything in a bowl.
Mold into ball or patty.
Dip in flour.
Dip in egg.
Dip in breadcrumbs and fry.
Delicious!

title: coconut tarts
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and melted margarine.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into tart shells.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until done.
Makes about 12 to 14 tarts.

title: stella henson's yeast rolls
directions: Use half of 2 pound bag of flour.
Sift flour with salt and sugar.
Dissolve yeast in warm water, filling 3/4 of a pint jar. Stir until dissolved.
Add to flour mixture.
Put in lump of shortening and work up like biscuits.
Turn out on floured board. Knead until not sticky.
Let rise in warm place until doubled in size (about 1 1/2 hours).
Roll out rolls.
Let rise again.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: turtle pecan pie
directions: Freeze crust 15 minutes.
Combine chocolate morsels, evaporated milk, marshmallows and salt in heavy pan. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and smooth. Remove from heat.
Set aside.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat in beer.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in gently to batter.
Slice onions.
Put in batter. Deep fry until brown (can store unused batter in fridge for couple days).

title: fettucini and clam sauce
directions: Saute garlic in margarine until brown and remove.
Add soup, milk, cheese and parsley.
Heat through.
Add drained clams and heat.
Do not boil.
Serve over hot, cooked fettucini.

title: b. g.'s baked apricots
directions: Drain apricots.
Layer ingredients as listed in rectangular Pyrex.
Cover and bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Serves as accompaniment to B. G.'S Sausage and Wild Rice Casserole.

title: cinnamon chocolate cake
directions: Blend sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Melt and bring to boil margarine, cocoa and water.
Mix milk, baking soda, vanilla and eggs.
Mix milk mixture with dry ingredients.
Add boiling water mixture.
Use hot icing mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: peach preserves
directions: Cook the peaches in the water until barely tender. Keep heat low so the peaches will not scorch. Drain off juice and add sugar. Boil until the syrup spins a thread. Add the peaches and cook very rapidly 10 to 12 minutes. Remove from heat. Skim if necessary. Let stand in a shallow bowl or tray for 24 hours. Pour into sterilized Kerr jars to within 1/2-inch of top. Put on cap. Screw band firmly tight. Process in boiling water bath 10 minutes. Yields 4 (8 ounce) jars.

title: seafood pasta salad
directions: Boil pasta noodles until tender.
Then drain and wash in a colander with cool water.
The colored noodles add color and improved taste to the salad.
Next dice red and green peppers and onion into small pieces.
Also slice seafood sticks into small pieces.
Mix peppers, onion and seafood sticks.
Next take cooled pasta noodles and start adding mayonnaise.
Gradually stir in other mixture of peppers, etc. and continue to add mayonnaise until salad is evenly mixed and of right consistency.
Makes approximately 8 large servings.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.

title: refrigerator tea
directions: Squeeze juice from lemons, reserving rinds.
Pour 5 cups boiling water over tea bags.
Let steep for 5 minutes.
Remove tea bags.
Add lemon rind and let stand, covered, until cold.
Make syrup of sugar and 1 cup water, boiling until sugar dissolves. When tea is cold, squeeze out lemon rinds and discard.
Add lemon juice and simple syrup.
Makes 2 quarts.
Tastes better after it has been stored in refrigerator and it will not cloud.

title: baked bread parcels with sausages
directions: Spread half the butter over one side of each slice of bread. Mix the onion and mustard with the remaining butter and spread on the other side. Prick sausages with a fork. Wrap each sausage in a slice of bread with mustard inside. Place on a baking sheet and cook in a preheated oven at 350° for 25-30 minutes. When bread is golden brown and sausage is cooked, remove from oven to cool.

title: deluxe patties
directions: Mix beef, cheese, chives and salt.
Shape into patties.
Mix flour and salt.
Dredge patties in flour, then dip in beaten egg and dredge in flour again or in bread crumbs, if desired.
Fry in cooking oil until golden and crispy.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Dice artichoke hearts in a bowl and mix with mayonnaise and cheese.
Place in a small casserole dish and heat in a 350°
oven until bubbling hot.
Serve with crackers, Melba toast or party shells.

title: potato cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients except shortening.
Heat shortening.
Drop potatoes by tablespoons and brown on both sides.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: warm chocolate raisin sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until marshmallows and chocolate are melted.
Blend well. Serve warm over ice cream.
Makes 3/4 cup.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Cream butter until consistency of mayonnaise.
Add sugar gradually; cream until light and fluffy.
Combine flour and cornstarch; beat in slowly.
When all is added, mix thoroughly with hands.
Chill.
Roll out on lightly floured surface to about 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with cookie cutter (about 2 1/2 inches). Bake on ungreased cookie sheets at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes. (Should be just barely browned.)
Makes about 36 cookies.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix together 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Shake together with biscuit dough in plastic bag.
Place in a greased Bundt pan. Combine remaining ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Pour over biscuit dough and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Mix, with a wooden spoon in a very large mixing bowl, all ingredients.
Grease pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chick pot pie
directions: Lightly salt chicken.
Melt margarine in a large casserole dish.
Arrange chicken in bottom of dish.
Layer carrots, peas and potatoes over chicken.
Mix soup and water together and pour over vegetables.
Blend flour and milk and pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: old settlers baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef, bacon and onion; drain fat.
Mix sugars, catsup, barbecue sauce, molasses, mustard, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Add to mixture the kidney beans, pork and beans and butter beans.
Put in casserole dish and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: spicy fried tofu
directions: Drain tofu, rinse, dry on a towel and cut into 1/2 to 1 inch cubes.
Heat oil in wok or skillet until quite hot.
Add tofu and turn when slightly golden.
Lower heat and add turmeric.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Add other spices and garlic to taste.
Turn up heat a little.
Add nutritional yeast and tamari; cook another 2 to 5 minutes.
Serve with rice or pasta.
Kids love it!

title: mounds cake
directions: Bake cake in 8 or 9-inch layers.
When cool, slice each layer in half rounds.

title: crispy pickles
directions: Wash fresh cucumbers with brush, then soak in ice water for 2 hours.
Bring water, vinegar and salt to a boil.
Pack chilled cucumbers, garlic, cayenne and dill in clear hot jars.
Pour vinegar mixture over cucumbers and screw on lids.
Put jars in simmering water (2/3 of jars in water).
Simmer 10 minutes. Remove, screw down lids tightly.
Quickly invert, then right jars. Can eat in 2 weeks.

title: hot chicken or turkey salad casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese and potato chips. Place in 2-quart baking dish.
Spread shredded cheese over top. Add crushed potato chips.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: no-fail pie crust
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and make a well in the center (including the shortening).
Mix wet ingredients together (including egg) and beat well.
Add wet ingredients to well created in dry mixture.
Mix together well with pastry knife and form into a ball.
Refrigerate for 15 minutes, then divide into 4 equal sections and roll.
Makes 4 single crusts.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Put zucchini through food chopper or chop fine.
Combine with remaining ingredients except cheese and place in a greased casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Yields 6 servings.

title: chai
directions: On the stove, put water, tea and spices in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Reduce to low boil and simmer for 20 minutes. Strain and return to pan.
Add milk and reheat.
Makes 4 servings.

title: holiday squares
directions: Mix sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating on low speed of mixer after each one.
Add flour and vanilla.
Mix.

title: broccoli cheese bake
directions: Cook broccoli in 1-inch salted water for about 20 minutes. Drain and put in ungreased casserole.
Mix soup and milk until smooth, then pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Mix oleo and Bisquick until it is coarse.
Sprinkle over cheese. Bake uncovered for 20 minutes or until brown.
Bake in a 400° oven. Delicious.

title: ice cream cone cupcakes
directions: You will also need 2 or 3 muffin tins to hold ice cream cones, large table and spoon to fill cones.

title: quick bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar, shortening and salt.
Mix in 2 cups flour and mix for 1 minute at medium speed with hand mixer and then 2 minutes at high speed.
Add the other cup of flour and mix well.
Let mixture rise in a bowl about 30 minutes or until doubled. Beat dough down and place it in a greased loaf pan.
Allow it to rise about 40 minutes and then bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: 7-layer casserole
directions: Layer rice and 3 tablespoons water and the corn.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour over 1 can tomato sauce and 1/2 cup water. Layer chopped onion, pepper and ground beef.
Salt and pepper. Pour over 1 can tomato sauce and 1/4 cup water.
Cover with bacon. Cover.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Uncover; bake 30 minutes longer until bacon is crisp.

title: salt water taffy
directions: Make a sandwich out of your leftover spaghetti.
Top with a slice of velveeta cheese.
Butter both sides of your sandwich and sprinkle the buttered sides with garlic salt.
Grill till golden brown.
Then enjoy, yummy, yummy!

title: raspberry cream cheese coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9-inch spring-form pan.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup and level off to measure.
In a large bowl, combine flour and sugar.
Using pastry blender or fork, mix in softened (not melted) butter until it resembles coarse crumbs.
Add baking powder, baking soda, salt, sour cream, egg and almond extract.
Blend well.
Spread batter over bottom of spring-pan and up sides, about 1 to 2-inches. Batter should be 1/2-inch thick on sides.

title: red-eye fried rice with country ham
directions: Bring coffee to a boil.
Add rice and cook per directions.
In large frying pan, heat bacon grease on medium and add diced country ham and cook until light brown in color.
Add onions and cook until the onions are transparent.
Then fold in cooked "coffee rice." Heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Freeze completely.
Cut into squares to serve, after letting sit out of freezer for several minutes.

title: herb butter
directions: Let margarine soften, then combine with the herbs.
Let stand at least 1 hour before using to let flavors set.
Will keep in refrigerator several days or can be frozen.
Serve with bread, vegetables, meats, etc.

title: nellie's pecan dressing with giblet gravy
directions: Mix ingredients as listed.
Mix with spoon until well mixed. Place in greased and floured pan.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Part may be used for stuffing bird.

title: salmon spread
directions: Process onion until minced in food processor for 5 seconds. Add remaining ingredients and blend with quick on/off turns.
Then let run until smooth.
Scrape down bowl as necessary.
Chill and serve with crackers, fresh rolls or bagels or raw vegetables.

title: mary's dressing
directions: In large bowl, mix herb and cornbread stuffing.
Chop onions and celery; add 1 stick butter and cover with water.
Cook until soft.
When cooked, pour over stuffing mix.
Add eggs (beaten) and stir until mixed well.
Add chicken broth to mixture (using 1 can at first so as not to get it too moist).
Then add sage, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix completely.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° or 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until "dry" and golden brown.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Place graham cracker crumbs in a pie pan (deep).
Pour melted butter into crumbs.
Mix until moist.
Press all around pie dish, making a crust.
Place into a preheated oven at 350°.
Brown lightly.

title: banana-oatmeal-pineapple muffins
directions: Baking Temperature: 400°.
Baking Time: 20 minutes.

title: mitch's champion chile
directions: Over medium heat, brown beef, onion and garlic.
When the fat is liquified, add the jalapenos, pepperoncini, banana pepper, Tabasco and whiskey and allow to simmer until the onion is clear and the peppers are softened.
When this is complete, drain the excess grease.
In stockpot, combine the remaining ingredients (except chile powder and cumin) and allow to heat on low (medium heat while preparing the beef/chiles).
When the beans and sauce are complete, add the meat and add chile powder and shake Tabasco and cumin to taste.

title: ambrosia
directions: Combine all ingredients.
This salad is better if made ahead and allowed to sit in refrigerator.

title: hyde's green pea casserole
directions: Saute onions, celery and green pepper in butter until soft. Remove and mix with other ingredients, using juice from water chestnuts to dilute soup; mix well.
Pour into greased casserole. Cover with crumbs.
Bake at 350° until hot.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Beat egg.
Add evaporated milk and water.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour into oblong baking dish.
Add cooked and drained macaroni to liquid.
Add grated cheese.
Mix gently together. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Pour milk over crushed crackers and set aside.
Steam squash until tender.
Mash; add onion, salt, pepper and beaten eggs. Fold in cracker mixture and grated cheese.
Put in greased casserole and bake at 350° until set.

title: mexican slaw
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.
If you like it hot and spicy, add some hot peppers.
Great for large get togethers.

title: bran muffins and jam
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt.
Combine egg and milk; add to flour mixture, then add shortening and mix only enough to dampen flour.
Fold in cereal.
Fill greased muffin pans 1/3 full.
Spoon 1 teaspoon jam onto batter in each cup, then top with remaining batter.
Bake at 425° 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 8 muffins.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in an 8-quart pot.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat to medium and cook for 1 hour, uncovered.
Remove from heat.
Remove chicken from broth.
Strain broth through cheesecloth-lined colander.
Set aside 4 1/2 cups broth.
Reserve the rest for something else.
Bring 4 1/2 cups broth to boil.
Add potatoes and next 3 ingredients.
Cover and cook 5 minutes.
Add carrot and green onions; cover and cook 3 minutes.
Add mushrooms and peas.
Cover and cook 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Combine flour and next 3 ingredients in a bowl.
Add milk, blending with a whisk.
Add to vegetable mix.
Cook over medium heat 3 minutes or until thickened and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add chicken.
Spoon into 9 x 13-inch sprayed pan.

title: tri-color pasta casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine cooked pasta with pasta sauce and mix thoroughly.
Spoon half pasta mixture in 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Spoon Ricotta cheese evenly over pasta. Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Spoon remaining pasta mixture over cheeses.
Bake, covered, 25 to 30 minutes or until heated through. If desired, serve with additional sauce and Parmesan cheese.

title: tomato soup
directions: Combine tomatoes, bay leaf, onion and clove.
Cover; simmer for 10 minutes.
Combine butter and flour.
Add to tomatoes.
Add slowly to cold milk.
Heat to boiling.
Season to taste.

title: dirt cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix the margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
In another bowl, mix pudding and milk, then add Cool Whip. Mix well with the margarine, cheese and sugar.
Layer in plastic flower pot, first cookies and then pudding mixture.
Continue to alternate until top layer is cookies.
Arrange 3 to 4 gummy worms to top.
Insert plastic flower in middle of pot.

title: rich man's 3 layer mint brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In medium mixing bowl, cream 1/2 cup butter, 1 cup white sugar and vanilla. Then beat in the eggs, flour, salt and sauce.
Mix well; pour into buttered pan.
Bake for 30 minutes until done (toothpick test). Allow to cool thoroughly before proceeding.
(After initial 15 to 20 minutes, can put in refrigerator to hasten cooling.)

title: minestrone soup
directions: Heat oil in large saucepan.
Add garlic, onion, celery, and parsley;
cook until tender.
Stir in tomato paste and next 7 ingredients (down to beans).
Mix well; bring to a boil.
Lower heat; cover and simmer slowly 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Cook 10 to 15 min. or until macaroni is tender. Serve piping hot with plenty of cheese.
Makes 8 generous servings.

title: salmon in cabbage leaves
directions: Cut fillet into 4 equal pieces and place in shallow baking dish.
Combine next 4 ingredients, stirring well; pour over salmon. Cover and marinate in refrigerator 30 minutes.
Blanch cabbage leaves in boiling water 30 seconds.
Drain and rinse under cold water until cool; drain again.

title: dark chocolate frosting
directions: Cream butter until smooth.
Sift sugar and cocoa together and add to butter alternately with cream and vanilla, blending thoroughly.
To darken color, place in saucepan and heat over a very low heat, stirring constantly, until frosting is dark and glossy, about 5 minutes.
Spread on cake immediately.
Enough for 2 (8-inch) layers.
Also good on eclairs.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix together and chill for 24 hours.

title: mystery salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple.
Mix dry jello with whipped topping until thoroughly mixed.
Mix in the cottage cheese and the pineapple.
Stir mixture well.
Chill 4 hours or overnight in a covered dish.
Add pecans on top before serving.

title: anytime soup
directions: Combine the first 4 items in a large pot with 2 quarts water. Cook until celery is tender.
(If fresh carrots are used, add at the same time.)

Add tomato juice and bring to a boil. Add cabbage and cook until done. Add tomatoes, beans, carrots and bay leaf. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes. Remove from heat and add sprouts.

title: caramels
directions: Cook all but vanilla and nuts to 246° (soft ball stage).
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into well-greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
When cold, turn upside down on flat surface and let it fall out.
Cut in strips and then into pieces.
Wrap in squares of wax paper.

title: layered jello
directions: *Use any combination.
We like to make the colors fit the occasion:
red, white and blue for July 4th, etc.

title: chuck roast and rice
directions: Cut chuck roast into small pieces.
Put in 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with meat tenderizer.
Let set 1 to 2 hours.
Melt margarine.
Pour over meat along with Dale's sauce.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.
Drain juice from meat into large skillet.
Put in flour.
Stir over medium heat to thicken into gravy.
Add small amount of water to thin gravy.
Pour this back over meat; cook for another 20 to 30 minutes.
Pour meat and gravy over rice.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: burrito casserole
directions: Brown meat. Add beans, water, tomato sauce, and taco seasoning. Layer taco shells and meat mixture in a casserole dish. Top with cheese. Microwave for ten minutes or until warm. Or heat in oven at 250-300 degrees until warm.

title: swiss steak for six
directions: Mix flour, salt and thyme. Dredge steaks in mixture to coat. Sear steaks in 2 tablespoons hot oil to brown on both sides. Place in saute pan. Add thyme and bay leaf.
Pour in beef stock. Cover and simmer 1 hour. Turn steaks.
Add vegetables. Cover and simmer 20 minutes. Arrange on platter, vegetables on top. Sprinkle with fresh parsley.

title: crawfish or shrimp fettuccine
directions: Saute onions and bell pepper in oleo.
Add flour, parsley and crawfish or shrimp.
Cook on low for 15 minutes, stirring often. Add cheese, jalapenos, half and half and garlic.
Cook 15 minutes more on low.
Fold drained, cooked noodles into sauce.
Pour into 3-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake at 350°, uncovered, until bubbly and hot.
Better if prepared the night before, chilled and then cooked before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: old fashioned chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat 2 minutes. Combine dry ingredients and add alternately with cup of water, beating thoroughly.
Bake in greased and floured cake pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Mix broccoli with eggs, mayonnaise, onion, salt, pepper and soup.
Put into greased casserole.
Top with layer of cheese, then a mixture of stuffing and butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hamburger pizza
directions: Combine beef, egg, garlic salt, onion and 2 tablespoons tomato sauce. Flatten out mixture to line bottom and sides of large nonstick pie plate.
Bake in 450° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.
Remove from oven and pour on remaining tomato sauce. Sprinkle with cheese and oregano and return to oven for 5 to 7 minutes.
Cut in 6 pie shaped pieces.

title: broiled cubed steaks with barbecue sauce
directions: About 15 minutes before serving:
Preheat broiler.
In medium bowl, mix chili sauce, brown sugar, soy sauce and hot pepper sauce.
If steaks are large, cut each into serving size pieces. Dip each steak into chili sauce to coat.
Place steaks on rack in broiling pan.
With oven rack at closest position to source of heat, broil steaks 5 minutes without turning.
Spoon any juices in bottom of broiling pan over steaks to serve.
Makes 4 main dish servings.

title: holiday cranberry salad
directions: *Lemon, lime or pineapple can be used.

title: venus de milo soup
directions: In Dutch oven pan, brown hamburg until brown; drain.
Add all ingredients except orzo.
Bring to a boil.
Add orzo and simmer, stirring occasionally for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: squash dressing
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Mix the rest of ingredients; add to onion and celery.
Add salt, pepper and sage to taste.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Do not overbake.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Cover a cookie sheet with foil and spray with Pam.
Cover with graham crackers.
Boil ingredients, then pour over graham crackers.
Bake at 350°
for 8 minutes.

title: tamale pie
directions: Cook onion in shortening until tender.
Add corn, tomatoes, salt, chili powder and pepper.
Bring to boiling point; add cornmeal gradually, stirring constantly.
Cook about 20 minutes. Add well beaten egg, nuts, olives and meat.
Pour into baking dish with greased paper in bottom and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Bring berries to a boil and add sugar.
Pour into baking dish. Mix remaining ingredients and knead on floured board and place over berries.
Prick with fork a couple of times.
Bake at 350° for about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cheesy ham casserole
directions: Mix
all ingredients except 1/2 cup cheese.
Spoon into casserole
dish.
Sprinkle	remaining cheese on top and cover. Microwave on High for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: mae's angel biscuits
directions: Cut shortening into flour. Mix warm milk and yeast which has been dissolved in the warm water.
Add sugar.
Add all at once to flour and mix or knead until smooth.
Roll out, cut as for biscuits and place on a greased flat pan.
Let rise before baking. Bake at 425°.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Cook sugar, milk, butter and cocoa for 2 1/2 minutes.
Start counting when mixture has reached a full, rolling boil.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add oats, nuts, vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat well until mixture is blended well.
Spoon onto waxed paper.
Let cool until firm.

title: fruit tea
directions: Bring to boil 2 cups water, add tea bags and let steep. Meanwhile, in one-gallon container, mix orange juice, lemonade and sugar.
While tea is still hot, pour over juice mixture.
Mix well; add enough water to make a gallon.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all together. Chill dough. Make balls the size of walnuts. Press with glass dipped in sugar. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Stir pie filling in pineapple; mix in remaining ingredients and chill before serving.

title: coke salad
directions: Drain liquid from fruit.
Add enough water to equal 2 cups. Bring to boil.
Dissolve Jell-O in hot liquid.
Add Coke to this and remainder of ingredients.
Chill until firm.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients, then spread on ham.
Roll wide end of ham, then cut into bite size pieces.
Place toothpick in middle of ham.
Makes about 20 to 25.

title: pepper steak grill
directions: Pierce meat with fork and put about 2 teaspoons unseasoned meat tenderizer on it.
Let stand about 2 hours.
Mix remaining ingredients and marinate meat at room temperature for at least 2 hours.
Turn meat occasionally.
Pound 2 tablespoons cracked pepper into meat before grilling.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare vanilla pudding according to directions.
Divide everything in half and begin layering in punch bowl in this order: cake, coconut, cherries, pineapple, fruit cocktail, pudding, Cool Whip and nuts.
Repeat.

title: lime mist mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add pineapple juice.
Chill until slightly thick.
Beat until foamy.
Fold in pineapple, cottage cheese and mayonnaise.
Chill until firm.

title: crazy pie (coconut custard)
directions: Put all ingredients in blender at once.
Turn on blender. Count 1 to 10 slowly.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Refrigerate when cool.

title: grandma's pie crust
directions: Break egg in bowl; add water and vinegar.
Add to dry mixture. Makes enough for two (9-inch) pies, top and bottom.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger.
Heat soup and salt and pepper to taste. Place meat in baking dish.
Spread Tater Tots (don't thaw).
Pour soup over mixture and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Mix ingredients and sprinkle over the apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until apples are soft and topping is brown.
Serve warm.
Can use Cool Whip topping or ice cream on top.
If using 9 x 13-inch pan, double the recipe.

title: mrs. s's date bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat sugar and eggs; add butter and beat a little longer.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Fold in dates and nuts.
Line a 15 x 10-inch cookie sheet with waxed paper.
Pour mixture into cookie sheet and spread evenly.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares with sharp knife while still lukewarm.
Sprinkle with 10x powdered sugar before serving.

title: excellent almond toffee
directions: Melt the margarine and add the sugar.
When this mixture starts to boil, add the almonds.
Continue to cook on medium heat, constantly stirring until it turns the color of Brach's caramel.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Cream sugar and margarine well and add eggs, one at a time, beating until fluffy.
Add vanilla and almond extract.
Mix in flour mixture, alternating with the milk.
Fold in nuts and chocolate chips.
Pat batter into pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Test with toothpick for doneness.

title: sweet-n-sour pork
directions: Brown pork in 1 teaspoon oil and season with salt and pepper. Take pineapple juice and add water to make 1 cup.
Add 1 tablespoon tapioca and 1/2 cup barbecue sauce.
Add to meat and simmer for 45 minutes.
Add 1 green pepper, cut in strips, and 1 onion, sliced.
Add cubed pineapple and heat for 10 minutes. Serve over hot white rice.

title: toll house pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into pie shell. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: hamburger with tomato gravy
directions: To hamburger meat, add salt, onions and egg (slightly beaten). Make into patties and fry.
Brown flour in hamburger drippings; add tomatoes (blended) and pepper.
If gravy is too thick, add water.
Toast bread.
Place hamburger patties on toast and cover with gravy.

title: apple pie
directions: Cut up apples and mix all ingredients.
Place into pie shell; dot with butter.
Cover with pie dough.
Place in oven at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Put ingredients in baking dish. Top with Cheddar cheese. Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Serves 12.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Cook onion in one tablespoon of margarine with garlic (to taste) and salt and pepper for 15 minutes in casserole pot.

Add 3 cups of water, 1 tablespoon of margarine and 1 teaspoon salt. Cover the casserole and cook for 5 minutes, then add rice, chicken (cut up in size pieces that you like) and red (bell) pepper and cover and cook 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: sweet-hot mustard
directions: Soak mustard in vinegar overnight.
Beat 2 eggs and add sugar to mustard mixture.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Combine flour, oats, brown sugar and melted butter. Mix and pat half of mixture in 9 x 9 baking pan. Spread diced rhubarb over crust.

title: swedish cream
directions: Combine cream, sugar and gelatin; beat until sugar and gelatin are dissolved over medium heat.
Remove from heat and cool until slightly thick.
Add sour cream and vanilla.
Chill.
Serve over sweetened fruit such as raspberries or strawberries.

title: baptist dish
directions: Dice chicken.
Beat eggs slightly and add all ingredients except noodles.
Add noodles last.
Place in greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cut into squares and serve with topping of mushroom soup, slightly thinned.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Mix well until smooth.
Put vanilla wafer in cup cake paper. Spoon in batter.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: leek and pepper spoon bread
directions: In a large saucepan, cook leek and red pepper in hot margarine for 4 minutes.
Combine the milk and cornmeal; add to saucepan. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is very thick and pulls away from sides of pan.
Remove from heat.

title: slow-cooker broccoli casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine cottage cheese, broccoli, cheese, eggs, flour, butter or margarine, onion and salt.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased slow cooker.
Cover and cook on high for 1 hour. Stir; reduce heat to low.
Cover and cook for 2 1/2 to 3 hours longer or until a thermometer placed in the center reads 160° and the eggs are set.
Sprinkle with a little cheese if desired, then serve.

title: douvshaniyot cookies
directions: Mix flour, salt, baking powder and sugar.
Make a well.
Mix oil, beaten eggs, vanilla and milk.
Pour a little at a time in the well and mix.

title: favorite baked beans
directions: Draining the cans of beans is optional, depending on how watery the liquid looks in each can.
Mix all ingredients together in large casserole except for the bacon which is placed on top. Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.
If bacon is still a little fat, turn on broiler until crisp.
If possible, let sit at room temperature for 1/2 hour before serving.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; set aside.
Mix dry ingredients in order given.
Cut in shortening.
Stir in buttermilk and yeast mixture.
Blend thoroughly.
Turn dough on floured board; knead lightly as for regular biscuits; roll and cut.
Place on greased pan.
Let rise lightly.
Bake in 400° oven 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers.
Salt cucumbers.
Cover with water and soak for 1 hour.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Drain water from cucumbers.
Add other ingredients.
Let stand several hours or overnight.

title: pillsbury's "bread flour" bread
directions: Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off. In large mixer bowl, combine 2 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast; blend well.

In small pan, heat water and oil until very warm (120° to 130°); this heats very quickly. Add warm liquid to flour mixture. Blend at low speed until moistened; beat 3 minutes at medium speed. Stir in additional 2 1/2 to 3 cups flour until dough pulls cleanly away from sides of bowl. On floured surface, knead dough at least 10 minutes. Place dough in greased bowl and cover loosely with plastic wrap and cloth towel. Let rise in warm place until light and doubled in size. This comes up quickly.

title: western omelet
directions: Heat butter in medium-size nonstick frying pan over medium heat.
Add vegetables and ham; cook 4 minutes.
Season well.

title: classic brownies
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Chop the chocolate; put into ovenproof pan and melt the chocolate, stirring occasionally, until smooth. Remove chocolate and increase temperature to 325°.
Butter 9-inch square baking pan.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt with electric mixer; beat butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs 1 at a time.
Slowly beat in chocolate, then the vanilla.
Reduce speed to low.
Beat in flour mixture until mixed, then add walnuts.
Put in pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Cream together milk and sugar.
Melt marshmallows and add. Mix in other ingredients.
Pack into graham cracker box; refrigerate until firm.

title: walking tacos
directions: Spread bean dip on pizza pan; spread avocado dip over bean dip. Mix sour cream, Miracle Whip and taco seasoning.
Spread cream mixture over avocado dip; spread Jack cheese.
Then spread Cheddar cheese, then chili peppers, if wanted.
Then spread green onions, then chopped olives, then chopped tomato.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, nutmeg and salt. Work 1 cup butter into mixture as you would for pie crust.
In another bowl, beat eggs, sweet milk, vanilla and sugar.
Beat well and pour into first mixture, stirring until well mixed.
Drop by teaspoon on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake in hot oven at approximately 400° until golden brown, approximately 8 to 10 minutes.
Dough may be covered overnight in refrigerator to make rolled cookies.

title: ellen's curry chicken
directions: Cut chicken in bite size pieces.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and a little flour.
Fry in oil until golden brown.
Cook broccoli and place in bottom of 2 quart casserole.
Add chicken pieces.
Mix undiluted soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken, broccoli.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Cover with foil. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: sweet potato salad
directions: Peel and dice sweet potatoes and add rest of ingredients. Cover with the following:

title: sugar coated peanuts
directions: Mix together; microwave 6 minutes on roast, then stir. Microwave again for 10 minutes.
Pour on wax paper and cool.
Make sure to not use a bowl, use a flat dish to microwave mixture in.

title: "syllabub" appalachian folk drink
directions: Sprinkle nutmeg on top when served.
Serves 12.

title: asian beef and noodles
directions: Preparing Ham:
use a 50 pound lard can.
Trim and wash ham; cut the hock bone off and a small piece from the bottom of the ham so it will fit into the can.
(A saw may be used for this.)
Cover the ham with water overnight.

title: mediterranean pot roast
directions: On a plate, combine flour, salt and pepper.
Lightly dredge the roast in the seasoned flour.
Reserve the excess dressing mixture. In a flame-proof casserole, warm 2 tablespoons olive oil over medium high heat.
Add the roast and cook until brown on all sides, about 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, chop onions.
Remove roast and add 1 tablespoon oil, onions and garlic.
Saute until onions begin to brown.
Add the dredging mixture and stir until the fat absorbs the flour.
Add tomatoes, broth or wine, thyme and bay leaf.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 2 hours, turning roast from time to time.

title: dixie relish
directions: Mix vegetables together; cover with salt and let stand overnight.
Drain, then add spices, sugar and vinegar.
Pack into sterilized pint jars to within 1/2 inch of top.
Put on cap, screw band tight.
Process in boiling water for 10 minutes.
Yields 5 pints.

title: peach pie
directions: Place peaches, whole side up, in shell.
Mix cornstarch and sugar and pour in and around peaches.
Pour heavy cream over all. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 325° for 45 minutes until peaches are cooked.

title: artie's fruit cake
directions: Preheat oven
to
Cream	sugar and shortening in large mixing bowl;
add
flour,
baking soda, salt, nuts, raisins, dates,
candied
fruits and spices.
Heat applesauce and add to mixture.
Fold
together
until
mixture is completely consistent. Grease sides,
bottom
and
stem of an angel food cake tin.
Line with waxed paper.
Place fruit cake mixture in cake tin.
Bake 2 1/2 to 2 3/4 hours.

title: egg rolls
directions: Cook ground meat, onion and garlic until red is gone from meat. Add finely julienned cut carrots, green beans, bean sprouts and water chestnuts. Add soy sauce and oyster sauce. Cook until carrots have lost their firmness. Add cabbage and cook until soft crispy. Drain mixture in a colander until cool. Roll in wrappers. Add oil to a nonstick skillet and fry until golden brown.

title: sparkling cranberry punch
directions: Mix all ingredients; serve on ice.

title: kings cake
directions: First cream butter and sugar until soft.
Add eggs very slowly. Add lemon peel, juice, extracts and nutmeg.
Blend well.
Mix flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder together and add slowly, blending well.
Add chopped raisins, saving a few to sprinkle on top of batter.
Generously butter a loaf pan (9 x 5-inch) and sprinkle with plain bread crumbs.
Pour in batter, sprinkle with remaining raisins.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 90 minutes until golden brown and toothpick comes out clean.
(If batter seems too thick, add a few teaspoons of milk.)

title: white chocolate chip cookies
directions: *Or just use 1 1/2 cups white chocolate chips.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Add salt to tomatoes and onions.
Cover with ice water and let stand one hour.
Combine vinegar, sugar, celery and mustard seed in large saucepan.	Bring to a boil.
Drain tomatoes and onions. Rinse in cold water.
Add to previous mixture and let simmer until hot.
Do not boil.	Pack into hot sterilized jars and seal.
Makes about 5 pints.

title: grandma's frozen pudding
directions: Beat milk until firm; add the rest of ingredients.
Pour onto crushed graham crackers which line a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze until firm.

title: berry crotty's corn bread
directions: Mix in any order.
Bake in a 9-inch square pan for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: "joggin in a jug"(miracle drink)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shake or stir well. Refrigerate and drink 2 ounces each morning.
Better than Geratol!

title: massachusetts cranberry pie
directions: Grease a 9-inch pie plate or fluted quiche dish.
Add cranberries and sprinkle with nuts and 1/2 cup sugar.
In medium size bowl, beat egg with remaining 1/4 cup sugar.
Add flour and melted butter.
Beat until there are no lumps.
Pour over berry mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325°.
Serve with spoon.

title: sweet 'n sour salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in oversized bowl to avoid splatter.
Mix well with electric mixer until blended.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Prepare spinach according to pkg. directions. Drain and season with salt.

title: fruit dip
directions: Bring to boil eggs, sugar and lemon juice.
Cool.
Mix together remaining ingredients with cooled mixture until smooth.

title: reese cups
directions: Combine peanut butter, vanilla and margarine and beat until smooth.
Add sugar and mix well.
Refrigerate until mixture is firm.
Form into small balls, melt chocolate and dip balls.
Place on waxed paper or cookie sheet until hardened.
Makes approximately 4 dozen.
May be frozen.

title: birdseed bread
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix baking mix, cold water and garlic powder to a soft dough in bowl with fork.
Pat the dough on ungreased cookie sheet into a 10-inch circle.
Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Brush the dough circle with the melted butter.
Sprinkle with sesame seed and sunflower nuts.
Firmly press the seed and nuts into the dough with rubber scraper.
Cut the circle into 12 equal wedges (like a pie).
Bake in 425° oven 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm. (The bread will break into wedges.)

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix together sugar and Bisquick. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Place in well-greased pie pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes its own crust. Serves 6 large slices.

title: fried cornbread
directions: Add hot water in small amounts to cornmeal until it becomes a medium thin mixture.
In heavy skillet, add cooking oil; heat for a few minutes.
With large spoon, drop cornmeal mixture into the frying pan, being careful to keep the corn cakes apart.
Fry until golden brown on both sides.
Serves with a pat of butter on each.

title: tossed green salad
directions: Dice lettuce and tomatoes, onion and carrots.
Season to taste with favorite seasoning.
Mix well and serve immediately.

title: spinach balls
directions: 1. Mix all ingredients; chill 2 hours.

title: dark fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs beaten separately, yolks first.
Add flour with baking powder sifted through it.
Mix soda with syrup.
Add spices.
Add fruits, nuts and raisins that have been rolled in extra flour.
Add pineapple juice along as needed to help in mixing and make cake moist.
Put in large pan and bake at low temperature until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: cheese and broccoli
directions: Boil ham in water for 10 minutes.
Add broccoli; cook until tender.
Gradually add milk to flour, stirring until well blended. Add milk mixture slowly to ham mixture, stirring until thickens. Simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add cheese and seasonings.
Cook until cheese is melted.

title: cheesy macaroni bake
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees.
Spray a 6 cup shallow baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Cut cheddar and mozzarella cheese into 1/4 inch cubes.
In a large saucepan of boiling water, cook the macaroni until tender, 8 to 10 minutes, or according to package directions.
If using fresh broccoli florets, add them to the pasta 3 minutes before the pasta is done.
(If using thawed frozen broccoli, pat it dry with paper towels.)
Drain the macaroni (and fresh broccoli) and return it to the saucepan in which it was cooked.
Add the cheddar and mozzarella cheese, bacon bits, salt, and ground red pepper.
If using thawed frozen broccoli, add it here.
Spoon the mixture into the prepared baking dish, pour the milk evenly over the top, and bake until bubbly and golden, 18 to 21 minutes.
Approximately 4 - 6 servings.
Serving size 1 1/4 cups.

title: mexican beef casserole(overnight)
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with chips.
Brown the beef, drain and add chopped onion.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add the enchilada sauce and stir together.
In another pan, heat the soup, water and chopped chilies.
Pour hamburger over the chips.
Add the soup mixture and top with cheese.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Remove foil the last 10 minutes to brown.
Serve with lettuce, tomatoes, cheese and taco sauce.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms with damp paper towels; trim ends from stems. Combine salad dressing, pimiento and parsley in a large zip-top heavy-duty plastic bag.
Add mushrooms, tossing gently to coat with salad dressing.
Chill 20 minutes.
Yields 16 appetizer servings.

title: clams casino
directions: Saute onions and green pepper in 3 tablespoons margarine.
Put all other ingredients in a casserole dish.
Add onions, peppers and clam liquid.
Refrigerate for awhile.
Bake, uncovered, at 450° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Combine sugar, pudding, milk and butter in heavy pan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until boil.
Reduce heat; cook while stirring for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and nuts. Beat until thick and glossless.
Drop with a teaspoon on wax paper.

title: oaten wheat bread
directions: Mix oatmeal, whole wheat flour, dry milk, brown sugar and butter in a large bowl.
Add boiling water and stir to blend. Cool to room temperature.

title: banana split cake
directions: Blend butter and graham cracker crumbs together and place into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend to fluff and spread over crust the following ingredients:
confectioners sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla.
Slice bananas on top of mixture.
Add pineapple over bananas; top with Cool Whip and chill.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat; add bell pepper and onion.
Cook until onion is clear.
Add all other ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.

title: mother's butterscotch sauce
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat yolks until thick; add cream. Beat into butter and sugar.
Cook in double boiler until thick. Pour slowly over egg whites.
Serve hot.

title: rice pudding
directions: Place rice in 4-quart saucepan.
Add water to cover rice. Pour in 1-quart of milk.
Bring to a boil (15 minutes).
Place in a mixing bowl, egg, sugar, vanilla, lemon or orange extract and 1 quart of milk.
Beat well.
Add this mixture to boiling milk. Also add margarine.
Bring to a second boil.
Allow to simmer for 1 hour, stirring frequently.
Sprinkle with nutmeg or cinnamon to serve.
Makes about 1 1/2 quarts.
Fills 2 (6 x 8-inch) aluminum tins.

title: chocolate dream pie
directions: Mix pudding and add in Cool Whip.
Spread in pie shell.
Top with nuts, miniature Oreo cookies or M&M's.
Chill.

title: corn bread salad
directions: *Use as much as you want.

title: bean and turkey soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large pot; bring to a boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, two hours.
Serves 6.

title: george's cherry crisp
directions: Pour pie filling into 8-inch square baking pan.
In small bowl, combine flour and butter.
With pastry blender or 2 knives, scissor-fashion, cut in butter.
Add oats, brown sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg; mix well.
Sprinkle over cherries.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
If desired, serve topped with whipped cream.

title: sweet sour beets
directions: Put drained beets into 1 1/2-quart casserole with cover.
Mix sugar and flour.
Add water slowly; stir so that flour does not lump.
Pour over beets.
Put cover on, place in a 350° oven and bake for 45 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a lightly greased baking dish.
Sprinkle other 1/2 can of noodles on top.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: lisa's fudge brownie pie
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in a medium saucepan.
Remove from heat and stir in the sugar.
Add one egg at a time.
Add vanilla. Stir in flour and nuts.
Mix well.
Spread ingredients in 2 (9-inch) pie crusts or 1 deep dish pie crust.
Serve with vanilla ice cream and hot fudge sauce.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine sugars, butter and syrup and bring to a boil. Let cool, then add 2 beaten eggs slowly. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Top with nuts and cook slowly at 325° to 350° for 40 minutes.

title: madelyn's orange cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar;
add
egg
yolks
and
beat well. Add sifted dry
ingredients
alternately with juice and rind. Fold in beaten egg whites.	Bake
at 350° in two 8-inch round cake pans.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients together. Refrigerate overnight.

title: italian oysters
directions: In heavy saucepan, melt butter over low heat.
Mix in olive oil and heat a few more minutes.
Add all other ingredients, except oysters, and mix well.
Remove from heat.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.

title: ricotta cake
directions: Mix cake as directed.
Cream together Ricotta, sugar, eggs, lemon juice and lemon rind.
Put this mixture over cake batter. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Put over the cake a lemon pie filling.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Use a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.

title: chicken pie 2
directions: Boil chicken in water until tender.
Debone.
Cut chicken in bite-size pieces and place in 12 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In medium-size pot, bring to boil chicken broth and soup.
Pour over chicken.
In another bowl, combine margarine, flour, salt, pepper and buttermilk.
Mix to form batter; spoon over chicken.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes until brown.

title: pumpkin bisque
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add pumpkin, chicken broth, 2 cups water, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bring to a boil; then simmer for 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to low; add cream.
Gently heat until cream is warm.
Season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with scallions before serving.

title: chicken divine
directions: Place cooked broccoli in a 2-quart oblong dish.
Place chicken slices over broccoli.
Scatter toast over chicken.
Mix together the soup, mayo and cheese.
Pour over toasted cubes.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes, or until sauce bubbles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: garlic chicken fettucine
directions: Boil spinach fettucine and rinse; drain thoroughly.
Put 1 teaspoon of olive oil in large frying pan.
Saute 2 garlic cloves and cook chicken until done (15 minutes).
Remove chicken and drain on paper towel.
Add 2 teaspoons garlic and saute 2 garlic cloves. Add fettucine and chicken to heat.
Just before removing, mix in Parmesan cheese.
Garnish with grated Parmesan.
Serves 4.

title: bing cherry mold salad
directions: Measure juice from cherries and water to make 2 cups.
Heat and dissolve cherry Jell-O.
When partly set, add cherries.
Make lime Jell-O with water.
When partly set, break up and stir in cream cheese.
Place cheese Jell-O in bottom of mold.
Let it set up.
Put cherry mixture on top.
Serve squares on lettuce leaf.

title: cajun cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage in eight pieces.
Peel potatoes and onions; quarter them.
Place potatoes, onions, cabbage and pepper in pot; cover with stock.
Cook until tender.

title: carey's meat casserole
directions: Mix ground beef that has been browned and drained with cooked macaroni, soups, tomatoes and mushrooms.
Pour 1/2 of the mixture into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Spread 1/2 of the can of onion rings on top of the mixture.
Cook in oven at 300° for 25 minutes. Then spread the other 1/2 can of onion rings on top of the mixture.
Cook 5 more minutes in the oven.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli. Make sauce with cheese, butter, salt, milk and pepper.
Layer broccoli, sauce and crackers in baking dish.
Put layer of crackers on top and dot with about 2 tablespoons of butter.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: summer souffle
directions: Blend oil with flour and seasonings over low heat.
Stir in milk.
Continue stirring until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add to beaten egg yolks; mix well.
Add fish and cool.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.

title: dumplings
directions: Stir in enough flour to roll and cut.

title: beef in beer
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Slice beef (uncooked) about 1/2-inch thick. Arrange in large roaster.
Combine all ingredients except the veggies.
Pour over beef.
Seal with heavy-duty aluminum foil. Cook in oven for 2 hours.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook green beans and drain.
Mix in soup, cheese and water chestnuts.
Turn into buttered baking dish and top with onion rings.
Bake until bubbly and onion rings are golden (350°). Serves 8.

title: oven barbecued venison
directions: Trim fat.
Cut steaks into serving portions.
Sprinkle both sides with tenderizer if meat is tough or from older animal.
In skillet, heat margarine, cook steaks until brown on both sides. Place meat, single layer, in a baking pan.
Using skillet the meat was fried in, combine remaining ingredients (except wine).
Stir until well heated.
Pour over meat; cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours, or until tender.
Baste occasionally.
Remove foil; turn meat.
Add wine and bake 10 minutes more.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar, eggs, apples, nuts and vanilla.
Sift together the flour, salt, baking soda and spice.
Combine all ingredients well and bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan or a prepared tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour for tube pan or for 40 minutes for rectangular pan or until tester comes out clean.
Sift with confectioners sugar when done.

title: green beans
directions: Combine green beans and soup in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° until hot.
Sprinkle fried onions on top.
Heat until onions are golden brown.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Parboil cabbage, salting to taste. Drain. Mix soup, milk and mayonnaise. Set aside. Mix corn flakes and margarine. Put 2/3 of corn flake mixture in bottom of 2 or 3-quart casserole, then the drained cabbage. Pour the soup mixture over this and top with the rest of the corn flake mixture. Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: strawberry marshmallow whip
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Set bowl of gelatin firmly in a bowl of ice; whip with rotary beater until very light and fluffy.
Fold into whipped topping.
Fold in marshmallows and pineapple.
Pour into mold and chill until firm.
Serves 12.

title: chocolate cake roll
directions: Mix egg whites, cream of tartar and sugar until peaks form, then set aside for later use.
Beat egg yolks for 5 minutes. Blend in milk and vanilla and then add dry ingredients and mix at low speed until moistened.
Beat for 2 minutes on medium speed. Pour yolk mixture over egg whites and carefully fold in by hand until evenly blended.
Pour onto jelly roll pan that has been greased and lightly floured.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Roll up in clean dish towel that has been sprinkled with 10x sugar until cool.

title: ham and cheese biscuits
directions: Coat medium size nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Place over low heat until hot.
Add ham; saute 3 minutes.
Combine flour and next 3 ingredients in bowl.
Add milk and stir until moist. Drop batter by heaping teaspoonfuls into a baking sheet, coating well with cooking spray.
Bake at 400° for 22 minutes.
Yields 4 dozen biscuits.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix and add dressing.

title: pork and noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in salt water; drain.
Brown meat.
Add onions and celery.
Cook 10 minutes.
Put in buttered casserole dish in layers the noodles, peas, meat, tomato soup, water, cheese, salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: california coleslaw
directions: For dressing, combine vinegar, sugar, salt, white pepper and salad oil.
Combine vegetables and dressing.
Cover and chill. Will keep for several days in refrigerator.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: company jello salad(makes 8 plus servings)
directions: Heat crushed pineapple and add jello until dissolves.
Chill about 45 minutes until slightly congealed, then add buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Makes 9 x 13-inch Pyrex full.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat; spoon off excess fat.
Add next 5 ingredients. Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles as directed on box.
Combine remaining ingredients, except Mozzarella cheese.

title: salad
directions: Mix apples, pineapple, nuts and coconut together.
Mix sugar and cornstarch with pineapple juice from drained pineapple.
Cook together until it comes to a boil.
Let thicken.
Pour over the apple mixture.
Mix and stir in cheese.
Delicious.

title: honey-mustard coleslaw
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine all the vegetables.
In a small bowl, combine
remaining
ingredients,
stirring until blended.
Pour over cabbage mixture and toss to coat thoroughly. Healthy.
Makes 4 servings with 106 calories per serving.

title: crab cakes
directions: Drain and flake crabmeat.
Mix everything together.
Roll in cracker crumbs.
Fry in deep fat.

title: zesty clam dip
directions: Blend all ingredients in a blender or with an electric mixer. Serve with raw vegetables.

title: noodle mix(healthy mixes u-make)
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in a sealable container or zip-lock plastic bag. This will keep for 2 months in the pantry; however, I personally store in the refrigerator because of the cheese; plus it will last longer. Mark the date on the container or bag with a sharpie pen. This recipe doubles and triples well.

title: genuine southern fried chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with 2 teaspoons salt.
Place on platter, cover with wax paper and refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.
Pour 1 inch oil into large, deep, heavy skillet.
Add butter and heat over medium-high heat to 375°.
Meanwhile, rinse chicken under cold water.
Place flour, remaining salt and pepper in a paper bag.
Add half the chicken.
Shake to coat well.
Shake off excess flour.
Repeat with remaining chicken.
Place chicken into hot shortening in skillet in single layer so as not to touch.
Cook until evenly golden brown on both sides, turning once (about 15 minutes).
Drain well on paper towels.
Serve hot.
Serves about 6.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Combine carrots, onions and green pepper.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Chill overnight.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Cream 1/3 of sugar with butter or margarine and salt in large bowl.
Blend vanilla, 2 tablespoons milk and remaining sugar into mixture.
Gradually stir remaining milk into frosting until desired spreading consistency is reached.

title: grilled quesadillas
directions: Roast bell and hot peppers over gas flame or in broiler. Peel, seed and slice thinly.
Heat 2 tablespoons of oil in a large skillet over medium-low heat.
Add the red onions and saute until tender (3 to 4 minutes).
In a mixing bowl, combine Cheddar and Monterey Jack cheese.
Heat 1 or more skillets over medium-high heat.
Add 1/2 teaspoon oil in each pan to coat.
Place a tortilla in each skillet and sprinkle liberally with grated cheeses. Arrange some of the peppers, onions, tomatoes or sardines, in any combination you choose, on top of the cheese.
Sprinkle with cilantro, salt and pepper, then top with second tortilla.
Cook for 2 minutes, then flip quesadilla, then cook the other side for 2 more minutes.
Slide quesadilla onto a plate or rack.
Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Using a pair of kitchen scissors, cut quesadillas into eighths and serve with guacamole and chopped cilantro.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, baking soda and 3/4 teaspoon salt.
Set aside.
Cream sugar and shortening until light.
Add eggs, one at a time and then the milk, beating until smooth.
Add flour mixture and bananas alternately, beating until smooth.
Fold in the nuts.
Pour batter into lightly greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: chocolate pie filling
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, flour, cornstarch, egg yolks and salt.
Add enough milk to make a thick syrup.
Add syrup to hot milk.
Cook until thick.
Take off heat and add margarine and vanilla.
Cover and let cool.
Pour into an 8 or 9-inch baked pie crust.
Top with meringue, if desired.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat in oil in large frying pan over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Add garlic, tomato paste, water, onion, bay leaves, parsley, salt and pepper; mix well and cover.
Simmer 1 hour over low heat.
Grease 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover bottom with 1/3 cooked noodles.
Put on 1/3 cooked noodles, than 1/3 cooked sauce, then Mozzarella cheese and cottage cheese. Repeat in layers until used up.
Bake at 375°, until Parmesan cheese on top melts, for 30 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine butter and flour in a saucepan over low heat; gradually add chicken broth and milk, stirring constantly until smooth and thickened.
Stir in chicken, salt, pepper, mixed vegetables and peas.
Mix well.
Pour into a 13x9x2 inch baking dish.
Roll pastry to 1/8 inch thickness on a lightly floured surface.
Cut into strips 1-inch wide and arrange in lattice design over chicken mixture.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Combine pudding, cream cheese and milk.
Spread on top of baked cake.
Add in layers:
pineapple, Cool Whip, chopped nuts and coconut.

title: deer jerky
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place strips of meat 1/4 to 1/2 inch thick in marinade.
Marinate overnight, turning if necessary.
Lay marinated meat strips on oven rack.
Cook for 6 to 8 hours at 150°.
They get crisper the longer they bake.
Store finished jerky in Ziploc bags.
Jerky will keep up to 2 years.

title: egg beater custard
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Place in 6 custard cups.
Place in shallow pan with a little water in bottom.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
