title: peanut butter sheet cake
directions: Bring margarine, peanut butter, water and oil to a boil.
Cool sightly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into well greased and floured jelly roll pan or deep cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 375 degrees.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread in a large plate in the order given.
Top with chopped green onions (approximately 1 bunch), black olives or green peppers.
Serve with taco or tortilla chips.

title: baked and stuffed red snapper
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Wash fish thoroughly and set aside. Cream the 1/3 cup of butter and save the rest for later.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Stir in the lemon juice.
Rub the fish, inside and out, with the mixture.
Put the fish in a covered bowl and refrigerate for about 30 minutes.

title: spicy chicken drummettes
directions: Melt butter over medium heat and add red sauce.
Fry chicken in Fry Daddy until brown and float (6 to 8 at a time).
Place butter mixture into crock-pot, then add chicken.
Plug in and they stay warm all during the party.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Add salt, pepper and margarine to macaroni.
Put in baking dish.
Cube Velveeta and stir into macaroni.
Pour in milk on top of noodles.
Put grated cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes until milk is bubbly and cheese is browned.

title: peach bliss
directions: Heat crushed pineapple and dry peach gelatin to dissolve; let cool.
Fold in whipped topping and buttermilk.
Pour into an 8-inch square dish to congeal.
Cut into squares.
Serve on lettuce leaf topped with mayonnaise.

title: strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and spread in pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: royal frosting
directions: Beat sugar, egg whites and cream of tartar until very thick and very fluffy.
Keep covered with a damp towel at room temperature.
When dry, this frosting is like a hard candy.
Use to decorate cookies and to hold a gingerbread house together.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Butter a casserole dish.
Cream the soup and blend in drained, cooked green beans.
Place in dish.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°. Cover with onions and bake for another 10 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken casserole 3
directions: Pull chicken from bones and place in baking dish.
Combine soups and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with dry dressing. Pour broth over this and dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Beat
shortening, sugar and eggs until light.
Dissolve soda in	milk and add remaining ingredients.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: yorkshire country captain
directions: Cut chicken into large pieces.
Dredge with salt, pepper, curry powder, and flour.
Fry minced onion and pork until golden brown.
Add chicken.
Brown slowly.
Add water and bouillon cubes. Cover and simmer until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken from mixture.
Combine butter and flour.
Add to chicken broth.
Cook until smooth.
Cover chicken with gravy.
Garnish with sauteed almonds, and serve with rice.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Save a few noodles for the top.
Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until celery is done.

title: banana pudding
directions: Follow directions on pudding box.
Add sugar and vanilla. Stir until it begins to thicken.
Put cookies and bananas in a bowl.
Pour pudding over the cookies and bananas.
Put a plate on top of the bowl.
Let stand for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: granny's bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix eggs, 1 cup sugar, milk, vanilla and butter in a large bowl.
Tear bread into small pieces and spread in the bottom of a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle nuts and coconut over bread.
Pour egg mixture over this and let set for 5 minutes for bread to absorb moisture. Sprinkle top with the cinnamon and sugar. Bake 30 to 40 minutes until firm at 350°. Serve warm with whipped topping.

title: pam's 4 bean casserole
directions: Brown onions in bacon fat.
Add vinegar and brown sugar; cook 20 minutes.
Mix beans with liquid and bake 1 hour in 350° oven. Do not cover.
Stir occasionally.
Best made in advance, then reheat.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients; add milk, water and beaten egg yolks. Cook over hot water until thick.
Add vanilla; cool.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Use egg whites for meringue or use a whipped topping.

title: hurry up cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Drop egg into shortening.
Dump into flour mixtures; add milk and flavoring.
Stir very well.
Pour into small greased and floured cake tin.
Bake in moderate oven, about 45 minutes, or bake in shallow tin.
Frost.
Mark into squares and place half an English walnut on each square before icing hardens.

title: date roll
directions: Cut dates and marshmallows into small pieces.
Pour orange juice over.
Crush 2 packages of graham crackers fine and another pack not so fine.
Mix with other mixture.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine sugar and shortening.
Cream until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat until batter is light.
Add mashed bananas. Sift dry ingredients together and add to batter.
Stir until well blended.
Add nuts.
Bake in a greased loaf pan for 60 minutes at 350°.

title: cucumber delight
directions: Pack cucumbers, onion and green pepper in large jar.
When sugar in mixture is dissolved, pour mixture over preceding (don't heat) cukes, etc.
Refrigerate.
Add cuke, onion and green pepper slices as needed.

title: cranberry tea
directions: Heat cranberry juice and sugar until sugar is melted.
Add spices and 1 jar of water (same amount of juice) and orange juice. Slice lemons and squeeze into mixture.
Heat until the house smells good.
Serve with one cinnamon stick.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Heat until cheese melts.
Mix well.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Cook ground beef and garlic in 10-inch skillet over medium heat, stirring frequently, until ground beef is brown.
Drain and stir in Italian seasoning and spaghetti sauce.
Heat to boiling and remove from heat.
Spread 1/4 cup beef mixture in saucepan, 8 x 8 x 2-inches or 9 x 9 x 2-inches.
Top with 2 lasagna noodles.
Spread 1/3 of the cottage cheese over beef noodles.
Sprinkle with 1/3 of the Monterey Jack cheese on top.
Repeat layers twice.
Bake about 10 minutes or until hot and cheese is melted.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Pour apple pie filling into frozen pie crust.
Combine remaining ingredients thoroughly and sprinkle over pie filling.
Cook for 30 minutes.
If you prefer, sprinkle additional cinnamon and nutmeg to taste over pie filling and mix together before adding topping.

title: 7 layer mexican dip
directions: Layer refried beans on platter.
Mix taco seasoning mix and sour cream; add this to beans.
Add rest of ingredients one at a time.
Chill.

title: honey cookies
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, eggs, milk and honey.
Add dry ingredients.
Chill dough.
Roll pieces of dough in walnut size balls.
Roll balls in granulated sugar.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: harvest muffins
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line with paper cups or grease bottoms and sides of 18 muffin cups.
In large bowl, combine all-purpose flour, whole wheat flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon, salt and cloves.
Add apples, carrots, coconut, raisins and nuts; mix well. Add oil, milk, vanilla and eggs.
Stir just until moistened. Fill paper-lined muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Immediately remove from pan.
Serve warm.
Yields 18 muffins. These freeze well.

title: banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding according to package directions using milk. Fold in 1 cup Cool Whip.
In bottom of 2-quart round baking dish, layer wafers, sliced bananas and pudding.
Continue to layer, ending with topping on top.
Chill 3 hours.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: ranch biscuits
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in buttermilk and salad oil.
Add to dry ingredients.
Dough can be kept in refrigerator for at least 1 week.
Take out as needed.
Roll out; cut with biscuit cutter and bake at 375° until done.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Stir together the first 5 ingredients in saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat until thickened.
Cool.
Add berries, sliced vertically (quartered if very large).
Pour into baked pie shell.
Refrigerate.

title: bird's nest soup
directions: Prepare noodle soup as directions on package instruct.
When noodles are almost all the way cooked, crack eggs into soup and cover pan.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes longer, low heat, or until egg is cooked.
Serve garnished with scallion tops and crackers on the side.
Serves 2.

title: library chopped apple cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs in a big bowl.
Add vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients; add to sugar mixture.
Add apples and nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until done.

title: spinach roll-ups
directions: While lasagna noodles cook, mix together remaining ingredients for filling.
Spread 2 to 3 tablespoons on each cooked noodle and roll up end to end.
Stand up in a 2-quart casserole, or an 8-inch square pan.

title: red's perfect cake
directions: Gently beat way to cake aisle in favorite supermarket. Stand in line 10 minutes. Repeat first 3 steps. Yields 1 or more perfect cake every time.

title: stuffed plantains(signature dishes)
directions: You will need nonstick cooking spray and 6 pieces of 12 x 12-inch foil.

title: aunt dow's king ranch chicken
directions: Boil hen in water seasoned with onion, celery, salt and pepper.
Cut hen in bite sized pieces and reserve all stock.
Chop onion and bell pepper.
Combine soups and grated cheese.
Just before putting casserole together, soak frozen tortillas in the stock until wilted.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips on low heat.
Add peanut butter, marshmallows and peanuts.
Mix and let cool. Spread in large pan and cut into squares.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients and pour into greased (butter or oleo) 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread 1 box yellow cake mix over top and pat down evenly.
(Use dry mix.)
Spread 1 cup chopped walnuts or pecans on top.
Pour 1 cup melted margarine over all.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.
Should set like pumpkin pie.
Cut; turn over.
Serve with ice cream.

title: mandarin chicken salad
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients. Mix well. Cover and chill for 2 hours. Fold in pecans just before serving.

title: tamale pie
directions: Smash tamales with fork (save juice).
Add both corns together.
Add chili powder.
Grease dish.
Pour mixture in dish and add smashed crackers.
Add the 4 dots of oleo.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: cherry pudding
directions: Put cherries into buttered dish sprinkled with sugar and cinnamon.
Mix together flour, sugar, milk, margarine and baking powder.
Pour batter over cherries.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Mix flour, salt and pecans together.
Mix butter or margarine, sugar and vanilla together.
Combine mixtures.
Roll into balls and flatten slightly.
Place on cookie sheet sprayed lightly with Pam.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar when cooled or shake, a few at time, in a clean bag.

title: microwave stuffed peppers
directions: Wash peppers.
Cut in halves lengthwise and remove seeds and white membrane.
Crumble beef into a 1 1/2-quart casserole; add onion.
Cook, uncovered, on High for about 5 minutes, stirring once during cooking period.
Cook until meat loses its red color. Stir in salt, pepper, rice and half the tomato sauce.
Fill green pepper halves with mixture, mounding mixture on top.
Place in a glass baking dish.
Top each pepper with a dribble of remaining tomato sauce.
Cook, covered, on High for 8 to 10 minutes or just until peppers are tender.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Mix all ingredients well in a bowl.
Bake at 350° covered about 1 hour.
(Stir about half done to mix the cheese.)

title: foil dinner for 12
directions: For Each Serving:
Cut up potato and 1/2 onion into small pieces.
Cut carrot into sticks.
Make a patty of 1/4 pound hamburger.
Place all ingredients side by side on a piece of aluminum foil.
Season with salt, pepper and 1 tablespoon cream of mushroom soup.
Wrap foil; put packet in the embers.
Cook for 10 to 20 minutes.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix jello and puddings with 3 cups water.
Bring to a boil and cook for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Add oranges (I crush the oranges) and Cool Whip.
Mix together and cool.

title: holiday punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in cranberry juice cocktail.
Add remaining fruit juices.
Pour over ice cubes.
Add ginger ale at serving time.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Wash fresh picked lettuce and drain well.
Break or cut into pieces into bowl.
Slice onions over top.
Add salt and pepper. Fry about 6 slices bacon until crisp; remove from skillet.
Pour hot grease over vegetables.
Mix; stir until lettuce is wilted. Crumble cooked bacon over the lettuce.
Serve immediately.
Six tablespoons of vinegar can be added to hot grease.

title: easy pot roast
directions: Place meat on a large piece of heavy aluminum foil.
Pour over chili sauce and sprinkle with onion soup.
Top with sliced onions and fold up tight in foil.
Bake at 350° for 4 hours.
(Do not open until done.)

title: corn pudding
directions: Thoroughly mix softened butter and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add sifted flour and salt; mix.
Add corn and milk and mix well.
Pour into slightly greased 1-quart baking dish at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate dessert(best to make the night before)
directions: Melt margarine.
Add flour and pecans.
Spread in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Cut cheese up and pour milk over it.
Put butter with milk and cheese.
Cook in top of double boiler until it thickens.
Drain all juice from pimentos and mash real fine.
Pour cooked mixture over the pimento and add mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Mix well. Very good in stuffed celery.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Makes 5 or 6 servings. (One-half cup chopped pecans may be added, if desired.)

title: bourbon bites
directions: Skin hot dogs.
Cut into bite-size pieces.
Combine the remaining ingredients and pour over the hot dogs.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 3 hours.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown hamburger meat in skillet; drain the liquid off the meat.
Add Lipton stroganoff package, cream of mushroom soup and milk.
Stir all ingredients and simmer until noodles are tender.

title: pudding cones
directions: Stir milk into pudding mix and beat 1 minute.
Set ice cream cones in a small glass to keep them from falling over.
Spoon pudding into cones and top with whipped topping.

title: easy egg nog
directions: Mix together in blender. Serve.

title: berry good french toast bake
directions: Generously grease 2 1/2-quart casserole or a 9 x 13-inch pan. Beat eggs, flour, milk, sugar, vanilla and salt until smooth. Stir in bread cubes. Pour bread mixture into pan (or casserole). Top evenly with cream cheese cubes and the blueberries. (May add 1/2 cup nuts, if desired.) Cover and refrigerate up to 24 hours. Heat oven to 400°. Uncover pan and bake 20 to 25 minutes (or until golden brown). Sprinkle with powdered sugar and/or serve with flavored syrups.

title: praline cookies
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt; set aside.
Cream butter.
Add brown sugar gradually, creaming well.
Blend in egg, vanilla and dry ingredients; mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa.
Add remaining ingredients and beat well with electric mixer for 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
May be topped with ice cream or Cool Whip.
Does not need refrigeration.

title: jello poke cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Blend, then beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Dissolve Jell-O as directed on package.
Poke holes in cake with chopstick (about 1-inch apart).
Pour dissolved Jell-O over cake.
Chill 4 hours.
Spread Cool Whip over top to serve.

title: chocolate mint snow-top cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Over hot (not boiling) water, melt 1 cup mint chocolate chips, stirring until smooth.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Mix egg, garlic powder and Parmesan cheese.
Toss with cooked spaghetti.
Place in a large pie pan or dish making a pie shell. Combine sour cream, cream cheese, and 1/2 Cheddar cheese; place on top of spaghetti. Top with sauce and remaining cheese.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into casserole.
Cook at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 3 or 4.

title: baked lemon steak
directions: Cut steak into 4 to 6 pieces.
Slice 1 lemon and 1 onion and place into a baking pan on the bottom.
Mix ketchup, Worcestershire sauce and 2 tablespoons of water.
Pour half of mixture into pan.
Salt and pepper steak if desired.

title: eggless chocolate cake
directions: Mix together the following ingredients in a 9 x 9-inch pan: flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Make 3 wells in dry ingredients.
Into Well #1, add 1/3 cup oil.
Into Well #2, add 1 tablespoon vinegar.
Into Well #3, add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Over all, pour 1 cup cold water.
Mix thoroughly in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Wash potatoes; make a deep crisscross slash in each and fill with butter and a little chopped onion.
Wrap in double thickness of heavy foil and place right on the coals for about 40 minutes. Open carefully to avoid steam.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Swish egg.
Add mayonnaise and soup.
Blend.
Stir in cooked broccoli, chopped onion and cheese.
Turn into baking dish.
Top with bread crumbs, mixed nuts and 2 tablespoons butter.
Top with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in skins whole until done.
Fry bacon.
Stir in onions; do not drain.
Mix sugar, flour, bouillon, salt, pepper, vinegar and water.
Add to bacon and onions.
Stir until thickens slightly.
Peel and slice potatoes.
Add to sauce; toss lightly.

title: cheese dip
directions: Soak soup mix in hot water for 30 minutes.
Add worcestershire sauce, blend into cream cheese.
Beat to make a smooth paste.
Add milk.
Beat well again.
Serve with vegetables or crackers.

title: beef pot roast
directions: Peel and cut vegetables; place in crock-pot.
Cut meat to fit pot.
Combine other ingredients and pour over meat and vegetables. Cover and cook 10 to 12 hours on low; 5 to 6 hours on high.
For more gravy, double water and spices.

title: herb marinated chicken breasts
directions: Stir together mayonnaise, wine and seasonings.
Pour dressing over chicken.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight. Drain, reserving dressing mixture.

title: rice pudding
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, combine eggs, milk, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Add rice and raisins.
Mix well.
Microwave on High, uncovered, just until thickened, 8 to 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Let stand 30 minutes without stirring.
Serve warm or chilled with light cream.

title: easy deer roast
directions: Coat roast with flour.
Heat shortening and brown roast on all sides.
Place roast in Dutch oven or electric slow cooker. Sprinkle flour in hot shortening and stir.
Brown for 2 minutes. Add water to thin gravy.
Pour over roast.
Douse roast with onion soup mix.
Cover tightly and simmer or bake at low heat (250°) until tender, about 1 1/2 hours per pound of roast.
Roast cooks best at low temperature.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: Add potatoes
to chicken broth.
Beat egg with milk and salt and add enough flour
for a stiff dough (like pie dough). Roll out and cut in	squares.
Drop	in
boiling chicken broth and cook until done, around	20 minutes.
Make a little thickening and put in when
finished.	Parsley
may be added if you have some.

title: tortilla roll-up appetizers
directions: Mix together softened cream cheese, olives, jalapeno peppers and garlic salt.
Spread mixture on tortilla and roll up. Refrigerate overnight or until chilled.
Cut into 1/2-inch pieces. Serve.

title: flower pot pudding(diet pudding)
directions: You will also need a 6-inch flower pot, lined with foil and silk flowers.

title: seven-minute pickles
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Cook in microwave oven on High for 7 minutes.
Cool for 7 minutes.
Pack into a jar.
Chill. Yield: about 1 pint.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cocoa.
Work with a spoon until smooth.
Add mayonnaise and sugar to dry ingredients, alternating with water.
Add vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Turn into a 9-inch greased square pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: june's hot artichoke dip
directions: Drain and chop artichokes. Combine all ingredients. Bake at 350° until hot, about 20 to 30 minutes. Serve with chips.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Blend oil and sugar in mixer.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour, soda, salt and vanilla.
Fold in apples and pecans.
Bake in Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and put in baking dish.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In an electric skillet, combine sugar, butter and evaporated milk.
Bring to a boil.
Cook for five minutes.
Turn off heat and add remaining ingredients.
Stir until all is melted and well blended.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: creamsicles
directions: Cook until thick and smooth, stirring frequently.
Cool.
Pour in molds and freeze.

title: apple-rice salad
directions: Cut apple and celery into small pieces.
Add carrot, raisins and corn.
When rice has cooled, add a little at a time so that rice is evenly distributed.
About an hour before you want to use it, mix with 3 to 4 tablespoons of mayonnaise.
Top with a pinch of paprika.
Serves 4.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken (boil or steam); defat and debone.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, curry and lemon juice, while simmering broccoli to cook.
Place broccoli on top of chicken in baking dish.
Pour on the sauce and bake 20 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top last few minutes and brown.

title: banana berry pudding
directions: Combine pudding mix according to package directions using pudding mix and milk.
Fold in sour cream.
Line bottom of a 3-quart glass bowl with some vanilla wafers.
Top with a third of the strawberries and blueberries.
Spoon one-third of pudding mixture over fruit.
Repeat layers twice using the remaining wafers, bananas, strawberries and blueberries and pudding mixture.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel potatoes and dice small.
Add water, salt, black pepper and margarine.
Cook under cover until done.
Good to eat on a cold day.

title: better than beer cheese dip
directions: Chop onion in food processor.
Add remaining ingredients to processor and process until smooth.
Slice top off of round loaf of pumpernickel rye.
Tear out middle of loaf, leaving a 1-inch rim.
Fill with cheese dip.
Use bits of bread for dipping in the cheese.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Open all cans into crock-pot, crushing tomatoes.
Chop cabbage up into fine, long strips (like cole slaw), adding to crock-pot. Dice onion up.
Brown hamburger, draining grease off.
Add to crock-pot.
Salt and pepper well.
Crock-pot will appear full, but will cook down as the day rolls on.
Let cook in crock-pot on low for 6 to 8 hours.

title: chocolate chip pudding cake
directions: Place cake in large bowl.
Cook pudding according to directions.
Pour hot pudding into dry cake mix.
Mix until dry cake is moist (do not overbeat).
Pour into greased pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top and add nuts on top.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes (check in 20 minutes) in a 350° oven.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Boil cut up meats until tender, then cut in small pieces.
Cook vegetables until tender.
Add meat to vegetables; add paprika and Tabasco.
If desired may add few drops of Texas Pete if you like it hot.
Simmer on low heat until thick.
Stir, so it won't stick to pot.

title: garlic and beer marinated shrimp kabobs
directions: Peel shrimp.
Make a shallow cut lengthwise down back of each shrimp and wash out vein.
Mix remaining ingredients in shallow glass or plastic container.
Stir in shrimp.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Set oven control to broil.
Remove shrimp; reserve beer marinade.
Thread shrimp about 1-inch apart on 15-inch metal skewers.
Place on rack in broiler pan.
Broil kabobs about 4-inches from heat for about 5 minutes, turning and brushing with marinade once until shrimp are pink.
Serve with melted margarine or butter and lemon wedges, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: plum cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and cinnamon.
Add baby food, eggs and oil; mix well.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Cool.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Stir in Cheddar cheese, green onion and mustard in cream cheese.
Spread cheese mixture on ham slices.
Roll ham from narrow end.
Cut each roll into 4 pieces.
Secure with wooden toothpick.
Microwave at High for 30 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger and onion, drain.
Add remaining ingredients and mix together until warm.
Add about 1/4 cup water to get desired consistency.
Serve on hamburger buns.
Makes 8 to 10.

title: chicken salad sandwich
directions: Mix all together. Serve in a sandwich with your favorite bread or serve with crackers.

title: "salmon" macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until tender in boiling water; drain. Mix in 2-quart bowl the macaroni, cream of celery soup, evaporated milk, pimiento and 1/2 cup American cheese. Drain salmon and break into pieces. Add to macaroni mixture; stir. Pour into 1 1/2-quart greased baking dish. Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup cheese around edges of dish. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until bubbly hot. Makes 4 servings.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Soak oatmeal in boiling water.
Preheat oven to 350°.
While oatmeal cools, cream butter and sugars.
Beat in eggs, vanilla and oatmeal.
Mix flour, salt and baking soda in a bowl and add to mixture.
Pour into 9 x 13 cake pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Combine the ingredients.
May serve hot or cold.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips in double boiler over hot water.
Add peanuts.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper lined tray.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Store in airtight container.
May add coconut, raisins, crispy rice cereal or other favorite ingredients.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: blueberry "grunt"(to die for!)
directions: Blend flour, margarine and sugar.
Add nuts (chopped).
Spread with your hands into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes (it won't look browned).
Cool completely.

title: pecan squares
directions: Spread crescent rolls out and press in pan to make a crust. Use a large pan so crust will be thin. Be sure there are no holes in crust. Pour Eagle Brand milk over evenly. Sprinkle whole box of frosting mix over this, then drizzle melted butter over all. Bake at 350° until golden brown. Cool completely and cut into squares.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into oblong baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: curried chicken with apricots and green peppers
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, saut chicken strips in 1 tablespoon olive oil about 6 minutes, until no longer pink. Add green pepper, onion, curry powder and remaining oil. Stir and cook until peppers are tender-crisp, about 2 or 3 minutes. Stir in apricots without the juice. Heat apricots for about 1 minute.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Mix lemon jello and orange jello with hot water and cold water.
When thickened, add crushed pineapple.
Keep pineapple juice.
Add marshmallows.

title: strawberry creme squares
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add berries, stirring until thawed.
Pour 1/2 in square 9 x 9-inch pan.
Chill until firm. Spoon creme over in even layer.
Pour remaining Jell-O over creme. Chill until firm.

title: mock potato salad(diet)
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.
Serves 2.

title: southern fried chicken with creamy gravy
directions: *This is important because the pieces will be smaller and will cook through to the bone more quickly.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Combine ingredients in a 3-quart casserole or 9 x 13-inch pan. Cook for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix cherry pie filling and pineapple with juice; stir in bowl until well mixed.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix on top of mixture.
Pour melted butter over cake.
Sprinkle pecans or walnuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let cool and serve.

title: curried rice salad
directions: In a small bowl, mix the first four ingredients.
Set aside.

title: chicken wings
directions: If you can't find "drummettes" buy a package of 12 chicken wings; remove wing tips and break each into two pieces.

title: creamy clam bisque
directions: In medium saucepan, cook onion in margarine until tender. Gradually stir in flour and pepper.
Add clam liquid and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Beat half and half with egg yolk.
Stir into pan along with clams.
Heat through (do not boil).
Serve with crackers.

title: beef noodle bake
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain.
Add salt, sugar, tomato sauce and water.
Cook at low heat for 20 minutes.
Cook and drain noodles.
Add cream cheese as soon as noodles are drained and cheese will melt.
Add sour cream.
Put layer of noodles and layer of meat, etc.
(I put noodles on bottom because there is not enough to layer.)
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: christmas east fruit cake
directions: In bowl, mix the flour with the fruit cake mix, raisins and nuts.
Set aside.
In another bowl, mix gingerbread mix with orange juice.
Add all of the fruit and nuts to the batter.
Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/4 hours.
Cool.
Pour apple juice or plain white syrup over top to make it soft.
To wrap and freeze, turn bottom side up.

title: oven barbecued chicken
directions: Flour chicken as for frying.
Roast for 30 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.
Melt butter in a frying pan; add onion and brown lightly.
Add water and remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 5 minutes. Pour over chicken and bake for 30 more minutes.

title: symphony bars
directions: Beat together and divide dough in half.
Put half in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add 2 ounces melted chocolate to other half and spread on top of first layer.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cranberry salad(fruit salad)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a mold and freeze. Serve in frozen slices.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onion in butter until limp; blend in flour. Add broths and water. Simmer for 30 minutes. Serve with croutons. Garnish with shredded Mozzarella cheese if desired.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer chicken chunks; mix soup and broth and put on top of chicken.
Combine cracker crumbs and margarine.
Top casserole with crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: delicious sausage-potato casserole
directions: Brown sausage links in a skillet; remove.
Add butter to drippings and saute onion until tender.
Stir in soup and milk; heat through.
Place potatoes in a 2-quart casserole and pour in soup mixture.
Top with cheese, then sauerkraut.
Bury the browned links in the sauerkraut.
Place remaining sausages in a pinwheel design on top of casserole.
Sprinkle with caraway seed.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: cranberry crunch
directions: Mix and pat 1/2 of this mixture into buttered cake pan. Spread 1 can of cranberry sauce over this.
Sprinkle rest of mixture over this.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Layer bread, sausage and cheese into a casserole dish.
Mix eggs and milk and pour over other ingredients.
Let set in fridge overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: golden baked pork chops
directions: 1. Heat oven to 375°.
Spray 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.
In shallow bowl, combine bread crumbs and margarine; mix well.

In another shallow bowl, beat egg with fork. 2. Dip pork into egg; coat with bread crumb mixture.* 3. Place in sprayed pan. 4. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until pork is no longer pink, turning once halfway through baking.
Makes 6 servings.

title: croquette sauce
directions: Melt butter; add flour and thoroughly mix.
Add all other ingredients and cook until very thick, stirring slowly while cooking.

title: chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients together.
Roll into small balls about 1 inch in diameter.
Melt the rest of the ingredients in a double boiler.
With a toothpick, dip balls into the chocolate mixture.
Cool on wax paper.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients with wet ingredients.
Beat well. Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°. Makes one loaf.

title: coconut cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, Crisco and cream cheese.
Add sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Combine flour and baking powder; add flour mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in flavorings and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or so.

title: ceviche
directions: Cut up fish in small pieces; pour lots of salt over.
Place in refrigerator 2 to 3 hours.
Chop up other ingredients.
Wash fish well after refrigeration time; pat dry.
Add rest of ingredients; squeeze lime juice and vinegar over fish, enough to cover.
Mix and refrigerate overnight.
The lime juice marinade cooks the fish.

title: eggs lorraine
directions: Spread butter in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pat half of the cheese in the bottom of the pan.
Beat eggs, just a little, and pour on top of cheese.
Add a little salt and pepper.
Put drained mushrooms on top of eggs, then add cream.
Next layer on the sausage and the rest of the cheese.
Let sit overnight.
Next day, bake at 350° for 60 minutes or until set.

title: instant hot chocolate mix
directions: Sift powdered sugar; mix well with other ingredients.
Store in airtight container.
To serve, measure 1/3 cup mix into cup and finish with hot water.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cut broccoli in small pieces.
Saute onions in small amount of margarine.
Mix all ingredients together and pour in buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
If cooked rice is used, just cook until casserole is hot, about 20 minutes.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain and add spices.
Stir in tomato paste and water.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Place on bun halves.
Top with cheese and broil until cheese melts.

title: peanut butter no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter and bring to boil for 1 minute, stirring well.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Drop onto waxpaper.
Cool.

title: easy cream cheese fruit squares
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

title: fried eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant and cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Sprinkle eggplant with salt and set aside for 10 minutes to remove bitter juice. When ready to fry the eggplant, squeeze the liquid from it or press it between paper towels to dry.
Fry in oil until brown. May be combined with laban.
Excellent in a sandwich with sliced tomato and onion.

title: autumn evening supper
directions: Mix lightly the first 5 ingredients.
Spoon into baking dish. Top with the sausage.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with triangles of cheese slices. Bake a few minutes more until cheese begins to melt.

title: double pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle brown sugar evenly in pan.
Arrange pineapple slices and cherry halves on the sugar mixture.
Mix cake according to package directions (do not substitute pineapple juice for water).
Beat as directed on package.
Pour batter over fruit.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes, or until toothpick inserted comes out clean. Let stand 5 minutes.
Turn upside down onto a large platter or cookie sheet.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Cook pineapple with juice, jello, baby food and sugar until dissolved.
Let stand until partially thick.
Whip or blend cream cheese and milk.
Stir all together and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with chopped nuts, if desired.

title: boiled pudding
directions: Add enough flour to make a very stiff dough (one that can still be stirred).
Spoon into a cloth that has been greased and floured.
Tie with string about the width of 3 fingers from where dough has been gathered into a bag.
Boil at least 3 1/2 or 4 hours.
Take out of rag as soon as removed from pot of boiling water.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in sugar and syrup.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes without stirring. Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and soda.

title: frazaline
directions: Fry the hamburger.
Add the onion, green pepper and celery; fry until tender.
Cook the noodles.
After noodles and meat mixture are cooked, put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add corn, soup, olives and cheese.
Save a little cheese for the top.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 375°.

title: beef and vegetable eggrolls
directions: Saute minced garlic and onion in hot skillet with oil in it. Add the ground beef until brown and done.
When the ground beef is done, add all vegetables, 1/2 salt, 1/2 pepper and 1 tablespoon oyster sauce.
Simmer it at least 4 minutes (don't overcook the vegetables).
Let cool and put in colander to drain.
After cooled, spoon some of the mixture onto an eggroll wrapper and wrap it.
Fold both sides and roll it.
Brush with flour and water on underside flap to seal.
Deep fry at 350° in 1/2 inch of oil for 3 to 8 minutes, turning onto both sides for even color.
When brown, ready to serve.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix beans and soup together.
Pour into a casserole and put Durkee French fried onions on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: huckleberry cheesecake pie
directions: Cream together butter, 2 tablespoons sugar, salt and flour. Blend well; press into sides and bottom of 9-inch pie plate.
Be careful not to cover rim.
Bake for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown onion and garlic.
Add ground beef.
Cook until done; drain.
Set aside.
Cut sausages into small slices and fry until well done.
Add to ground beef mixture.
Add tomato sauce and paste.
Season to taste.
Add dash of sugar; simmer.
Cook noodles as directed; 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in cold water until ready to use.
In bowl, combine Ricotta cheese, egg, cottage cheese and parsley; mix well.
Drain noodles.
Put layer of noodles in pan, spoon on sauce, cheese mixture and Mozzarella cheese.
Continue, ending with Mozzarella.
Cook 45 to 55 minutes at 350°.
Let cool 10 minutes before cutting.

title: pasta with spinach
directions: Stem, wash, drain and coarsely chop spinach leaves.
Set aside.
Cook pasta as package label directs.
Drain.

title: strawberry perfection salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Mix in ice cream and orange juice until well blended.
Chill until partially set.
Add drained pineapple and nuts.
Pour into large mold.
Chill until set. Serves 12.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken; debone and chop.
Saute onion in skillet, add soups, Veg-all and chicken.
Line 2 qt. casserole with one pie shell.
Add chicken mixture.
Top with other pie shell for crust. Prick for air vent on top.
Bake for 1 hour on 350° until crust is brown.
Let cool before slicing into pie wedges for serving. Refrigerate.
Great Left overs.

title: marinated shrimp
directions: Mix all together, except shrimp, to make marinade. Pour over shrimp which have been washed and drained but not cooked. Let stand 2 hours, covered, in your refrigerator. Place shrimp on skewers. Cook over low coals on grill (or in broiler) about 7 to 10 minutes, turning several times. Serve hot from grill with side skewers of peppers and mushrooms.

title: pie crust
directions: Beat water and Crisco together until Crisco is fluffy (water won't all work into Crisco).
Add flour and salt.
Mix until dough forms into ball.
This makes enough dough for 4 pie shells or 2 (2 crust) pies.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, egg yolks, buttermilk and salt together.
In a grease-free narrow-bottomed mixing bowl, beat the egg whites until stiff and fold into batter.
On a lightly greased, preheated griddle or skillet, spoon on desired amounts of pancake batter and bake, turning once.

title: party barbucups
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add barbecue sauce, brown sugar and onion. Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Using cupcake pan, place 1 biscuit dough in each ungreased cup making sure that dough goes over edge of cup.
Spoon meat into cups and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Let stand about 5 minutes before taking out.

title: homemade cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt butter in bread pan in oven. Combine ingredients and pour into pan.
Use any kind of fruit desired (blackberries and peaches are especially good).
Pour sweetened fruit into batter.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes in 350° oven or until done.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cake
directions: Combine oats and boiling water in a large bowl.
Let stand 10 minutes. Add remainder of ingredients except chocolate chips.
Mix well. Stir 1/2 chips into batter.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix rest of chips with coconut and chopped nuts. Sprinkle on top of batter. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: date roll
directions: Mix together dates and marshmallows with enough graham cracker crumbs to mix all together.
Add a bit of milk and mix together with hands.
Shape into roll.
Roll in extra crumbs and chill. Slice and add a dollop of ice cream or whipped topping.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut flowerets from broccoli.
Discard stems.
Combine with bacon and raisins.
Mix remaining ingredients for dressing.
Add dressing to salad.
Let marinate 2 to 24 hours.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together.
Add vinegar and water. Bring to a boil.
Add celery seed and chopped parsley to sliced potatoes.

title: baked french toast
directions: Melt brown sugar, butter and corn syrup.
Spray bottom of 9 x 13 Pyrex dish.
Pour brown sugar and butter mixture into dish. Blend eggs with milk and vanilla.
Slice one loaf French bread to fit Pyrex dish.
Put bread over brown sugar mixture in dish.
Pour egg mixture over bread.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with bacon and fruit.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar and oil and pour over drained vegetables; let set in refrigerator overnight.
(Sugar, vinegar and oil can be doubled or tripled according to taste.)
Mixture keeps for a couple of months.

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix oleo mixture in flour, soda and salt.
Let chill for 1 hour.
Roll out and cut shapes.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: lazy day stew
directions: Arrange beef cubes in pan large enough to hold them in a single layer.
You do not need to brown first.
Cut potatoes, carrots, onions and celery in good size chunks; layer on top of meat.
Mix tomato sauce with water and sugar.
Pour over meat and vegetables.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Scatter tapioca on top. Don't stir.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° at least 2 hours.
Do not peek during 2 hours baking.
Will not harm if baked longer.

title: funeral cake
directions: Sift sugar and flour together into bowl.
Put margarine, shortening, cocoa and water in saucepan. Bring to rapid boil and pour over sugar and flour mixture.
Mix well. Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased 11 x 16-inch pan. Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 400° until a toothpick comes out clean or cake begins to pull away from sides of pan.
Ice with Funeral Cake Icing while cake is hot.
Serve with cool.
Soothing at funeral luncheons or anytime.

title: calico beans
directions: Saute meat and onions; drain.
In a large casserole dish or small roaster, add all the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours. Add water as needed.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together sugar and oil. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and vanilla and beat well.
Add apples, nuts, raisins and coconut.
Bake in a tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: angel yeast biscuits
directions: Next add 1 cup applesauce or crushed pineapple (drained) and 2/3 cup nuts.
Pour into 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool on rack for 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: creamy peach pie
directions: Drain peaches; reserve syrup and set aside.
Add water to syrup to make 2 cups and combine with vanilla pudding and peach jello in saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Pour into bowl and chill well.
Blend in Cool Whip and fold in diced peaches.
Pour into cooked pie shell. Chill 2 hours before serving.

title: aunt roxie's chocolate pie
directions: Reserve egg whites at room temperature.
Mix dry ingredients first and set aside.
Mix liquid ingredients in a saucepan; heat until milk is scalded.
Add to dry ingredients slowly until mixed well over medium heat.
Stir constantly until thick.
Let cool and pour into baked pie shells.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add 3 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat again.
Top pies and lightly brown in oven at 425°.

title: no knead hot rolls
directions: In a large mixer bowl stir together 2 cups flour, yeast and salt.
In a small saucepan, heat water, shortening and sugar until warm (120° to 130°).
The shortening does not need to be entirely melted.
Pour into dry ingredients in mixer bowl.
Add eggs and beat mixture on low speed until combined.
Beat on medium speed 3 minutes.
By hand, stir in enough additional flour to make a soft dough.
Make sure flour is thoroughly mixed in.
Transfer dough to a bowl; cover with plastic wrap, then with foil.
Refrigerate overnight or up to 2 or 3 days.
Punch down dough 2 or 3 times during the next 4 or 6 hours or until dough is very cold.

title: cheesy turkey and vegetable pizza(makes one 12-inch pizza)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Unroll dough and press into greased 12-inch pizza pan or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Brush 1 tablespoon oil evenly over dough, then spread with pizza sauce.
Heat remaining 1/4 cup oil in large skillet over medium-high heat until hot.
Add turkey cubes and garlic; cook and stir 2 minutes.
Add onion, green pepper and mushrooms; cook and stir 5 minutes longer or until turkey is tender and no longer pink.
Spoon turkey mixture evenly over sauce.
Top with olives.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and basil.
Top with Monterey Jack and Muenster cheeses. Bake 20 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix like pie crust.
Pat in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: sauerkraut casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion, celery and green peppers. Drain.
Add brown sugar, sauerkraut, rice, tomatoes and water. Mix well.
Pour into a 3-quart casserole.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Place onion and garlic in a medium saucepan coated with cooking spray; cover and cook over low heat 15 minutes or until tender.
Add tomato and next 4 ingredients; simmer, uncovered, 45 minutes.
Set aside.

title: supreme chicken casserole
directions: Butter casserole dish generously.
Place 1/2 bread cubes in bottom of casserole dish.
Combine chicken, celery, pimento, salt, pepper and salad dressing.
Pour into casserole dish.
Cover with remaining cubes.
Combine milk and eggs.
Pour over cubes.
Chill overnight.
Before baking, pour soup over mixture.
Bake covered for 40 minutes at 325°.
Uncover.
Add cheese and bake 10 minutes. Add onion rings.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: fruited ricotta bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour cookie sheet.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt into large bowl.
Make a well in center and stir in Ricotta, eggs, vanilla, sugar, candied fruit, raisins, almonds and lemon peel.
Knead lightly until dough holds together.
Shape into a 12-inch long loaf and place on prepared cookie sheet.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Transfer to wire rack.
Brush butter or margarine over warm loaf; sift confectioners sugar over top.
Cool completely.
Makes 12 servings.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Chop and mix in a large bowl the cabbage, onion and pepper. Take remaining ingredients and combine them in a pan.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over first 3 ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.
It will keep for days.

title: borsch (stew)(international:  ukraine)
directions: In a large covered saucepan, simmer meat in broth and water for 45 minutes or until tender.
Stir in salt, onion, potato, carrot and celery.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes more or until vegetables are tender.
Combine flour and lemon juice.
Slowly add to soup while stirring.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until mixture thickens.
Serve hot.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Make bread dough and rise halfway.
Press apple wedges in or put cottage cheese in and fold over.
Pour sugar and cream over (cinnamon with the apples) and bake at 350° until hollow to tap.

title: green bean bundles
directions: For each bundle use 10 green beans.
Wrap 1/2 piece of partially cooked bacon around them and place them in a greased cooking dish or cake pan.
Mix 3 tablespoons brown sugar with 4 tablespoons melted margarine or butter.
Sprinkle over bundles. Sprinkle a little garlic salt over each.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes (35 minutes if fresh beans are used).
Easy, pretty and good!

title: no-bake chocolate candy
directions: Melt chocolate pieces in top of double boiler.
Add milk. Stir in nuts and chow mein noodles.
Spoon into candy-size paper cups or onto a baking sheet.
Chill.
Makes 25 to 35.

title: chocolate-pecan pie
directions: Mix milk, butter and chocolate bits in pan.
Heat until chocolate melts.
Stir in remaining ingredients, adding vanilla last.
Pour into pie shell and bake 35 minutes at 375°.

title: coffee cake
directions: Put on top of cake before putting in the oven.
You can add sliced apples, blueberries or raisins, just one kind.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: corn cheese casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir well and spread into a lightly greased 1-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until corn is tender.
Yields 4 servings.

title: hummingbird egg treats
directions: Cut white cheese into 2-inch circles.
Cut yellow cheese into 1-inch circles.
Place on dark party bread, white cheese, then yellow cheese.
Place on baking sheet and bake in oven just until cheese softens.
Should look like a sunny-side-up egg.

title: layered avocado dip
directions: Spread refried beans in a 10 x 6-inch Pyrex dish (with sides). Mix the sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning together. Spread over beans.
Blend avocados and lemon juice in food processor until smooth.
Spread over mayonnaise layer the other ingredients in order (green onions, tomato, cheese and olives). Serve with tortilla chips.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage.
Add onions and cook about 2 additional minutes; drain.
Place bread cubes in bottom of buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Add seasonings.
Pour over bread cubes.
Place sausage on top.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° approximately 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: date porcupine balls
directions: Beat eggs with sugar and salt until thick.
Add dates.
Turn mixture into heavy saucepan and cook over low heat, about 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add cereal, chopped nuts and vanilla.
When mixture is cool enough to handle, pinch off small portions and form into ball.
Then roll each ball in the coconut as you form them.
Cool; store in cool dry covered container.

title: quick fudge
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler, add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Spread in wax paper lined pan.
Chill until firm, remove from pan and cut into squares.

title: creme de menthe brownies
directions: Mix together brownie ingredients.
Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: the quickest cobbler
directions: Melt butter in medium size baking dish.
Pour in flour, sugar, milk and vanilla.
After it has been mixed thoroughly, then spoon in pie filling evenly over mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown and bubbling.

title: my mom's popcorn balls
directions: Boil together sugar, syrup, butter and salt until a soft ball forms in cold water (about 5 minutes).
Add to popped corn, mix and shape into balls.

title: snowballs
directions: Mix together all ingredients except coconut.
Shape into balls.
Roll balls in coconut for a snowy look.
Place in deep freeze.

title: anise cookies
directions: Beat sugar, butter and egg until creamy. Stir in flavoring. Add flour, salt and baking powder; mix by hand.
Form dough into balls and flatten.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Ice with powdered sugar, Pet milk and butter, mixed together.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar and milk in a square Pyrex dish.
Pour peach pie filling evenly into mixture. Slice stick of margarine on top. Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese log
directions: Soften all cheeses for 45 seconds or less and put in food processor and put on wax paper, then refrigerate.

title: raisin filled oatmeal sandwich cookies
directions: Mix ingredients and pat out cookie dough on sheet with glass dipped in flour.
Bake 350° until edges are lightly browned.
Cool.

title: red devil's food cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add unbeaten eggs, one at a time. Add vanilla and milk, alternating milk with flour which has been sifted with salt, soda and cocoa.
Add boiling water all at once; stir until well mixed.
Bake in three 8-inch layer pans or one 9 x 12-inch sheet cake pan.
This is a large, moist cake that will keep well.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Top with your favorite chocolate frosting.

title: peanut butter cookies for diabetics
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine butter, peanut butter and Sucaryl.
Blend well.
Add milk combined with egg and vanilla. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add to first mixture and blend.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheets. Flatten with fork.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: In a covered saucepan, cook broccoli in water until crisp-tender; drain.
Place in a greased 11 x 7 x 2 baking dish; set aside.
Combine chicken, soup, mayo, Parmesan cheese and curry powder; spoon over broccoli.
Top with bread cubes and butter. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: perch creole style
directions: Saute vegetables in oil.
Add tomato sauce and seasonings; simmer 10 minutes.
Oil a baking dish and lay fillets in a single layer on bottom.
Cover with sauce.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes per inch of thickness of fillets with sauce, measured at the thickest part, or until fish flakes easily.
Serve over rice, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: zucchini squash casserole
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients in 1 cup water until tender.
Drain.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Layer all ingredients in order listed. Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Bring the sugar, oil and vinegar to a boil; let cool.
Pour over vegetables and let set overnight in the refrigerator.

title: aunt fanny's baked squash
directions: Cut up and boil squash until tender.
Drain thoroughly, then mash.
Add rest of ingredients and 1/2 of melted oleo.
Mix 1/2 cup bread crumbs and rest of melted oleo.
Put squash mixture in 8 x 8-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle crumbs over top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: round steak
directions: Cut steak into serving size pieces.
Coat one side of each piece with flour and tenderizer.
In fry pan, put oil and brown meat on both sides.
In baking pan, put cut up potatoes and carrots.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add meat along with 2 to 3 cups water.
Sprinkle 1 package onion soup mix over the top of meat and potatoes.
Bake covered at 350° for 2 hours.

title: no fat christmas wreaths
directions: Spray saucepan with nonfat cooking spray.
Melt marshmallows with Smart Beat until marshmallows are melted and remove from heat. Add green food coloring and vanilla.
Stir in cornflakes.
With slightly sprayed finger, shape mixture into wreath shape with hole in center.
Decorate with candies.

title: yellow rice casserole
directions: After rice has cooked, mix the remaining ingredients.
Heat in oven until hot.

title: strawberry rhubarb pie
directions: Cover rhubarb with boiling water and let stand 15 minutes. Drain and add strawberries in saucepan.
Add sugar, butter, water and cornstarch.
Cook over low heat until it begins to thicken. Pour over berries and rhubarb in pie baked shell.
Put meringue on pie.
Bake until brown.

title: quick appetizer
directions: Cut each bacon slice into thirds.
Wrap each water chestnut half with bacon slice.
Secure with toothpick.
Dip in teriyaki sauce.
Arrange in circle on cooking grill or bacon rack.
Cover with paper towel.
Microwave on Full power for 3 to 5 minutes or until bacon is crisp.

title: hawaiian pork chops
directions: Brown chops in 1 tablespoon oil.
Drain off excess fat. Combine pineapple, juice, ketchup, onion and seasonings.
Simmer. Turn and baste frequently.
Stir in green pepper, cut in chunks. Cover; simmer until tender.
Thicken with cornstarch.
Makes 4 servings.
Yields 1 1/2 cups sauce.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: candied sweet potatoes with apple
directions: In a medium covered saucepan cook the sweet potatoes in enough boiling water to cover the potatoes for 25 to 35 minutes or until tender.
Drain; cool slightly.
Peel the potatoes and cut into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Set aside.
Core the apple and thinly slice into 1/8-inch thick rings.
Cut the apple rings in half crosswise.
Place apple slices in a 1-quart casserole.
Place sweet potato slices atop apple slices.
Sprinkle with the brown sugar and butter flavored sprinkles.
Drizzle with the apple or orange juice.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until heated through.
Stir gently to serve, spooning juices over potato and apple slices.
Serves 4.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Mix flour, milk, baking powder, egg, 1/2 cup sugar, pudding mix and vanilla together.
Pour into a 10-inch pie tin (a smaller pan will not work).
Drain peaches, reserving juice.
Arrange peach slices on top of dough.
Combine the cream cheese, 3 tablespoons peach juice, 1/2 cup sugar and peach flavoring.
Spread over peaches, but don't go to the edge with it.
Combine 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes (glass pie pan) or 40 minutes (metal pie pan).

title: easy lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In saucepan, heat spaghetti sauce and water.
Combine Ricotta, 2 cups Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses. Add parsley.
Pour 3/4 cup sauce in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Arrange 3 pieces uncooked pasta lengthwise over sauce.
Pour 1/2 cup sauce over pasta.
Spread with 1/2 cheese mixture.
Cover with 1/2 cup sauce; repeat layers.
Top with pasta and remaining sauce; sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Cover with foil; bake for 60 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining 1 cup Mozzarella cheese; let stand 10 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: chicken breast supreme
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread crumbs and butter.
Place chicken breasts in sour cream mixture.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator for at least 8 hours.
Heat oven to 350°.
Remove chicken from sour cream mixture and roll in bread crumbs.
Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Drizzle melted butter over chicken and bake for 10 to 15 more minutes. Makes 8 servings.

title: low-fat waldorf salad
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, toss together the chopped apples and lemon juice.
Stir in the raisins, grapes and celery.

title: french toast
directions: Spray pan with nonstick spray. Heat pan to medium/medium-high. Mix milk, eggs and flavoring in separate bowl. Dip bread (each piece) into mixture. Brown each piece of bread in pan. Turn bread and do not allow to burn.

title: coconut pie
directions: Separate 2 eggs and save egg whites for meringue. Beat the 2 yolks and 1 whole egg. Mix flour with sugar and add to beaten eggs. Add cup of milk. Melt butter and add to mixture. Add 1/3 can of coconut. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Beat egg whites until stiff. Add 2 tablespoons sugar and vanilla to egg whites; continue beating until stiff. Spread on pie and sprinkle remainder of coconut on top. Bake until coconut is light brown.

title: boots delight salad
directions: Mix jello as directed.
Add fruit and refrigerate until congealed.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind the cranberries and orange in a grinder or food processor.
Combine the remaining ingredients and mix with the cranberry and orange mixture.
Let stand for 48 hours before serving.
This relish freezes well.

title: spinach salad
directions: Toss above ingredients.
Add enough dressing to coat leaves.

title: chicken chili
directions: Saute onions and garlic in oil.
Add rest of the ingredients. Taste and add more spices if desired.
You can also add Cajun or creole spice.
Cook 30 minutes.
Add shredded cheese just before serving.
Enjoy!

title: chocolate-p-nut butter chip bark
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil. In medium saucepan, melt chocolate chips and peanut butter chips over low heat, stirring constantly, until smooth. Remove from heat. Stir in peanuts. Spread to 1/4-inch thickness on cookie sheet. Refrigerate about 30 minutes or until set. Break into pieces. Makes about 15 to 20 candies.

title: salty peanut chews
directions: Mix together first three ingredients and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle marshmallows over cake.
Put back into oven until they are puffy.
Combine peanut butter chips, Karo syrup and vanilla in a large saucepan and heat until chips are melted.
Add peanuts and rice cereal and stir to coat.
Drop topping by spoonfuls onto puffy marshmallows.
Cool completely and cut into 2-inch squares.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Sift flour.
Measure into bowl.

Add baking powder and salt. Cut in shortening until mixture looks like coarse meal. Add milk. Stir until soft dough is formed. Turn onto floured board and knead 30 seconds to shape (about 20 kneading turns).
Pat dough 1/2-inch thick.
Cut biscuits with 2-inch floured cutter.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet in a 450° oven for 12 to 15 minutes. Makes 14 biscuits.

title: sweet potato pie(sugar free)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil sweet potatoes until tender, cool. Then peel and mash.
Warm apple juice concentrate and mix with softened butter.
Beat 3 eggs and combine with butter and apple juice mixture.
Add salt, vanilla extract and spices.
Stir in the mashed sweet potatoes.
Add the cup of milk and beat the mixture well with an electric mixer and pour into the pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until the center is firm.
Makes 2 pies.

title: old fashion cucumber salad
directions: Peel cucumbers, but leave some narrow strips for color. Slice cucumbers very thin and place in a large bowl.
Sprinkle with a small amount of salt (will flavor through better if added after slicing each cucumber).
Stir well.
Let sit for about 15 minutes and liquid will form.
Drain liquid and gently squeeze from cucumber slices.
Place in bowl with onion.
Mix with dill weed, sour cream, vinegar and pepper.
Refrigerate until well chilled.
Stir and add salt and pepper, if needed.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Make a well in the mix. Add the milk and stir with a fork (about 25 strokes). Turn onto a sheet of waxed paper. Knead well 6 times.
Roll out or pat into 1/2-inch thickness on a lightly floured board or pastry cloth.
Place on a baking sheet. Bake in a 450° oven about 15 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Blend the cream cheese and sugar until smooth. Add the pineapple, oranges, cherries, marshmallows and banana. Add the Cool Whip.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Freeze overnight.

title: strawberry daiquiris
directions: Mix in blender, then add ice; the more the slushier.

title: delicious vegetable casserole
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in large bowl; salt and pepper to taste.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into greased casserole, then mix last 3 ingredients in small bowl.
Spread over top of mixture and bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: beef noodle soup
directions: Place first 5 ingredients in soup pot.
Cover with 1-inch water.
Separate meat.
Strain broth.
Discard bone and vegetables.* Trim any fat from meat that still remains.
Add to broth.
Boil fine noodles separately** and add as desired.
Sweeten to taste.

title: chinese cooking made e-z
directions: Prepare cornstarch mixture by mixing 1 teaspoon cornstarch with 1 teaspoon of water.
Cut or slice meat and vegetables (2 cups). Heat the wok or skillet until red hot.
Add 1/4 or less cup of vegetable oil and follow by the meat.
Stir until it is cooked. Add the vegetables and stir for two minutes.
Remove contents in the wok to a plate.
Add 3 ounces of sauce to the wok.
Wait until it starts to boil and then add the meat and vegetables.
Stir until boils and add cornstarch mixture to thicken it.
Ready to serve.

title: bran muffins
directions: Soak Nabisco 100% Bran in 2 cups of boiling water.
Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and buttermilk.
Add All-Bran. Combine flour, soda and salt; add to mixture.
Fold in the soaked bran.
Bake in greased muffin tins (or use muffin papers) at 400° for 15 minutes.
This batter will keep for approximately 10 days in tightly covered container in refrigerator.
Spoon out as needed; no need to re-stir.

title: sweet potato fries
directions: Scrub sweet potatoes and cut lengthwise into wedges.
Preheat oven to 450°.
In jellyroll pan, heat butter in oven one minute until melted.
Remove from oven.
Set aside 2 tablespoons melted butter.
Place sweet potato wedges, flat side down, on pan.
Brush with reserved butter.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes until golden and fork-tender, turning once or twice; season with salt and pepper to taste.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Heat water; add to cocoa and stir until smooth.
Add butter, sugar and salt.
Heat until sugar is dissolved; add vanilla and serve.
Use for ice cream, pudding topping.

title: shrimp macaroni salad
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients, then add remaining ingredients.

title: macaroni ambrosia
directions: Boil and drain acini de pepe.
Drain pineapple and oranges and chill.
Save juice.
Add sugar, flour, cornstarch, salt, eggs and lemon juice to fruit juice.
Cook until thick.
Cool.
Pour over macaroni.
Refrigerate.
Drain cherries.
Cut in halves.
Before serving, mix fruit, cherries, macaroni and Cool Whip.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Blend one stick butter or oleo with one cup of sugar.
Add 1 large egg; blend one cup of all-purpose flour.
Batter will be like cookie batter (stiff).
Push off a teaspoon onto top of fresh or canned fruit in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° until dough is brown, about 45 minutes to one hour.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and beat.
In other bowl, mix dry ingredients.
Add applesauce and mix well.
Add creamed mixture to second bowl and beat.
Add raisins and nuts. Bake in floured tube pan for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: southern raised biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients together in a large bowl; set aside. Dissolve yeast in slightly warmed buttermilk.
Add buttermilk mixture and oil to flour mixture.
Stir gently and quickly until mixed.
Turn dough onto a lightly floured board and knead gently 20 to 30 times.
Roll out or pat to a 1/4-inch thickness.
With a floured 1-inch biscuit cutter, make 60 biscuits, then brush each biscuit with oil.
Place 30 biscuits on an ungreased baking sheet. Place another biscuit on top of each.
Cover and let rise in a warm place (about 85°) for about 2 hours.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 30 servings.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease baking pans.
Sift dry ingredients together in large bowl.
Blend in shortening. Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add buttermilk to yeast.
Pour over flour mixture.
Mix well.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: confectioners custard
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt; gradually stir in milk.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 2 minutes.
Blend a small amount of hot mixture into egg yolks; return all to pan.
Cook for 1 minute (do not boil).
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cover and chill.

title: carpet cleaner
directions: Use a stiff bristle scrub brush.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Use ripe firm fruit.
Scald and remove skins as you would tomatoes.
Stick 6 cloves in each peach.
Make syrup of vinegar and sugar; add cinnamon.
When boiling, add enough peaches to fill quart jars.
Cook until tender, but not broken.
Put in jars and fill with syrup.
Keep repeating the whole process, until you have used all the peaches and syrup.
(If you cook all the peaches at once, they will cook until done.)

title: mom's chicken and mushroom pizza
directions: Trim Boboli shell (see recipe).
Place shell in pizza pan. Trim to fit.

title: fruity clay dough(homemade play dough)
directions: You will need a mixing spoon and an electric skillet.

title: deviled beef
directions: Cut beef in small pieces.
Coat with flour and brown on both sides in oil.
Mix the 3 tablespoons flour and mustard and combine with remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook slowly on top of range 1 1/2 hours.

title: carolina chew cake
directions: Cream margarine and brown sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs.
Blend in flour.
Stir in other ingredients except powdered sugar.
Spoon batter into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Dust with powdered sugar.
Let cool before cutting.
Cake will fall.

title: chicken seasoning
directions: Take skin off chicken.
Place flour, salt, seasoning and pepper into a large plastic bag.
Shake chicken in bag to coat well.
Place chicken in a deep baking sheet.
Dribble butter on it.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Remove foil and bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes more.

title: cranberry ice
directions: Cook cranberries until they pop and are well done.
Run through a sieve.
In a large bowl, dissolve
3 cups sugar in 1 cup hot water, then add the berry pulp and stir well.
When cool, add juice of 4 oranges and 2 to 3 lemons and stir.
Put in any size pan, but the 10 x 3 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch works well.
Freeze until partly frozen, then stir well once or twice.
Good served at holiday time.
Makes about 2 quarts.

title: cindy's carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil; add eggs, pineapple, coconut, nuts and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Then add to first mixture.
Add cinnamon and nutmeg.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Combine cheese spread and milk; mix well.
Toss spaghetti with margarine.
Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Spoon into 2-quart casserole.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until hot.
Stir before serving.
Can also be cooked in microwave.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus, reserving 1/2 cup liquid.
Arrange in a casserole dish.
Combine the soup, liquid from asparagus, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Pour this over the asparagus and sprinkle with the grated cheese.
Combine the butter and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle this over the cheese.
Top with almonds.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: carrot-raisin salad
directions: Mix together carrots and raisins.
Combine oil, vinegar, mayonnaise, honey and dill weed in jar with tight fitting lid. Shake well until blended.
Add to carrot mixture and mix well. Chill before serving.

title: elvis presley cake
directions: Make cake as directed on box.
Punch holes in cake 3 or 4 inches apart as cake comes out of the oven.
Cook pineapple and sugar together for 5 minutes.
While cake is still warm, spread all of this mixture over the entire cake.

title: energy squares
directions: Heat corn syrup and sugar until boiling.
Add peanut butter. Add cornflakes, nuts and raisins.
Spread evenly in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let it cool.
Cut in squares.

title: nutmeg butterball cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Blend in vanilla.
Combine salt, flour and nuts; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls and chill 1 hour.
Mix together nutmeg and confectioners sugar.
Bake cookies at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.
While warm, roll in nutmeg mixture. Makes about 86 cookies.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef; add onions and brown lightly.
Add green pepper, tomatoes and salt to taste.
Cook until tomatoes cook done; add water until soupy and cook slowly 1 1/2 hours.
Place beans in pot with more water, if needed.
Add chili powder and cook 1/2 hour more.

title: brown gravy
directions: In dry boiler, sprinkle red pepper, black pepper, salt and flour.
Over medium heat, stir until flour mixture is brown.
Add 2 cups broth; stir until thick as desired.
More or less broth may be used.

title: taco soup(weight watchers)
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain.
Mix ranch dressing and taco seasoning pkgs. into meat.
Add all other ingredients and simmer 1 hour.
Makes 12 - 1 cup servings (2.5 Weight Watchers pts. per serving).

title: easy cheesy potatoes(microwave)
directions: Slice potatoes very thin.
Place half of potatoes in an oiled 2-quart casserole dish.
Add a layer of onion slices.
Sprinkle with half the dried parsley, salt and pepper.
Add 1/2 cup shredded cheese and top with half of the butter pats.
Repeat the layers.
Cover the dish and cook in microwave on High, 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger; add onions, peppers, refried beans, and 1 package per pound taco mix and fry. Break up tortilla chips and place in pan.
Take hamburger mixture and pour over chips.
Put shredded cheese on top and bake until cheese is melted.
Top with tomato and lettuce.
Enjoy with your favorite dressing.

title: corn and potato soup
directions: Melt butter in pan and add onion.
Add potatoes, water and stock cubes.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add creamed corn.
Reheat.
Do not boil.
Serve and sprinkle with chives.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Mix cake mix according to package.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350°.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese, pudding and milk and beat for 2 minutes.
Put on cake and refrigerate until set.
Mix pineapple and Dream Whip (prepared).
Put on top of pudding mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: cocoa bread pudding
directions: Combine
milk
with
water;
add
margarine and heat to scalding.
Pour
over
bread crumbs.
Stir well and set aside. Beat
eggs
slightly and add remaining ingredients, continuing to mix
well.
Combine
thoroughly with milk mixture and pour into greased
6-cup baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.
Serve hot or cold.

title: holiday punch
directions: Mix all ingredients, except for 7-Up.
After frozen juices have melted, add chilled 7-Up.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease 2 large loaf pans or 4 smaller pans and flour.
Place dry ingredients in a bowl; blend and make a well.
Mix all liquid ingredients together.
Add to the well of dry ingredients, then add zucchini and nuts.
Pour into pans and bake for 55 minutes at 350°, 35 minutes for small pans, 15 minutes for mini muffin pans. Cool before removing from pan.

title: holiday trail mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in closed container in refrigerator.
Will keep for 2 weeks.
Makes 11 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Line bottom of pan with chicken.
Blend cream soup, chicken broth and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Make Stove Top as directed and spread over top. Cook at 325° for 45 minutes, covered.
Cook 15 more minutes uncovered.
Recommend cookie sheet under casserole dish; it may bubble up.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Halve
1 cup berries. Combine with sugar, water and cornstarch. Cook over low heat until it thickens.
Cool, then stir in the remainder of the quart of berries and a few drops of red food coloring. Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill well.

title: greek salad
directions: Break the lettuce in bite-size pieces.
Prepare other vegetables and add to lettuce.
Drain olives.
Crumble cheese; add to salad.
Add oregano and dressing just before serving.
Put anchovies on top.
Garnish top with a few black olives and Feta cheese.

title: all-american chili
directions: Saute turkey, onion and peppers.
Add rest of ingredients and cook over medium heat until desired consistency.
Flavor improves with length of cooking time.

title: french fried onion rings fritter batter
directions: Sift dry ingredients into mixing
bowl.
Combine beaten egg and milk. Stir into flour
mixture
along with shortening. Mix until all ingredients are blended.
Peel
and
slice onion 1/4 inch thick.
Break into rings.
Dip a few
at
a time into batter. Drop
into hot deep fat;
fry
until
golden
brown. Drain on absorbent paper.

title: kourabiethes-cute umbrellas(butter cookies)
directions: Soften butter to room temperature; beat with electric mixer until lite and creamy.
Add sugar; beat 5 minutes until smooth. Then add whiskey and egg yolks, beating until well blended.
Add in baking soda and flour to make soft dough.

title: party punch
directions: Add enough water to make a gallon.
Mix all juices.
Chill until needed.
Add ginger ale.
Serve over ice.

title: strawberry-applesauce congealed salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water. Add orange juice and applesauce. Refrigerate until consistency of egg whites. Add nuts. Refrigerate until set.

title: five cup fruit salad
directions: Toss fruit, coconut and marshmallows with sour cream.
Chill and serve.

title: pasta alla panna(cream and cheese sauce)
directions: If a more pungent and robust sauce is desired, use 1 cup each of Parmesan and Romano cheese.
Mix the cheeses together.
