Cook the pasta as per package directions until al dente, "tender to the bite."
While the pasta is cooking, make the sauce.
Melt the butter in a saucepan.
Add the cream and 1 cup of the combined cheeses.
Stir over medium low heat until thoroughly blended and smooth.
Do not let the sauce bubble.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease a
9 x 13-inch pan (if you use a smaller pan, you will have runover in the oven.)
Cover bottom with coconut, as much as you like.
Cover coconut with chopped nuts.
Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Pour over coconut-nut mixture.
Combine margarine,
powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Stir until smooth. Spoon over cake mix; do not stir into cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: grilled chinese soy hamburgers
directions: Combine ingredients and add to meat mixture.

title: velveeta light vegetable bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix broccoli and Velveeta cheese product; spoon into greased 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with crushed crackers; dot with spread.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: bulgogi(korean barbecue beef)
directions: Cut beef into thin cross grain slices, approximately 3-inch square.
Combine sugar, oil, soy sauce, onion, garlic and pepper. Marinate beef in this mixture at least 15 minutes.
Broil for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot with rice.

title: five hour stew
directions: Combine everything.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours.

title: old-fashion potato salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise and pickle relish into potatoes.
Add salt and sugar.
Peel and cut eggs into small slices and stir in.
You may stir in only 2 eggs and reserve the third to make a lily on top.

title: indian golden chicken
directions: Saute onions, ginger and garlic in shortening or salad oil. Heat yogurt in a small saucepan and add all seasonings.
Put chicken in pan with sauteed onion mixture.
Pour yogurt mixture and tomatoes over this.
Mix well and cover pot, letting it cook on medium for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally, until chicken is tender.
Remove lid and brown the chicken until much of the liquid evaporates.
Serve over rice or couscous.

title: chocolate cherry cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Combine cookie mix, egg and water in a large bowl. Stir until thoroughly blended. Stir in cherries and coconut. Shape dough into balls and roll in nuts. Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake for 12 minutes or until cookies are lightly browned. Makes 3 dozen.

title: easy casserole
directions: Layer vegetables in casserole dish.
Top with turkey or beef that has been browned.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Top with undiluted can of tomato soup.
Cover casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until carrots are done.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in top of double boiler.
Mix the eggs, sugars, flour, milk and vanilla.
Add to chocolate mixture. Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Arrange fresh peaches on 9-inch layer pan.
Sprinkle with mixture of sugar, 2 tablespoons flour and cinnamon.
Blob with butter.
Stir rest of ingredients until blended.
Drop by teaspoon over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bread and fruit, in a large bowl. Beat well with whip.
Pour over bread cubes in buttered casserole dish (large).
Sprinkle with cinnamon or nutmeg.
Bake 1 hour or longer until top is golden brown at 350°.
Pudding will rise over dish in oven, but will fall as it cools.
Great served warm.

title: wanda's pinto beans
directions: Wash pinto beans, put in slow cooker.
Add whole onion, salt, pepper and browned ground beef.
Cook until beans are tender and juice is thick.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mix first three ingredients well, then mix in the rest.
Makes about 6 cups.
Serve with crackers.

title: flounder fish and vegetables
directions: Wash flounder and set aside.
Cut peppers and onion in strips. Saute together with herbs, vinegar and olive oil until tender. Place in bottom of baking pan and place flounder over vegetables. Bake for 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Sprinkle salt and pepper.
Make sure fish is opal and flaky but don't overcook.

title: forgotten kisses
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites.
Add salt and sugar. Beat until stiff.
Add vanilla.
Fold in chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Place in oven and turn oven off. Leave in oven overnight.

title: gourmet spaghetti
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients and turn down to simmer.
Serve over spaghetti, rice or with lasagna.

title: mom's sweet zucchini biscuits
directions: Beat oleo until it is fluffy. Add sugar, eggs and orange juice. Beat well. Add spices, baking powder, soda and salt.
Stir well. Add zucchini, nuts and orange rind.
Stir well.
Add flour and stir well. Drop by teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until the edges begin to brown. Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar. Very good.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: You can use up to 1 1/2 pounds of ground beef to one can of soup.
Salt and pepper ground beef and mix with soup.
Place in rectangle cake pan.
Lay Tater Tots on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken for 1 hour.
Cool and shred chicken.
Mix together the soups and milk.
Fold into this mixture the green beans, chicken and the onions.
Salt and pepper to taste. Sprinkle with the onion/garlic croutons.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: applesauce jello salad
directions: Bring applesauce to a boil.
Add dry Jell-O.
Stir until Jell-O is dissolved.
Cool slightly.
Add can of Sprite.
Add slowly because it foams up.
Pour into mold or pan.
Raspberry Jell-O is especially good in this recipe.

title: homemade ice-cream
directions: Mix egg yolk and sugar. Separately beat egg white. Put cream and water in separate bowl. Mix all together and add flavoring. Pour into ice-cream mixer; begin to freeze.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Sift sugar.
Have cream cheese at room temperature.
With fingers, cream cheese and sugar together thoroughly.
Divide dough in as many portions as desired.
Color and flavor each portion differently as desired.
Roll in small balls and roll in sugar. Press in mold.
Turn mold upside down.
Be sure to have enough sugar or they won't come out of the mold.

title: potato chocolate cake
directions: This makes a large loaf cake.
Very moist cake due to the potatoes.

title: pumpkin dip
directions: Cream cheese and sugar, blend in pumpkin and spices.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together in blender until well blended.
Serve with corn chips to dip.

title: lemon sauce
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; then add water.
Cook 5 minutes and let cool.
Then add butter, lemon juice and egg yolk.
Recook for 3 minutes.
Delicious!!

title: italian pasta salad
directions: The pasta I use is the tri-flavored spiral paste.
For the Italian dressing I use "Good Seasons" with balsamic vinegar.
It make a wonderful difference.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Fill the pie crust with 1 pint whole strawberries. Take 1 pint berries and mash. Add sugar and cornstarch; mix and cook until thick. Pour over berries and top with whipped cream.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water; add 1 cup cold water. Add strawberries.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Tear cake into pieces and place on Jell-O.
Press down.
Chill 4 hours.
Frost with Cool Whip.
Serves 10.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Mix eggs, oil and vanilla.
Sift together salt, sugar, flour, soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add egg mixture.
Mix well with a spoon.
Add zucchini, raisins and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy pot roast
directions: Turn chuck roast in seasoned flour and brown on all sides in small amount of hot oil.
Put the browned roast and vegetables into large roasting pan.
Add the salt, pepper and bay leaf.
Pour the can of beef broth over all and cover tightly.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, then reduce heat to 350° for 2 hours, or until meat is tender.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix together with salt, pepper and mayonnaise.

title: mexicali dip
directions: Blend in blender until smooth.
Pour in serving dish.
Garnish with chives.
Chill overnight.

title: pumpkin bread ii
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix 1 cup flour and all other ingredients, except walnuts, for 2 minutes on high speed.
Add remaining flour and beat well.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake for 60 to 65 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Wrap and store overnight before slicing.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, salad oil, tomato soup, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, salt and pepper.
Layer carrots, onion and pepper. Pour sauce over it and let stand 24 hours.

title: baked rice and fry-chick
directions: Bring liquid to boil.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Saute onion in margarine until translucent.
Add rice and stir until well coated. Add chicken cubes.
Add boiling liquid.
Cover and bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Yields 4 servings.

title: skillet fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter, salt and evaporated milk in electric skillet. Set thermostat at 280°.
Bring mixture to a boil and boil for 4 1/2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Turn off skillet and add marshmallows, chocolate chips, nuts and vanilla. Stir until melted and smooth.
Pour into buttered 9-inch pan. Cool before cutting.

title: babanatsoo
directions: Combine apples, raisins, walnuts, oil, sugar, eggs, cinnamon and matzah meal. Put aside. Wet matzah farfel with water and squeeze out excess water after 5 minutes.

title: bacon poles
directions: Coat one side of each bacon slice half with cheese.
Wrap each bread stick with 1 bacon slice half in "spiral" fashion, cheese side toward bread stick.
Place bacon poles on microwave-safe plate lined with 3 microwave-safe paper towels.
Cover with paper towel.
Microwave on High 4 to 6 minutes.
Remove from paper towels and allow to cool before serving.

title: pam's zucchini bread
directions: Stir together flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt. Stir in wheat germ and nuts.
Set aside.
With electric mixer at high speed, beat eggs, oil and sugar until thickened and foamy. Stir in zucchini.
Add flour mixture and stir only until dry ingredients are moistened.

title: pork loin roast - americana
directions: Place roast, fat side up, on a rack in an open roasting pan. Combine applesauce, onion, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, brown sugar and salt.
Spread applesauce mixture over meat. Insert meat thermometer so tip reaches the center of the thickest part.
Be careful that tip does not rest in fat or on bone.
Do not add water.
Do not cover.

title: easy punch
directions: Chill soda well.
Mix juices according to instructions on can; use ice water.
Mix in punch bowl.
Add ice cubes to bowl.
Add soda just before serving.

title: marinade for country style ribs
directions: Mix all ingredients (except meal) in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Place meat in a glass dish; pour marinade over meat.
Let it set 12 to 24 hours in the fridge. Bake on a broiler pan at 375° for about 1 1/2 hours or until meat is done.
May also be grilled on the barbecue.
Baste meat throughout the cooking.

title: the rogers' famous malt
directions: For Chocolate Malt:
Mix 4 to 5 heaping, big spoonfuls of ice cream with milk in a blender.
Add 1/4 teaspoon vanilla and 1/2 tablespoon powdered chocolate drink mix.
Mix in blender.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Put the rice in the bottom of the casserole dish.
Put 3/4 of the onion soup mix, drained mushrooms and 3 cups of hot water on the rice.
Put the pork chops on top and sprinkle with the remaining onion soup mix.
Bake at 350° for about 55 minutes. Uncover the dish the last 10 to 15 minutes of baking time.

title: fruit cake
directions: Crumble graham crackers, chop gumdrops, chop raisins and chop nuts.
Melt marshmallows in milk in double boiler until melted and pour it over the mix.
Put mix in fruit cake pan.
Let set until molded.

title: dump cake
directions: Blend cream cheese with milk.
Add sugar and enough additional milk (if necessary) to make frosting of spreading consistency. Add vanilla.
Brush all crumbs off cake and frost.

title: mexicana casserole
directions: Brown and season the ground
beef.
Line
a 9 x 13-inch casserole with tortillas.
Layer
the
beef,
onion, beans and cheese over the tortillas.
Place
another
layer of tortillas over this.
Spread the cream of celery soup over the tortillas and then the tomatoes on top.
Bake
at
350° uncovered for 30 minutes.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Stir the sugar, milk and cinnamon until sugar melts.
Boil slowly until it reaches soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and pecan halves.
Stir together until very stiff.
Pour out onto wax paper; separate into pieces.
Let set until they harden.
Store in airtight container.

title: bean soup
directions: Combine ingredients in large covered pot. Boil slowly for 3 hours.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Boil water.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add thawed strawberries and the juice.
Add applesauce.
Chill it until set.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray the bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan with nonstick spray. Sprinkle coconut and pecans evenly in pan.
Set aside.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Pour evenly over coconut and pecans in pan.
Set aside.
In mixer bowl, cream oleo, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Drop this mix by spoonfuls in an even pattern over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: unbaked chocolate cookies
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients for 1 minute at rolling boil.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper and refrigerate.

title: 48 hour pickled fish
directions: Put ingredients in one gallon jar.
Stir well.
Add enough fish (raw and cut up) to fill jar.
Let sit 48 hours.

title: chocolate chip cream cheese bars
directions: Press 1 roll of cookie dough into a greased 9 x 13 pan. If it gets too sticky to work with put back in refrigerator for a few minutes. Cream eggs, sugar and cream cheese, pour over dough. Crumble remaining cookie roll and sprinkle over top. Cook at 350° for 30-40 minutes.

title: diet vegetable soup
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook until vegetables are tender. Longer cooking improves flavor.
Meats can be added.
This recipe can be canned.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add chili beans and cook until hot.
Place halves of hamburger buns on cookie sheet and brown (toast) in broiler.
When brown, spoon hamburger mixture on bun.
Place one slice of cheese on each.
Slide back in broiler until cheese melts.
Serve immediately.

title: cream of carrot soup
directions: Saute onions in oil until transparent.
Lift out of pan and put into blender.
In same pan, saute carrots until tender.
Set aside 1/3 of the carrots.
Put 2/3 of sauteed carrots in blender. Add 1/2 cup of stock or water and puree.
Heat in the top of a double boiler.
Combine skim milk powder with remaining stock, using a wire whisk.
Add to puree.
Add salt and pepper.
Add the reserved 1/3 sauteed carrots to the soup.
Garnish with dill or parsley.
Yields approximately 6 to 8 cups.

title: our "most" favorite banana pudding
directions: Layer vanilla wafers and bananas in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix pudding and milk in a large bowl.
Blend in sour cream and whipped topping in a bowl.
Fold gently into pudding.
Spoon over bananas and wafers.
Chill for at least 4 hours.

title: chinese noodle chicken salad
directions: In small bowl, stir together mustard and mayonnaise.
In separate bowl add chicken, celery, onion, pineapple, and oranges. Stir in mustard/mayonnaise mixture.
Chill.
Right before serving, stir in Chinese noodles.

title: portuguese potato casserole
directions: Drain cooked potatoes and put in large casserole dish. Sprinkle cubed cheese over potatoes, then onion, pimento, parsley flakes, paprika and garlic salt. Cube bread slices and arrange over top of casserole. Melt margarine and pour over entire casserole. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chili
directions: Cook meat and onions together and drain.
Cook spaghetti and drain.
Put 2 cans of tomatoes in a large pot and pour in tomato juice.
Add beans, salsa, and Chili-O mix and stir until blended well.
Add meat, onions, and spaghetti.
Simmer as long as you want.
I don't wait.
I eat it right away.
UMMMMMM!

title: lime jello
directions: Mix jello as directions given on box.
Cool until slightly set.
Mix everything together.
Whip well with beater.

title: chicken "tet"
directions: Boil chicken breasts; to water, add onion, garlic and celery. When done, debone and tear into small pieces.
Set aside 1/2 soup can of the water you boiled chicken in.
Boil noodles until done and drain off water.
Combine the chicken pieces, noodles, cream of chicken soup, water from boiled chicken, Parmesan cheese, mushrooms and lemon juice.
Mix well in 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle with paprika; dot with butter.
Bake, covered, 40 minutes and 15 to 10 minutes uncovered at 350°.

title: spicy dog bites
directions: Cut each frank crosswise into 5 or 6 pieces.
Place in chafing dish or stove top casserole over low heat.
In a small saucepan, combine jelly, chili sauce, mustard and onion.
Stir over low heat until jelly melts.
Pour over franks and heat through.
Serve warm.

title: party punch
directions: Mix together, chill and serve.

title: date loaf cake and icing
directions: Pour boiling water over dates and let stand 1 hour.

title: crescent chicken squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Blend cream cheese and melted margarine until smooth.

Add the next four ingredients, mixing well. Separate crescent rolls into four rectangles, seal perforations and spoon 1/2 cup chicken mixture onto center of each rectangle. Pull corners of dough to center of mixture; seal.
Brush tops with 1 tablespoon melted margarine.
Sprinkle tops with crushed croutons.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 20 to 25 minutes, until golden brown.

title: cherry torte
directions: Mix flour, sugar, nuts and margarine and pat in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Beat cream cheese and powdered sugar together until creamy.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Let set in refrigerator.
Pour pie filling onto baked crust, spreading evenly.
Spread Cool Whip on top of pie filling.
Refrigerate until served.

title: bleu cheese dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Chill before serving.

title: chilpolte marinade
directions: Put in blender and blend.
Marinate chicken, pork, ribs, etc. in marinade for an hour and a half.

title: german chocolate delight
directions: Liberally
butter
bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chopped
nuts.
Prepare cake mix according to directions on package.
Pour
over
nuts.
Mix
butter,
sugar and cream cheese. Drop
by spoonfuls into batter.
Bake 1 hour at 325°. Cake is better if you prepare 1 to 2 days early.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook all ingredients 15 minutes, stirring as needed.
Put in baking dish.

title: date delights
directions: Mix and cook until thick; spread on a cracker.
Bake 6 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool, then frost.

title: reuben supper
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish and layer each ingredients in order given, mixing the salad dressing and mayonnaise together before spreading over sauerkraut.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 30 minutes until cheese is melted and bread is toasty.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: layered spaghetti
directions: Cook hamburger and onion; drain.
Add soup, garlic salt, oregano and Ragu sauce; simmer 1/2 hour.
Layer spaghetti, sauce and Mozzarella cheese, ending with cheese.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk and syrup to very soft stage.
Remove from flame and add peanut butter, salt and vanilla immediately.
Beat until creamy.
Spread into 8-inch square buttered pan.
Makes 1 1/3 pounds.

title: soft, drop sugar cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar by hand until light in color and texture.
Dissolve baking soda in sour cream.
Beat eggs by hand. Add to butter and sugar mixture, then add flour, working it in by hand.
Add sour cream and baking soda mixture and flavoring.

title: cinnamon twists
directions: Grease 2 large baking sheets. Combine muffin mix, flour and yeast in large bowl; set aside. Combine contents of swirl packet from Mix, egg, hot water and melted butter in medium bowl. Stir until thoroughly blended. Pour into flour mixture; stir until thoroughly blended. Invert onto well floured surface; let rest for 10 minutes. Knead for 10 minutes or until smooth, adding flour as necessary. Divide dough in half. Cut and shape 24 small ropes from each half. Braid 3 ropes to form small twist and place on greased baking sheets. (Or, join ends of twist to form circles.) Combine egg white and 1 tsp. water in small bowl. Brush each twist with egg white mixture and sprinkle with contents of topping packet from Mix. Allow twists to rise 1 hour or until doubled in size. Preheat oven to 375°. Bake at 375° for 17 to 20 minutes or until deep golden brown. Remove to cooling racks.
For topping, combine confectioners sugar and milk in small bowl. Stir until smooth. Drizzle over warm rolls. Serve warm or cool completely. Makes 16 rolls.

title: sweet and sour macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions. Drain.
Rinse with cold water.
Drain.
Combine macaroni, carrot, celery, onion, cucumber and tomato.
Mix oil, vinegar and sugar.
Pour over vegetable mix.
Toss gently. Cover and chill 8 hours.

title: potato pancakes
directions: If blender is used, blend potatoes and squash or eggplant together.
Add one egg, milk and flour.
Mix all together in blender and fry in part oil and part butter to a golden brown.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together.
Roll in chopped nuts or chipped beef. Refrigerate.

title: frosted delights
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together; put aside.
Cream shortening with sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, vanilla and sifted ingredients; mix well.
Spread batter very thin on baking sheet. Fold brown sugar into egg whites.
Mix until soft peaks form. Spread over batter and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: hot broccoli sauce
directions: Place ingredients in a china bowl over steam and stir until margarine is melted.
May use sauce over broccoli, English peas, cauliflower or other vegetables.
Store in covered jar in refrigerator.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding together.
Add Cool Whip.
Stir. Chill.
Very easy to make and is ready when you finish stirring it.

title: hawaiian meatballs
directions: Mix beef, crumbs, onion, egg, salt, ginger and milk.
Shape mixture into tablespoon sized balls.
Melt shortening into large skillet.
Brown and cook meatballs.
Remove meatballs from skillet and pour off fat.
Mix cornstarch and sugar.
Stir in pineapple juice, vinegar and soy sauce until smooth.
Pour into skillet and cook over medium heat until thick.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Add meatballs, tidbits and peppers.
Heat thoroughly.

title: christmas congealed salad
directions: Drain and reserve pineapple juice.
Add water to juice to measure 1 cup liquid.
Bring mixture to a boil; add jello and stir until dissolved. Cool slightly. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into salad molds.
Refrigerate until congealed.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fish cakes
directions: Poach fish until flaky.
Drain off water until fish is very dry.
Boil potatoes, drain well and mash; must be very dry.

title: party snacks
directions: Mix pretzels, cereals and nuts in large roaster.
Heat in saucepan the margarine, bacon grease, sauces and seasonings. Gradually add sauce to other ingredients and mix well.
Bake 1 hour at 250° in uncovered roaster.
After thoroughly cool, these may be stored in tightly covered container for a month.

title: southern pecan pie(from a long time alabaman cook)
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly with sugar, dash salt, corn syrup and butter.
Add pecans.
Stir well.

title: streusel cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour lightly a 13 x 9 baking pan. In a mixing bowl, combine cake mix, eggs, oil and orange juice. Beat with electric mixer until well blended. Pour into prepared cake pan.

title: goulash
directions: Brown meat with onion, add all other ingredients and cook until well blended and seasoned.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add macaroni last.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Mix soup with water.
Place noodles in a 9 x 13-inch or smaller pan.
Layer noodles, tuna, carrots, peas and cheese.
Pour soup over.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: corn muffins
directions: Butter muffin pans for 12 muffins.
In a bowl, mix cornmeal, flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
In another bowl, beat the egg, milk and butter. Add the mixtures and stir until just moistened.
Spoon the batter into muffin cups.
Bake in a preheated 425 degree oven for 16 minutes or until lightly browned on the edges.

title: microwave chili
directions: Serve cold with nacho chips.

title: cranberry bread(makes one loaf)
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Add to this dry mixture one beaten egg.
In a 1 cup measuring cup, put 2 tablespoons liquid oil, juice and rind of orange and boiling water to fill cup.
Add liquid mixture to dry mixture and egg.
Stir until well mixed.
Add cranberries and nuts as desired and stir well.
Bake in a loaf pan for 1 hour or more at 315°.

title: "busy day casserole"
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Mix with chili and mushroom soup in casserole dish.
Prepare macaroni in saucepan.
Mix cooked (plain) macaroni with ground beef mixture.
Warm at 350° for 15 minutes. Sprinkle with shredded cheese and serve.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: baked stuffed tomatoes(pomodori ripiene con formaggio al forno)
directions: Wash
and
dry tomatoes.
Cut in half and gently scrape out seeds
with
a
knife.
Drain tomatoes upside down for 10 minutes. Combine
parsley,
garlic, oregano, Parmesan cheese, breadcrumbs, salt
and pepper.
Place tomatoes in 9 x 13-inch baking
dish and
divide
filling
among the 8 tomato halves. Sprinkle
with a little more Parmesan cheese and drizzle olive oil
over top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pecan or peanut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together syrup, sugar, vanilla and margarine; set aside.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add to syrup mixture and beat.
Add pecans or peanuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: corn flake candy
directions: Mix sugar and syrup in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Add peanut butter and mix until smooth.
Remove from heat and add corn flakes.
Mix until coated.
Drop by spoonfuls on buttered wax paper.
Cool.

title: deer, elk or antelope stew
directions: In dish with
cover,
marinate	meat in vinegar and 1/2 cup dry
wine
overnight
in
refrigerator.
Drain thoroughly. Dry with paper towel.
Dredge meat in flour.
In heavy skillet with tight fitting
lid,
melt
bacon
drippings or shortening over medium-high heat.
Brown
meat
on	all
sides.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper
to taste.	Add onion.
Saute until limp. Stir in celery, parsley,
carrots, thyme, 1/2 cup wine and 3/4 cup beef broth.
Cover.
Simmer
over
low heat for 2 hours or until meat is tender.	Add remaining 3/4 cup consomme or broth during cooking.
Add
mushrooms,
olives and remaining 1/2 cup wine and simmer 40
minutes more; thicken liquid with 1 tablespoon flour.

title: chocolate crisco frosting
directions: In a saucepan, melt Crisco and remove from heat.
Stir in cocoa and salt.
Mix milk and vanilla in a mixing bowl.
Stir in cocoa mixture into sugar, milk and vanilla mixture.
Beat at medium speed until smooth and creamy.
Add 1 tablespoon more milk, if needed, for good smooth spreading.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown ground round or round steak, onion, mushrooms and spices.
Add mushroom soup.
Simmer for about 20 minutes.
Add sour cream to mixture.
Pour over hot noodles.

title: mother's famous chocolate cake(from the files of ola dortch williams)
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Sift flour with cocoa.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
To creamed mixture, add coffee, vanilla, flour mixture and salt.
Beat well, then add 4 eggs, one at a time and soda mixture.
Mix well.
Bake in 3 (8-inch) round layer pans at 325°.
Frost with favorite fudge frosting.
Cake is very moist and brownie-like.
I've made 100's of these!

title: homemade bread
directions: Warm milk and butter together.
In a large bowl, combine the water, sugar, yeast, salt and milk mixture.
Add the flours. Knead until smooth and elastic, adding as little additional flour as possible.
Let rise until doubled; punch down.
Let rise until doubled again.
Form into 2 loaves and place in greased loaf pans. Bake in a 350° oven for 50 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: fruit topping
directions: Mix all together.
Great over pound cake, ice cream or just by itself!

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix and shape into loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with Mustard Sauce.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream sugar and oleo and add flour and mix well.
Set aside 3/4 cup of this mixture.
Into remaining mixture sprinkle soda, spices and eggs.
Mix well.
Stir in buttermilk and mix lightly. Pour into greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle remaining mixture over top; bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: sweet and sour beans(allow for 3 to 5 hours in crock-pot.)
directions: Fry
bacon
in large skillet until crisp.
Remove bacon and drain
off	some
of
the
fat.
Mix in 2-cup measure, the sugar, mustard, garlic powder, salt and vinegar.
Slice onions and separate
the
slices.
Cook in fat until tender.
Stir in the mixture.
Cover; simmer for 20 minutes.

title: basic white sauce
directions: To prepare white sauce, over medium heat, bring milk just to a boil in a small saucepan.
Remove from heat.
In a small, heavy-bottomed saucepan over medium heat, melt butter.
With a wooden spoon stir in flour until mixture is thoroughly blended and bubbly (about 2 minutes).
Gradually add reserved milk, whisking constantly.
Bring mixture to a simmer over medium heat, continuing to stir.
Add salt and pepper and cook, stirring constantly, until sauce is thick and smooth (5 to 10 minutes).

title: rosettes
directions: Cook in deep fryer; oil should be heated to 400°.

title: chef salad
directions: Gently combine all ingredients except dressings in a salad bowl.
Combine dressing and pour over salad. Toss gently.
Serves 8.
Contains 160 calories.

title: strawberry cake frosting
directions: In a small saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in milk, salt and vanilla and heat until hot (not boiling).
Add pureed strawberries and enough confectioners sugar to make mixture spreadable for frosting.

title: hacienda dinner
directions: Brown sausage, onion and green pepper.
Drain.
Add tomatoes, barbecue sauce, uncooked macaroni and cheese dinner.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin raisin muffins
directions: Stir all dry ingredients together.
Add all moist ingredients; mix well.
Add raisins.
Place in sprayed muffin pans.
Makes 12 muffins.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
One serving is 3 muffins and contains 30 calories.

title: fluffy dumplings
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together in a bowl.
Cut in shortening until coarse.
Lightly mix in milk with fork to make a soft dough.
Stir as little as possible.
Drop tablespoonfuls of dough into broth.
Cook 10 minutes, uncovered, then cover tightly and simmer 10 minutes longer.

title: homemade lemonade
directions: Stir together sugar and 1/2 cup boiling water until sugar dissolves. Stir in lemon rind, lemon juice and 5 cups of cold water. Chill for 8 hours. Garnish with fresh lemon slices. Yield: 8 cups.

title: peanut butter snack cups
directions: Line 12-cup muffin pan with paper baking cups.
Combine crumbs and butter; mix well.
Press about 1 tablespoon of the crumb mixture into each cup.
Top with 1 tablespoon whipped topping. Gradually add milk to peanut butter in bowl and blend until smooth. Add pudding mix.
With electric mixer at low speed, beat until blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Fold in remaining topping.
Spoon into crumb-lined cups.
Top each cup with 1 teaspoon of the preserves. Freeze about 4 hours.
To serve, peel off papers.

title: sour cream dip
directions: Pour sour cream in bowl. Fill sour cream container with Hellmann's mayo. Put in bowl with sour cream. Add grated onion and parsley flakes. Mix with mixer until well blended. Great all year long.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Add rest of ingredients (not the marshmallows).
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 300° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cover with the marshmallows. Return to oven for 5 minutes only.
Cool and frost.

title: karen's apple pie
directions: Dip the apples out of the sauce they come in and discard the sauce.
(The sauce will make the pie too juicy, will not cut to serve well.)
Place the fried apples in the unbaked pie crust. Mix the melted butter or margarine, pecans, brown sugar and flour until crumbly.
Place the dry mixture on top of the apples and bake in a 350° oven until the crust is brown and the top is golden.

title: alpine chicken casserole
directions: Mix chopped chicken, bread crumbs, celery, onion, milk, salt, pepper and cream of chicken soup.
Layer in a 9x12 casserole dish 1/2 chicken mixture and 1/2 slices of cheese.
Add remaining chicken mixture and top with remaining cheese slices.
Cook for 30-40 minutes at 350°.
Cut into squares.
Great with frozen cranberry salad and a roll for luncheon dish.
Serves 8.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil macaroni; drain and cool.
Add sugar, vinegar, mayonnaise, bell pepper and pimento.
Mix well.

title: portuguese bean soup
directions: Wash beans and put in a large Dutch oven.
Cover with boiling water and let stand 1 hour.
Cut sausage into 1/4-inch slices. Add with onion to the undrained beans.
Cook for one hour over low heat until beans are tender.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours, adding more water, if needed.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Crust:
Put powdered sugar and flour in bowl and pour melted margarine in on top and mix until blended.
Pat in greased pizza pan.
Bake in 300° oven for 15 minutes.
This pizza pan should be approximately 15-inch diameter.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs.
Blend in flour, cocoa, salt, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread miniature marshmallows evenly over top.
Return to oven and brown marshmallows under broiler.
Cool and cover with chocolate icing.

title: tasty chicken wings
directions: Separate wings at joint.
Discard tips.
Mix sauce ingredients together in a Dutch oven.
Add chicken wing parts and cook over low heat for 40 minutes or until tender.
Baste occasionally, then place wings in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve warm.

title: au gratin chicken bake
directions: Combine chicken soup, water chestnuts, fettucini, 1/2 c. Parmesan, milk and pimiento.
Mix lightly.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole; bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and bake until Cheddar melts.

title: tangy baked chicken
directions: Rinse chicken; pat dry with paper towels.
Combine peppers; rub over chicken.
Combine salad dressing, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Lightly brush both sides of chicken with dressing mixture.
Place chicken in shallow baking dish.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until chicken is done. In small saucepan heat remaining dressing mix to boiling; serve with chicken.

title: turkey tortilla casserole
directions: In 2-quart low baking dish (9 x 13-inches), cook onion, celery and broth in microwave for 2 to 3 minutes, until tender.
Stir in turkey, tortillas, chilies, soup, pepper and 6 ounces of the cheese.
Top casserole with reserved cheese and salsa.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: cherry pie supreme
directions: Start oven at 425°.
Spread 1/2 cherry pie filling over the bottom of crust; save remaining filling.
Bake for 15 minutes until pastry is golden brown.
Beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat.
Pour cheese mixture over hot cherry pie filling.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Continue baking 25 to 30 minutes.
Before serving, spoon sour cream around rim and spoon the rest of the cherry filling in the center.

title: homemade kahlua
directions: Mix coffee and sugar in a bowl. Stir until dissolved. Cool completely. Add brandy to sugar/coffee mixture. Divide mixture evenly between 2 fifth bottles. Add a vanilla bean to each bottle. Cap after the liquid is completely cooled. Must be stored at least 30 days to steep before consuming to get full flavor.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Place oleo, sugar and milk into saucepan. Bring ingredients to boil. Turn off heat after boils. Add oats, peanut butter, vanilla, cocoa and salt to saucepan. Mix
well together. Drop on wax paper.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Boil peeled and cut sweet potatoes about 20 minutes.
Preheat oven to 450°. Drain potatoes, mash and add margarine and sugar while still hot.
Sift flour into mixture. Cut in shortening. Add water, if needed, for right consistency.
Roll out and cut to size and thickness you like. Bake about 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
May be partly done ahead.
Stores well.
Yields 4 to 5 dozen.

title: twinkie delight
directions: Arrange Twinkies in 3 rows of 5 in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix jello with boiling water; add 1 cup cold water. Add strawberries and blend. Pour over Twinkies. Make pudding according to directions; pour over jello. Top with Cool Whip.

title: hawaiian punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serves a "bunch".

title: homemade rice krispies crunch bars
directions: Microwave on High 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes the milk chocolate and dark chocolate.
Blend until smooth.
Add coconut and cereal; blend well.
Press mixture into jelly roll pan or large rectangular pan.
Chill to harden.
Cut into bars.

title: cheese boxes
directions: Beat oleo, cheese, egg and pepper until fluffy.
Cut crusts from bread slices, then cut each slice into 4 squares.
Put egg and cheese mixture in between 3 squares to make a box.
Frost top and sides with egg-cheese mixture.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes 36 boxes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all together and put in a dish.
Crush corn flakes and put on top.
Melt 1 stick margarine. Spoon over the top.
Bake for 1 1/4 hours at 350°.

title: l.b.j.  ranch deer meat sausage
directions: Mix together for 200 pounds of sausage.
A favorite recipe at the LBJ Ranch is for Deer Meat Sausage.
The finished product is recommended for late Sunday morning breakfast with scrambled eggs, hominy grits, hot biscuits and boiling hot coffee.
Or, it can be served for a late afternoon snack in hot biscuits.

title: sausage fettuccine
directions: Cook fettuccine according to package directions. Drain.
Melt butter in a large skillet. Saute mushrooms and garlic until mushrooms are soft. Remove from skillet.
In the same skillet, heat sausage over medium heat until lightly browned. Drain excess drippings. Add mushrooms and garlic back to the skillet. In a small bowl, combine eggs and cream.
Add to skillet mixture and heat just until cream mixture is hot (do not boil). Add cooked fettuccine, tossing gently.
Mix in cheese and parsley and serve.

title: hamburger cream cheese casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion in butter in skillet.
Stir in salt, pepper and tomato sauce.
Remove from heat.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, green pepper and onion.
In a 3-quart casserole, spread half the noodles. Cover with cheese mixture.
Top with remaining noodles.
Pour hamburger mixture over top.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings. Casserole can be frozen.

title: my best gingerbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar together and add egg.
Combine molasses with hot water.
Add dry ingredients to butter and sugar mixture alternately with small amounts of liquid mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Bake in wax paper lined 9 x 9 x 2 inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Double for long loaf pan.

title: licious pie
directions: Mix all together and put into graham cracker crusts and freeze. Makes 2 pies.

title: farmer jones special
directions: Cook celery and onion in butter or margarine until golden brown.
Cover.
Cook until vegetables are tender.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add strawberries to punch bowl.

title: chicken stew
directions: Brown skinless thighs in 2 tablespoons oil.
Add onion and 1 teaspoon salt.
Cook until tender.
With a fork, remove chicken to bowl, leaving onion in skillet.
In bowl, mix together orange juice, broth, flour and 3/4 cup water.
Add this mixture and the potatoes to the onion in the skillet.
Also add 1/4 teaspoon salt. Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Return thighs to skillet.
Stir in remaining rosemary and cook until done.
May garnish with thin strips of orange peel.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Combine the first 8 ingredients; mix lightly.
Put into 2-quart baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Melt butter in pan.
Add flour and cook gradually add milk; cook until thick and smooth.
Add cheese and stir until smooth.
Stir in corn. Pour over meat and top with pepper rings.
Bake 350° for 20 minutes.
tags: whole kernel corn with sweet peppers

title: vanilla cookies(this is an easy cookie recipe.)
directions: Put sugar, syrup and one cup of cream in a heavy saucepan. Boil on medium heat to soft ball, then add second cup of cream, and again boil to soft ball.
Add third cup of cream and boil to a firm ball.
Add vanilla and pour into a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
When cooled slightly, cut into squares.
You can cut with scissors.

title: stratta(serves 6 to 8)
directions: To this you may add mushrooms, tomatoes, cooked bacon or cooked sausage.

title: candie apple walnut pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Put in 1 frozen pie shell.
Crumble 2nd pie shell and mix with 2 tablespoons sugar.
Sprinkle on top of pie.
Bake at 350° until candies bubble through top.

title: can-can casserole
directions: In shallow baking dish, combine beans, beef and peppers. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until hot.
Stir.
Top with border of chips.
Bake for 5 more minutes.
Garnish with lettuce and olives.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Or if rushed, use 1 can or 2 of Swanson white chicken, broth from chicken or 1 can of broth added to water or 2 chicken bouillon cubes added to water.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a well-greased casserole dish. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: hamburger buns
directions: In a large mixer bowl, combine 4 cups of flour and the yeast. Combine warm water, oil, sugar and salt.
Add to dry mixture in bowl.
Add eggs.
Beat at low speed of electric mixer for 1/2 minute, scraping sides of bowl constantly.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
By hand, stir in enough of the remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out on a lightly floured surface.
Knead until smooth.

title: chicken cheese casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch dish, place chicken.
Place cheese and chestnuts on top.
Pour diluted soup over all. Mix stuffing with margarine and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 325° until brown and bubbly, about 30 minutes.
If it gets too brown, place a piece of foil on top near end of baking.

title: five flavoring pound cake
directions: Soften butter to room temperature.
Cream butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and stir.
Mix flour and baking powder and add alternately with milk.
Add extracts and stir.
Spray 10-inch tube pan with Pam to coat.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Test for doneness after 1st hour.

title: texas hash
directions: Saute onions in shortening in 10-inch skillet until brown. Stir in ground beef, green peppers, salt, pepper, chili powder and rice.
Place in casserole dish.
Pour tomatoes over mixture; cover. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chicken in a pot
directions: Melt margarine.
Add Italian or garlic dressing.
Dip chicken breasts in mixture (other pieces optional).
Place chicken in center of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chop or cube potatoes and dip them in mixture or drain 1 can of new potatoes and dip in mixture.
Place on one side of chicken in the dish.
Drain green beans and dip them.
Place them on the other side of the chicken.
Cover with foil and bake in oven for 50 minutes at 400°.
After 50 minutes, pull back the foil, leaving chicken and potatoes exposed, but leaving green beans covered.
Bake an additional 10 to 15 minutes.

title: italian chicken supreme
directions: Drain artichokes, reserving liquid from one jar.
Combine liquid with olive oil in skillet.
Heat over low heat.
Place flour, paprika, garlic powder and 1/2 teaspoon black pepper in a paper bag and place the pieces of chicken inside and toss to coat thoroughly.
Brown chicken for 3 to 7 minutes on each side over medium-high heat.
Transfer chicken to a 3-quart casserole or baking pan.
Add the onion and garlic cloves to the skillet and saute over medium heat until softened (10 to 15 minutes).
Add tomatoes, mushrooms, sherry and remaining spices to skillet and simmer for 10 minutes.
Pour sauces over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 minutes.
Remove from oven and stir in artichokes. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
To serve, bake, covered, for 25 minutes at 350°.
Serve over rice or vermicelli.
Makes 8 servings.

title: heidesand(german)
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add egg and vanilla.
Stir in flour mixed with cream of tartar and soda.
Form small balls. (Refrigerate dough before making balls.)
Put on ungreased cookie sheet, flatten with glass that has been dipped in fine sugar. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add cold water; mix well. Cool.
Grind cranberries and oranges.
Add apples and sugar.
Add fruit to gelatin.
Pour into shallow dish.
Chill until firm. Yields 24 servings.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix all together. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes. Ice with the Impeachment Icing.

title: dole raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt in bowl; set aside.
Beat margarine and sugars in bowl.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Beat in flour mixture until blended.
Gradually add oats and raisins while stirring.

title: chili
directions: Put all ingredients in a crock-pot in order listed. Stir once. Cover and cook on low 8 hours.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients; form a ball.
Sprinkle with a few more finely chopped pecans.

title: sour cream pie
directions: Boil raisins until tender; cool.
Mix flour, milk, sugar, sour cream and beaten egg yolks.
Cook, stirring constantly.
Add raisins and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue.
Brown in oven at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: spicy raisin-walnut pie
directions: Heat oven to 345°.
Beat all ingredients, except walnuts and raisins, until well blended.
Stir in walnuts and raisins;
mix well.
Pour into pastry lined pie plate.
Bake until set, approximately 50 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Serve warm or refrigerate.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Spray 12-inch pan with Pam and put shredded potatoes in pan on low heat (covered) to cook.
When potatoes are almost done, throw eggs in, stirring frequently so the mixture won't stick.
Crumble bacon on top when the eggs are done.
Serve on flour tortilla with cheese and hot sauce.

title: goulash
directions: Boil macaroni as directed on the box.
Brown hamburger and onion in a large skillet; drain.
Add ketchup, cheese from macaroni and cheese box and brown sugar.
Drain macaroni and mix all together in a large pan.
Cook on medium heat until hot.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: whoopie pies
directions: *One tablespoon vinegar, then add milk to equal 1 cup.

title: carrot pennies
directions: Mix all ingredients, except vegetables.
Pour mixture over combined vegetables.

title: stove top potpourri
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store airtight at room temperature.
To use:
Add 3 tablespoons of mixture to 2 cups of simmering water in a saucepan over low heat.
Fragrance lasts about 2 hours.
Add more water, if desired.

title: set up
directions: Brown Spam and corned beef in pan with butter.
After browned, mix in cooked rice.
Let simmer for 5 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender. Remove from heat. Add salt, pepper and butter. Add cracker crumbs, milk, egg and half the grated cheese. Stir until well blended. Pour into casserole; sprinkle remaining grated cheese over top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Yields 8 servings.

title: monterey chicken-rice bake
directions: Blend cottage cheese, cream cheese and sour cream until smooth.
Add mixture to remaining ingredients.
Pour into shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Top with corn chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crabmeat spread
directions: Spread cream cheese over the surface of a serving plate, add cocktail sauce to cover the cream cheese and then sprinkle with crabmeat.

title: hickory chicken
directions: In roasting pan, pour 2 to 3 cups of water and all but 1 tablespoon liquid hickory.
Place roasting rack in pan.
Place chicken on rack.
Put stick of margarine inside chicken, then put 1 tablespoon of hickory smoke inside chicken.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil.
Place in 300° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: chicken-sausage-wild rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage in heavy skillet.
Save drippings to saute onions.
Prepare rice according to box directions.
Combine chicken, sausage, onions and rice along with soup.
Transfer to two 7 x 11-inch casseroles.
Melt oleo in skillet.
Lightly saute croutons.
Spread on top of casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serve with favorite salad and homemade bread.

title: monster cookies
directions: Start with a big bowl.
Mix all together.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.
Don't overbake.

title: pineapple custard pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: easy chicken
directions: Mix
the first 3 ingredients.
Place chicken breasts in a flat casserole.
Cover
with sauce.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Sauce is sufficient to cover 8 boneless pieces.

title: casey's favorite fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Mix in eggs.
Beat well until batter is light and fluffy. Add melted chocolate; blend well.
Sift together cake flour, baking soda and salt.
Add alternating with ice water.
Mix well.
Spray three 8-inch pans with Baker's Joy or use Pam and sprinkle well with flour.
Pour batter into pans.
Weight each pan on a scale to be sure the dough is divided equally.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes (until a cake tester comes out clean or until you can gently press a finger into the top of cake and the cake will spring back into position.
Cool.

title: jane's kielbasa
directions: Combine all ingredients except kielbasa and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Add kielbasa and bake for another 30 minutes.

title: chocolate vinegar cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together directly into ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch cake pan.
Make 3 depressions with spoon and add vanilla to one, vinegar to another and melted butter to the third.
Pour water over all and stir together until well mixed.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Leave cake in pan.
Frost and serve while warm.
Serves 9 to 12.

title: easy crumb cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed, baking for a shorter time than given on the box for a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut rest of ingredients together to make crumb topping.
Spread over baked cake and return to oven for 10 minutes.
Cool slightly and then sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Serve warm or cold.

title: delicious dessert
directions: Mix Dream Whip according to directions.
Let ice cream and milk stand in large bowl.
Crush crackers with oleo; set aside 3/4 cup of crumb mixture.
Pat rest of crumb mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix ice cream and milk until mixed.
Gradually add dry pudding until mixed.
Pour over crust.
Top with Dream Whip and crumbs.
Refrigerate.

title: rum cake
directions: Put cake mix in bowl and add remaining ingredients.
Mix for 2 minutes.
Grease and flour Bundt or ring cake pan.
Chopped nuts or cherries may be put in bottom of pan or mixed in batter.
Pour into pan and bake at 325° for 60 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour, shortening, salt and baking powder until crumbly. Add egg with water.
Mix.
Sometimes it takes more water.

title: honey baked chicken
directions: Combine ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 300°.
Baste every 15 minutes until chicken is tender and nearly brown.
(Turn chicken.) Good with rice.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Sprinkle 1 can coconut and 1 cup chopped pecans into the pan.
Mix German chocolate cake mix according to directions.
Spread over coconut and pecans.
Mix together powdered sugar, cream cheese and melted butter.
Drop by the spoonful over the cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat sugar, flour, eggs, salt, corn syrup, melted margarine and vanilla with mixer.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into prepared pastry shell and bake 45 to 50 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Prepare rice as directed. Cook sausage, using fork to crumble while cooking. Drain and set aside.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Parboil noodles.
While noodles are draining, soften margarine and cream cheese in pot.
Throw noodles back in and then everything else back into pot.
Grease casserole and add all the ingredients.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, about 45 minutes to 1 hour or until done.
Sprinkle cinnamon on casserole after about 35 minutes.

title: carrot pineapple cake
directions: In large bowl, stir together dry ingredients.
Add oil, eggs, carrots, pineapple and vanilla flavoring.
Mix by hand only.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: buttercream easter eggs
directions: Cream 1 cup of butter and the cream cheese together.
Blend in sugar, gradually.
Shape cream cheese mixture into small eggs. Cool for about 1 hour.

title: millie's hot roll recipe
directions: Make pancakes according to the directions.
Cut up 4 to 6 hot dogs (cut round).
Add to batter and cook as directed.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Have cheese at room temperature.
Chop fine onion and corned beef.
Mix all ingredients well.
Form into ball.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift sugar, flour and soda.
Melt butter, cocoa and water; bring to rapid boil.
Pour over dry ingredients that were sifted. Add buttermilk, vanilla and eggs and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: candice bergen's chicken casserole
directions: Mix soups and wine; pour over chicken, in a casserole dish, and top with cheese.
Cover and bake at 300° for 2 hours.
Remove cover and bake 30 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together Crisco, margarine, eggs and 1 1/2 cups sugar. Add flour, vanilla and milk.
Beat for 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a tube pan.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: clams and pasta
directions: In 1-quart saucepan, heat oil with crushed garlic.
Heat until garlic is toasted (do not overcook).
Add parsley.
Take pan off stove.
Add two cans clams with liquid.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: lemon dessert(if you like lemon, you'll love this lemon cake.)
directions: Prepare the cake mix according to directions in a 9 x 12-inch pan according to directions.
Let cool.
Cut cake in half; crumble 1/2 into another 9 x 12-inch pan.
Press down.
Mix the Eagle Brand milk with lemonade; pour over the crumbs.
Crumble the other half of the cake on this and press down.
Ice with whipped topping; sprinkle generously with coconut.

title: icebox mash potatoes
directions: Peel and cut as to boil. Cook, then drain. Mash and beat in cream cheese, sour cream and seasonings. Store in refrigerator. Will keep 2 weeks in closed container. Bake at 300° for 1 hour. Yields 15 to 16 servings.

title: italian meatball ragout
directions: Mix ground beef lightly with egg, bread crumbs, parsley, and 1 teaspoon of the salt until well-blended; shape into 24 balls. Brown, half at a time, in salad oil in a large frying pan. Remove with a slotted spoon and set aside. Stir onion and garlic into drippings in pan; saute just until soft. Add eggplant and meatballs. Mix tomatoes with remaining 1 teaspoon salt, sugar, and cumin seeds; pour over meatballs and eggplant. Cover.

title: old-time popcorn balls
directions: In a large pan, mix sugar, molasses and water.
Cook to a rolling boil.
Continue to cook until the syrup, dropping from a spoon, spins a thread.
Quickly stir in the vanilla and soda.
Pour syrup over popcorn.
Stir with a large spoon.

title: mexican drumsticks
directions: Melt margarine and stir in taco mix, picante, sugar and salt. Roll each drumstick in mixture, then in crushed chips.
Place, not touching, in pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: mushroom salad
directions: In a salad bowl, combine thinly sliced mushrooms and thinly sliced radishes.
Force the yolks of the eggs through a sieve into a bowl and stir in mustard and vinegar.
Add olive oil in a stream, beating constantly, and beat the dressing until it is creamy.
Add parsley and chives, then salt and pepper to taste. Pour the dressing over the mushrooms and radishes; add chopped egg whites and toss.

title: bacon appetizers
directions: Take each strip of bacon and coat completely and thoroughly with brown sugar (press brown sugar into bacon).
Place the coated bacon on a foil covered cookie sheet.
Keep the bacon flat and not touching each other.
Bake 11 to 13 minutes or until golden brown at 475°.
Allow to cool on tinfoil.
Stir in airtight container.

title: hominy soup(southeastern tribes)
directions: Render the salt pork thoroughly in a large, heavy kettle. Drain off drippings.
Add onion to the kettle and saute slowly until golden and transparent.
Mix in the hominy and beat gently, stirring for about 5 minutes.
Add buttermilk, salt and pepper and heat very slowly (do not allow to simmer) for about 5 minutes. This soup should be served warm, not hot.

title: turkey divan
directions: In a flat Pyrex dish, put a layer of broccoli and then turkey. Combine next 5 ingredients and pour over turkey and broccoli. Top with mixture of bread crumbs and margarine.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Brown and drain hamburger and bacon.
Add all ingredients in casserole dish and bake one hour at 350°.

title: fresh peach cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Mash or finely dice peaches and cook slightly (no water); set aside to cool.
Plump raisins in boiling water, drain on paper towel, cool and dredge with flour.
Cream together margarine and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture alternately with peaches. Stir in vanilla; fold in raisins.
Turn into pan; bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool completely and frost.
Melt the 1/2 cup margarine and brown sugar.
Boil 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Add milk and just bring to boiling point and remove from stove. Cool to lukewarm; add sugar gradually and beat with electric mixer.
Add vanilla.
Beat until smooth.

title: tony's crock pot chicken
directions: Wash chicken well and place in crock pot. Place a piece of pepper, onion and celery inside chicken. Salt and pepper to taste. Place rest of vegetables and mushrooms on chicken. (Add no water.)

title: fresh tomato sauce
directions: Heat corn oil over
medium
heat.
Add rest of ingredients and cook 2 minutes, stirring.
Then simmer 30 minutes.

title: oreo cake
directions: Crush cookies (except 12; reserve for later use).
Mix with melted butter.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar until smooth and creamy.
Pour 3/4 mixture onto cookie crust and spread evenly.
Prepare pudding as directed on box.
Pour 3/4 of pudding on top of cream cheese mixture.
Combine the remaining cream cheese mixture and the pudding; mix well.
Pour on top of the pudding and spread evenly. Crush remaining 12 cookies and sprinkle on top.
Chill for 3 to 4 hours or until cake is set.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: In 8 x 14-inch glass pan pour cherry pie filling.
Onto pie filling spread entire can of crushed pineapple.
Pour entire package of dry yellow cake mix over pineapple.
Pour nuts over cake mix.
Slice pats of butter (entire stick); place over nuts.
In oven bake at 350° until brown, about 20 minutes.

title: jollof rice
directions: Season chicken with salt and black pepper.
In large frying pan, heat oil over medium heat for 4-5 minutes.
Add chicken pieces and brown on both sides.
Place chicken in a kettle and set aside. Add onions and salt pork to oil in frying pan and saut until onions are transparent.
Add onions and pork to kettle.
Set frying pan aside.
Add bouillon cubes, red pepper, thyme, 1 1/2 c. water and tomato paste to kettle; stir well.
Simmer over low heat for about 10 minutes.
Add rice to frying pan and stir to coat with oil.
Add rice and vegetables to kettle, stir well and cover.
Cook over low heat for 35-40 minutes or until vegetables and rice are tender.

title: french bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Soak bread in half and half.
Crush with hands until well mixed.
Add all ingredients, except butter. Stir well.
Pour melted butter into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Pour batter into pan and bake until firm at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes. Cool.
Top with vanilla sauce.

title: sesame seed dip
directions: In a blender, combine all the ingredients, except sesame seed, until smooth and milky white in color.
Refrigerate.
Garnish with sesame seed.
Serve with crackers or as a vegetable dip.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, cream, butter and vanilla in a large saucepan. Bring to a rolling boil over medium heat.
Boil for 9 minutes. Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Beat by hand until smooth.
Pour into 2 buttered platters and slice into squares when completely cooled.

title: taco dip
directions: In large bowl, mix sour cream, cream cheese and taco seasoning until well blended and put in bottom of 9 x 13 dish. Spread refried beans onto cream cheese mixture and top with remaining ingredients.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt butter or margarine on low heat.
Put in peanut butter, stirring in until smooth.
Take off heat, then take 1 box of powdered sugar.
Pour mixture of butter and peanut butter over the powdered sugar and mix through until smooth.
Put in pan and refrigerate until hard enough to cut, eat and enjoy.

title: chili
directions: Saute onions in oil in large skillet until onions are brown. Add ground beef and brown; drain off excess fat.
Add beans, ketchup, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil, then cut temperature to low and simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.

title: moist pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, oil and pumpkin.
Add remaining ingredients in order listed.
Place in greased loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, salt, soda, vanilla, nuts and apples.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan and cook about 30 to 35 minutes at 300°.

title: baked custard
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and salt.
Bring milk to scalding and stir into egg mixture.
Add vanilla and pour into custard cups. Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Place cups in pan of hot water.
Bake in slow oven at 325° until mixture does not adhere to a knife blade, about 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: krispie cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, sugars and eggs.
Add sifted flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Add vanilla. Work in oats, Krispies and chocolate chips.
Cook by teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Fill pot with 6 cups of water and bring to a boil.
Add noodles and bring to a boil.
Cook until tender.
Drain and rinse with hot water.
In a large bowl, mix soup, milk, peas, salt, pepper and celery seed.
Pour into a 2 quart casserole dish.
Add noodles and sprinkle top with parsley. Cover and cook for one hour at 350°.

title: butterhorns
directions: Add 1 tablespoon sugar to yeast and warm water.
Mix with remaining ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Divide into 3 parts.
Roll 1/4-inch thick and cut into pie wedge shapes.
Roll from large end.
Let rise 2 hours.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes on cookie sheet at 350°.
Brush with butter.

title: cherry saladstilwell, kansas
directions: Mix all together and chill 1 hour.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well except cheese, then sprinkle the cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: easy coffeecake
directions: Place rolls frozen in Bundt pan.
Mix brown sugar and pudding mix.
Sprinkle mixture over rolls.
Put pecans on top.
Melt butter and pour over mixture.
Cover with Saran Wrap and a towel over Saran Wrap.
Let set overnight.
Punch down and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand a few minutes.
Dump out, but be careful because the sauce is hot.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 8 x 9-inch pan.
Pour in mixture of sugar, flour and milk.
Drop in sliced peaches.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato delight
directions: Slice yams and apples and place in layers in casserole dish. Dot with butter and cover with juices, sugar and salt.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 400° until bubbly.
Lower heat to 350° for 40 minutes.
Add nuts and marshmallows and bake 5 minutes or until marshmallows are light brown.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in 1/2 tablespoon cooking oil. Mix all ingredients into a casserole dish. Top with bread crumbs mixed with 1/2 tablespoon cooking oil. Brown 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together in 9x13 baking dish.

title: evan's favorite spaghetti
directions: Cook vermicelli according to package directions.
Drain and rinse with cool water.
Reheat in microwave on High for 30 seconds. Melt butter over the top.
Add Parmesan cheese and pepper to taste.

title: vinegar cobbler(1800)
directions: Put water, sugar and vinegar on to boil.
Add oleo.
Make crust as for pies.
Roll thin and pinch off small pieces.
Drop in liquid and let boil.
Do not make too dry.
Cool thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
Pour in bread pan and top with crust.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake in oven until brown.

title: sweet corn soup with chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients in a kettle except coconut milk. Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer for about 15 minutes. Remove from heat and add coconut milk.
Stir well and serve. Yields 4 servings.

title: mexican soup
directions: Bake chicken breasts in whipping cream with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Saute onion in butter.
Add chicken and all other ingredients.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve.

title: fry cabbage
directions: Put in heavy pan or skillet, shredded cabbage or cut as for cabbage slaw.
Add rest of ingredients.
Fry on top of stove slowly.
Stir occasionally.
Also can be eaten cold.

title: gazpacho
directions: Combine the onions, garlic, green peppers and tomatoes.
Force through a sieve or puree in a blender.
Add salt, pepper and paprika.
Add the olive oil gradually, beating steadily.
Add the vinegar and water and stir well.
Place in the refrigerator to chill for at least 2 hours.
Use a wooden or glass bowl, not metal. Add the cucumber slices before serving.
If desired, slices of toast rubbed with garlic may be served with the Gazpacho.
Serves 6.

title: baked mashed potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until fork-tender.
Drain.
Add milk, salt and 1 tablespoons butter.
Beat until fluffy.
Fold in egg, sour cream, cottage cheese and onion.
Place in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.

title: honey-glazed ham
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.

title: english pea and asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus and peas.
Place in buttered Corning dish. Mix crumbs with melted butter; brown and sprinkle half over vegetables.
Add mushrooms.
Make sauce:
Melt 4 tablespoons butter; stir in flour and salt slowly.
Add milk and stir until sauce thickens.
Stir in cheese spread.
Pour sauce over vegetables and top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until well heated.

title: cranberry sauce cake icing
directions: Cook the 1/4 cup pineapple juice and cornstarch in saucepan until thickens (1 minute).
Add cranberry sauce.
Cool and refrigerate.
Spread between three 9-inch cake layers.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Tear chicken in small pieces.
Place in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch Pyrex.
Layer the rice and chicken.
Mix the remaining ingredients and pour over chicken and rice.
Top with buttered bread crumbs and sliced almonds.
Cook 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: mango with passion fruit
directions: Arrange mango and dates on 4 dessert plates.
Cut passion fruit in half and scoop out center.
Mix passion fruit and yogurt. Serve with fruit.
Makes 4 servings at 110 calories per serving.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Blend together all ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes. Serve warm with crackers.

title: shriners kula onion casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt butter in large skillet over medium heat.
Add onions.
Saute until transparent.
Cook rice in boiling water 5 minutes.
Drain.
Add rice, cheese and half and half to onions.
Pour into shallow 2-quart baking dish and bake uncovered 1 hour.

title: broccoli stir-fry
directions: Stir-fry meat in hot oil until cooked.
Add broccoli, carrots and water.
Cook and cover 5 to 7 minutes.
Add prepared sauce or seasoning mix.
Heat through.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: corn flake candy
directions: Combine sugar and syrup; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter, then all other ingredients until well coated.
Drop by teaspoons onto wax paper.

title: presbyterian salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix all together and let cool for at least one hour.

title: "my" meat loaf
directions: Combine sirloin and sausage. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Form into an oblong shape and place into a loaf pan. Spread "Mustard Sauce" (recipe follows) and a little ketchup on top.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain all beans and chestnuts.
Heat sugar, salt, pepper, oil and vinegar.
Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
(May double beans without doubling ingredients.)

title: quick cherry cobbler
directions: In saucepan, combine pie filling and almond extract.
Bring to boiling.
Turn into six 6-ounce custard cups.
Top each with a biscuit.
Combine granulated sugar, brown sugar and cinnamon. Brush top of each biscuit with melted margarine.
Sprinkle with sugar mixture.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with whipped dessert topping, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Cook over low heat
until
thickened.
Remove from heat and add 1 cup shredded coconut.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, pineapple, bell pepper, onion, salt and half of the pecans.
Spread other half of the pecans on wax paper and after the ball is formed, roll the ball in the pecans.
Makes 1 large cheese ball.

title: easy creole soup
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Over medium heat, heat through.
Makes 7 1/3 cups or 6 servings.

title: chicken gumbo with shrimp
directions: Put oil in pot.
Brown chicken to golden brown.
Remove chicken from pot.
Brown flour in oil in which chicken was browned until it is dark brown.
Stir constantly.
Do not stop stirring until flour has reached the desired color.
Add chopped onion, green pepper and celery.
Stir.
Add water; stir.
Add chicken. Cover.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer for 40 minutes.
Add shrimp and green onion.
Cover and continue to simmer for 20 minutes more.
Add salt and cayenne pepper to taste.
Cut off heat; serve over steamed white rice topped with gumbo file and chopped parsley.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Line with bread.
Mix eggs and milk. Pour over bread.
Put sausage over this.
Sprinkle with both cheeses.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Remove foil the last 15 minutes.

title: best peanut butter fudge
directions: In saucepan, stir sugar and milk over medium heat, then bring to boil for 2 1/2 minutes.
Remove from fire and add vanilla, nuts, peanut butter and marshmallows.
Mix until well blended. Pour into a 9 x 9-inch pan greased with butter.
Cool.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix
pineapple,
flour,
sugar	and Cheddar cheese in a medium size baking dish.	Cover top with crumbled Ritz crackers.	Melt margarine
and
pour over top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs.	Combine flour and salt.
(If self rising flour is used, omit the salt but add soda.) Add flour mixture, buttermilk, soda, bananas to the sugar and shortening and mix well.
Fold in nuts.
Spray a large loaf pan with Pam.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: polka dot pizzas
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Rub some flour onto breadboard to cover about a 10-inch area.
Mix the tomato sauce, 3 tablespoons minced onion, 2 tablespoons oregano and 1/4 teaspoon pepper in medium bowl with fork.
(You'll use this later for topping.)

title: orange pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add one egg at a time and beat well.
Stir in a little flour and then milk mixture alternately until all the flour and milk is used.
Add the flavoring.
Pour in a large tube pan which has been greased and floured.
Put in a cold oven; set oven at 300° and bake 1 1/2 hours.
Cool and spread icing.

title: cranberry casserole
directions: Mix together apples, cranberries and sugar.
Pour into pan. Mix together remaining ingredients and pour over apple mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: blackberry pie
directions: Get ready the pastry.
Line pan.
Put in half the berries, then the sugar and sift flour over the sugar or mix together dry. Add the other half of the berries.
Place on the top crust.
Make a long cut in center.
Place in moderate oven to bake.
Sometimes a small piece of butter is added.
This makes a richer pie and kills the sharp tartness.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel, dice and cover potatoes with about enough water to equal 2 inches above.
Add onions, celery and carrot and simmer just below boil until tender.
Remove from heat (or turn down very low).
Add bouillon cubes.
Stir gently to dissolve.
Make a thick flour paste (about 1 cup).
Before adding to potato mixture, add enough water to bring water level up if it has boiled away.
Add paste and stir.
Cook gently until quite thick.
Add several good shakes of Jane's Crazy Mixed Up Salt.
(This cannot be substituted because it is the main flavor ingredient.) When thick, pour in milk until a good consistency.
Add gobs and gobs of butter. Simmer on low until hot enough to serve.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Mix all together until hot.
Serve on buns.

title: charlotte's "dressed" eggs
directions: Boil eggs and then let cool before peeling.
Cut eggs in half; scoop out yolks.
Place whites on separate plate.
In medium mixing bowl mash yolks and add the above ingredients.

title: barbecue green beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in casserole.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Mix all ingredients. Divide ingredients and spread evenly over tortillas. Roll up tortillas.
Refrigerate for several hours.

title: refrigerator cucumbers
directions: Mix last 4 ingredients.
Pour over cucumbers and onions. Refrigerate.
Will keep over 3 weeks.

title: fake kentucky fried chicken gravy
directions: Blend until smooth 1 cup water and 1/4 cup cornstarch (in blender).
In saucepan over medium heat, combine this with 10 ounce can Banquet chicken broth or homemade stock, 2 chicken bouillon cubes and two (10 ounce each) cans Franco American beef gravy.
Stir until thick and clear.
Serve over chicken, thoroughly heated.
A pinch of sage does wonders to this for flavor.
Bouillon powder may be substituted for the cubes if you wish.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven
to 350°.	Into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, sprinkle marshmallows and
nuts.
In
medium bowl, combine the brown sugar, cocoa	and 2 cups hot water.
Pour over marshmallows. Mix cake as directed on box.
Spoon batter over mixture in pan. Bake approximately 40 minutes.
Serve upside down.

title: south american steak sauce
directions: Mix all together in a large bowl.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: microwave turkey goulash
directions: In 2-quart casserole dish place butter, onions and garlic. Microwave at High 5 to 6 minutes, stirring after 3 minutes, until onion is limp.
Add turkey, broth, tomato sauce, paprika, salt and pepper.
Cover.
Microwave at High 6 to 8 minutes, stirring after 3 minutes, until hot.
Stir in sour cream into hot mixture just before serving.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Makes 6 servings.

title: raspberry pretzel salad or dessert
directions: Mix together and pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: chicken broccoli vegetable saute
directions: Heat 1 tablespoon margarine in skillet.
Cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned on both sides.
Remove and keep warm.

title: old fashion icebox fruit cake
directions: Melt marshmallows with Eagle Brand milk.
Mix other ingredients in very large mixing bowl. Add marshmallow mixture to the dry ingredients. Begin kneading with hands.
Mix well.
Pack in wax paper lined tube pan.
Keep refrigerated. Wait 2 to 3 days before cutting cake.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Mix together salt, flour, sugar, baking powder and 2 teaspoons cocoa.
Stir in milk and melted shortening.
Blend in nuts. Spread in a 9-inch pan; then sprinkle with mixture of brown sugar and cocoa.
Over this, pour hot water.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
When baked, turn upside-down on a large plate.
Serve plain or top with whipped cream.
Cake will raise to top and the pudding is in
the bottom.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cook all approximately 30 minutes or until cooked.
Add soup, diluted with one can of water.
Add Velveeta cheese.
Heat thoroughly on low.
Add no salt.

title: beans and ham
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, combine all ingredients. Cook and stir until beans are thoroughly heated.
Spoon into 2-quart casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350° for about 35 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 6 (1 cup) servings.

title: peach cobbler sam's way
directions: Melt margarine and mix all ingredients together.
