Pour into a baking dish and bake 30-45 minutes or until brown on top at 350 degrees.
Top with ice cream if desired and enjoy.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, then add vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add flour to creamed mixture (do not over mix).
Add bananas and nuts to dough.
Stir until just mixed.
Bake in 2 greased 5x9 loaf pans about 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350 degrees.
Do not overcook or it will dry out.
Remove from pans soon after baking.

title: chocolate balls
directions: Melt the square of chocolate.
Add the condensed milk, vanilla wafers, pecans, vanilla and salt.

title: never fail peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar, milk and salt for 10 minutes.
Add butter; continue boiling until mixture forms a soft ball in cold water. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat until mixture starts to set.
Pour quickly into buttered pan.
Cut into squares.

title: vermicelli with white clam sauce
directions: Cook vermicelli as directed.
Drain.
In a 10-inch skillet, heat the olive oil over medium heat.
Add garlic halves and saute over medium heat, turning now and then until golden.
Press on garlic with a fork for flavor, then discard.
Gently slide the clam juice into the oil, stirring.
Be careful, the oil will pop and bubble up.
Add salt, pepper and oregano.
Simmer over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Add the clams and their liquid; mix well and cook, uncovered, over medium heat for ten minutes to reduce the sauce.
Stir in parsley.
Toss hot, drained pasta with half of the sauce.
Place pasta in bowls and spoon the remainder of sauce over each portion.
Yields 4 main course servings.

title: emerald souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a souffle dish.
Steam bok choy until tender, about 10 minutes.
Drain and chop in a food processor.
Set aside.
Melt margarine in a medium size saucepan. Add flour and cook, stirring constantly, for one minute.
Add milk and slowly bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in bok choy, eggs, cheese, salt, pepper and mace.
Set aside.

title: plaza iii steak soup
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Melt in butter.
Mix in flour. Add water and whole tomatoes.
Add Accent and black pepper. Parboil onion, carrots and celery; add to mixture.
Add frozen mixed vegetables and bring to a boil.
Simmer until vegetables are cooked.

title: quick coffee cake
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients at medium speed.
Combine the remaining ingredients.
Put 1/3 of the sugar mixture in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan, then put half of the batter on top of that, then another 1/3 of sugar mixture.
Next, put rest of batter on that.
Top with last 1/3 sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pizza balls
directions: Open buns and place inside up.
Cover with 1 ounce or 1 tablespoon pizza sauce.
Add meat evenly on all 16 bun halves. Cover with cheese.
Put in oven on flat sheet and bake at 350° until cheese melts and bubbles and buns start to toast.

title: graham cracker cream cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together; mix with crumbs. Cream shortening and sugar; beat in eggs.
Add dry ingredients and liquids alternately.
Bake in greased pans at 300° for 30 minutes. Makes 2 (8-inch) layers.
Fill with cream filling.

title: mother's holiday salad
directions: Dissolve first 2 ingredients.
Stir in salad dressing; cool. Add remaining ingredients and let gel.

title: prize winning meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly.
Pack firmly into a greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake in a preheated moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: old virginia spoon bread
directions: Scald milk.
Mix salt and corn meal with water and stir into milk.
Cook until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add small amount of hot corn meal to egg yolks, then stir yolks into hot cornmeal. Add cream of tartar to egg whites.
Whip until stiff but moist. Fold whites into cornmeal and pour into 2-quart greased casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until light brown and a knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: hole in middle cake
directions: Mix thoroughly and bake at 350°.

title: quick but delicious peach cobbler
directions: Pour pie filling into baking dish.
Put tablespoon of butter (divided into portions) in with filling and leave in oven while preheated just to melt butter.
In bowl, mix sugar, flour and salt together.
Slowly add milk as you blend it into dry ingredients. Mix well.
Pour all over top of filling.
Bake at 375° until crust is golden brown.

title: wild rice
directions: Brown rice, oregano, salt and pepper, butter, garlic clove and onion.
Put together in baking dish with beef consomme, water and mushrooms with juice.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli cornbread no. 2
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine butter, onion, salt, cheese, broccoli and beaten eggs; blend.
Stir in muffin mix.
Pour into greased, hot 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or cast-iron skillet.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into serving size squares.

title: pickle relish
directions: Put veggies through food chopper.
Add salt and let stand overnight.
In morning, drain and add vinegar, sugar, spices and horseradish.
Cook for 20 minutes and seal up.
Yield:
23 pints.

title: twinkie dessert
directions: Place Twinkies, after slicing in half, in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Prepare pudding, using package directions.
Spread over Twinkies.
Layer bananas and strawberries over top.
Top with Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: mama ruth's cooked caramel icing
directions: Put sugar and butter in an iron skillet and stir until mixture turns a light caramel color.
Stir frequently.
Add milk slowly (it will have a tendency to boil over).
Cook about 5 minutes after it begins to boil.
cook until softball stage. Remove from heat, add vanilla and cool.
Stir until thick enough to ice cake.

title: tortilla soup
directions: In a 4-quart pot heat oil over medium heat.
Add beef and onion.
Saute 5 minutes.
Add jalapeno, garlic, chili powder and cumin.
Cook 5 minutes or until meat is browned and vegetables are tender.
Add tomatoes with puree and water.
Heat to a boil over high heat; reduce heat to low.
Cover and cook 15 minutes.
Stir beans into soup mixture.
Cook 10 minutes.
Heat oven to 400°. Cut tortillas into triangle chips.
Place chips in bowl and spray with vegetable spray and toss to coat.
Arrange chips on baking sheet and bake 8 minutes until crisp.
Cool chips.
Sprinkle soup with chopped cilantro.
Serve with sour cream if desired.
Makes eight 1 1/4-cup servings.

title: red velvet pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Add rest of ingredients as listed.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° in large tube pan for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: corn relish
directions: Cut corn from cob.
Chop vegetables.
Put in kettle and pour half of vinegar over mixture.
Mix sugar, flour, salt, mustard, cayenne and turmeric; add the remaining vinegar.
Combine mixtures and bring to boiling point.
Simmer 40 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 pints.

title: banana bread
directions: Blend Crisco and sugar well.
Add eggs and bananas.
Mix well. Add flour, baking soda, salt and baking powder.
Pour in a greased loaf pan.
Test with toothpick.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: vanilla sauce
directions: Combine water, bay leaves, sage, marjoram, savory, thyme, nutmeg, pepper, cloves and salt.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer while processing hamburger, adding more water until brown and in granular form.
After hamburg is browned, add contents of saucepan and simmer 30 minutes.
Add paprika, chili powder and garlic.
Simmer 30 minutes longer, stirring often.
Freeze in small portions if desired.

title: egg custard
directions: Heat oven to 475°.
Heat milk and butter in a double boiler, just until butter melts.
Beat together eggs, sugar and vanilla and add to milk mixture.
Pour into a 10-inch pie crust.
(I use crust from dairy counter, not frozen).
Cook at 475° for 5 minutes.
Turn temperature to 425° and cook 15 minutes more.
Do not open oven door while cooking!

title: daffodil dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix all ingredients except egg together with mixer.
Separate egg; crumble and sprinkle over top of dip. Serve with veggies or crackers.

title: crepes
directions: Mix well; let stand in refrigerator for 1 hour, then cook as you would for pancakes on a nonstick skillet, or a skillet that has been sprayed with cooking spray, turning once.

title: healthy cocoa muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Line 12 medium muffin cups with paper baking cups or spray bottoms only with vegetable oil cooking spray.

title: zucchini-walnut bread
directions: Mix eggs, applesauce and sugar first.
Add all other ingredients and blend well.
Bake at 350° for about one hour. Makes 2 loaves.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs, then chocolate.
Sift dry ingredients together; blend in alternately with milk.
Add nuts.
Chill 3 hours.
Form into 1-inch balls. Roll in powdered sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet, 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for about 13 minutes.
Cool slightly; remove from pan.
Do not overbake; bake just until set.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: elvis presley cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box.
Bake in Bundt pan. Mix pineapple with sugar and bring to a boil.
Punch holes in cake with end of wooden spoon.
While cake is still warm, put pineapple mixture on top.
Cool cake.
Mix softened cream cheese and butter together.
Work powdered sugar into cream cheese mixture.
Spread on cooled cake.

title: banana split pie
directions: Melt 1/2 stick margarine.
Add graham cracker crumbs and 1 cup powdered sugar to make crust.
Use 10-inch pan.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except sausage and cheese.
Bake in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Arrange sausage links on top of potato mixture.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until bubbly. Uncovered, with cheese on top, bake 5 minutes more.
Serves 6.

title: peach chiffon pie
directions: Blanch peaches and slip off skins.
Dice and add sugar, salt and lemon juice; let stand 30 minutes.
Soften Knox gelatine in 1/4 cup cold water, then dissolve in 1/2 cup very hot water.
Stir gelatine mixture into peach mixture.
Chill until partially set, 30 to 45 minutes.
Whip the cream until peaks form, then fold into peach mixture.
Chill another 10 to 15 minutes until it mounds when poured into pie shell.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer ingredients in this order:
lettuce, celery, onion and peas.
Cover with mayonnaise, sprinkle with sugar, crumbled cooked bacon and top with grated cheese.
Refrigerate overnight. Serves 8 to 10.

title: chocolate p-nut butter ice cream
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/2 cup cold milk in small bowl.
Add gelatin to scalded milk.
Stir in peanut butter; mix well and cool.
In mixing bowl, beat eggs until frothy.
Add sugar gradually.
Freeze chocolate chips until firm, then chop in blender while still frozen.
Add chips and remaining ingredients to peanut butter mixture.
Pour into ice cream freezer can; finish filling can with milk.
Freeze.
Remove paddle and pack in ice for several hours to mellow.

title: italian pasta stir-fry
directions: Cook linguini according to package directions, drain and keep warm.
Heat oil in a large skillet.
Press garlic into hot oil and stir-fry 15 seconds.
Add onion and zucchini; stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes or until tender.
Add tomatoes, parsley and seasonings. Stir gently until heated through.
Remove from heat and stir in linguini.
Grate Parmesan cheese over pasta.
Serve immediately. Yield:
8 servings.

title: caramel icing
directions: Mix sugar, milk and butter. Bring to soft-ball stage (start out on medium-high heat, then reduce to medium heat).
Remove from heat and add Kraft caramel kisses.
Beat until desired consistency. Spread on cake.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Plump raisins by microwaving in water 1 or 2 minutes; then drain.
Mix broccoli, bacon, raisins and pecans.
Just before serving, mix in dressing made by mixing the mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar until smooth.

title: white chili
directions: Cube cheese; place all ingredients in crock-pot until cheese is melted. Allow to cook on medium for up to 2 hours.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix all together and drop by teaspoons or fork onto ungreased pans.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 15 minutes.
Cool cookies on brown paper bag, doubled.
After they cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: cauliflower salad bowl
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine cauliflower, olives, green pepper, pimiento and onion.
Mix well.
In another mixing bowl, combine oil, lemon juice, vinegar, salt, pepper and sugar.
Mix well.
Pour oil mixture over vegetable mixture.
Toss to coat vegetables.
Refrigerate, covered, 4 hours or overnight.

title: tuna sandwich melts
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix together first five ingredients. Fill
buns
with
cup tuna mixture.
Wrap in foil. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with 3/4 of the bag of Doritos.
Brown ground beef and onion.
Mix with remaining ingredients and pour over Doritos.
Top with grated cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pistole
directions: Simmer hominy in skillet for 10 to 15 minutes. Add chili, mix well, simmer 10 more minutes. In separate pan, scramble eggs in butter. Cook eggs until done, but not dry. Pour into the chili mixture; add grated cheese. Save some cheese to garnish each serving.

title: party beans
directions: Drain all beans, except pork and beans and chili with beans. Mix all together in large baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serve piping hot.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: *Use plain flour with 1/2 teaspoon soda and 1/2 teaspoon salt.

title: baked yellow squash
directions: Cook squash and onion in covered boiling water for 20 minutes. Drain, mash and place in bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; pour into a greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(Top with additional cracker crumbs and melted butter before baking.)

title: italian fondue
directions: Brown beef, then drain.
Add tomato sauce, Cheddar cheese, Mozzarella cheese and sauce mix.
Pour into fondue pot.
Cut up bread into small pieces to dip into fondue.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add flour alternately with eggs.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 to 2 hours.

title: baked salmon loaf
directions: In a medium saucepan, heat the milk, bread and butter until creamy. Remove bones from salmon carefully, then beat eggs and mix with salmon. Combine the salmon with the bread mixture in the saucepan.
Add the can of vegetables to the salmon mixture and mix thoroughly. Bake in greased bread pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy cheese quiche
directions: *Onion, mushrooms, spinach, squash, etc.; a great way to use leftovers.
Also may use ham.

title: spoon butter rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 2 cups warm water.
Melt butter and sugar together.
Add beaten egg.
Pour this mixture into water and yeast.
Mix in flour.
Drop by spoon into greased muffin tins. Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all together and barbecue.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain kraut well.
Chop onions, celery and pepper.
Mix all ingredients with kraut and chill.

title: squash casserole
directions: Dice squash and onion.
Saute.
Combine squash, onions, cheese and soup.
Put into casserole.
Top with bread crumbs (I use Pepperidge Farm stuffing mix).
Bake 40 minutes in a 350° oven or until golden brown.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together and cook at 350° for 15 minutes. Add 1 cup grated cheese and cook 30 to 40 minutes until set. Serves 8.

title: easy eggnog
directions: In a bowl beat the egg yolks with the 1/2 cup of sugar until thick.
In another bowl beat the egg whites with 1/4 cup of sugar until thick.
In a third bowl beat the cream until thick.
Add the cream to the yolks, fold in the egg whites, and add the milk, Bourbon, vanilla, and a pinch of nutmeg, if desired.
Chill in freezer before serving.

title: easy hot apple cider
directions: Bring ingredients to a boil, then let simmer.
Add more juice as needed.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Cook rice in 2 1/2 cups broth from chicken according to package directions.
Combine all other ingredients, except almonds.
Pour into large casserole. Sprinkle almonds on top. Bake for 30 minutes or until bubbly at 375°.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all together
in blender and blend well.
Let stand before using.

title: pizza casserole ii
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Crumble sausage into a medium skillet; cook over medium heat until browned, stirring occasionally. Remove sausage and drain on paper towels. In a large lightly greased casserole dish, layer 1/2 of the noodles, 1/2 of the sausage and 1/2 of the remaining ingredients. Repeat with second layer of noodles, sausage and remaining ingredients. Reserve several pepperoni slices to garnish top. Bake 35 to 40 minutes. Serve immediately. Serves 6 to 8.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients; set aside.
Combine oil, sugar and vanilla; mix well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well. Gradually add dry ingredients mixing well.
Add carrots and mix well.
Pour into 3 (8-inch) round pans.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.

title: firehouse hoagie
directions: Cut bread in half lengthwise.
Spread oleo on bread.
Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Spread Cheez Whiz evenly on bread.
Add chopped onion and black olives.
Wrap in aluminum foil and heat in oven at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese has melted. Slice and serve.

title: mexican pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Roll out crescent roll onto round pizza pan.
Cook until slightly golden.
Brown hamburger with minced onion and add refried beans.
Put tomato sauce on crust.
Add beef and bean mixture.
Top with cheese and bake until bubbly, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Garnish with sour cream and black olives.

title: freezer cole slaw
directions: Mix cabbage, carrots, pepper and salt.
Let stand for 1 hour, then squeeze dry.
Mix vinegar, celery seed and sugar.
Bring to a boil and let boil for 1 minute.
Cool.
Pour over slaw.
This is good frozen for later use.

title: easy vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add vegetables, soup, catsup, water and seasonings.
Cook until done.

title: garlic dill pickles
directions: Simmer vinegar, salt, water and sugar.
Wash and sterilize jars, lids and bands.
For each jar, add 1/4 teaspoon each:
dill and celery seed, 5 peppercorns, 2 cloves garlic and 2 sprigs dill. Pack with cucumbers.
Pour hot vinegar mixture over cucumbers, leaving in 1/2-inch headspace.
Wipe rims of jars.
Place lids on jars; screw down bands.
Simmer in a water bath canner for 5 minutes to seal.

title: peach pie with crumbly crust
directions: Empty peaches and syrup into baking dish.
Mix together sugar, flour and soft margarine.
Sprinkle over peaches.
Bake at 350° until crust is brown.

title: quickie beef and tater casserole
directions: Combine beef with salt.
Pat into bottom of baking dish or casserole. Cover with drained green beans. Spread mushroom soup over beans. Top with frozen Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until meat is done and Tater Tots are tender.

title: banana orange muffin cake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottom of 9-inch round spring-form pan or cake pan.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add combined banana, juice, margarine, egg and orange peel, mixing just until moistened.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 10 minutes on wire rack; remove from pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and drizzle evenly over cake while still warm.

title: low-fat low-sugar cottage cheese dessert
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix cottage cheese, Cool Whip, dry jello and pineapple.
May use any flavor jello and any type fruit.

title: smothered chicken with mushroom gravy
directions: Prepare chicken cut in desired pieces for frying.
Rinse in cold water and dry.
Put flour, pepper, paprika, salt and monosodium glutamate in paper bag.
Put in 3 or 4 pieces of chicken at a time and shake until thoroughly coated.
Brown chicken on both sides in hot shortening at 360°.
Drain off excess fat.
Combine soup with water and blend; pour over chicken.
Cover skillet.
Bring to a free steam, then switch to about 200° and cook 30 to 45 minutes until tender.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: richmond chocolate frosting
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add chocolate and salt.
Add water. Cook until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla. Spread on cake while hot.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs.
Peel shells when cool.
Slice eggs lengthwise and remove yolks.
Mix onion, celery, mayonnaise, mustard, vinegar, salt and pepper into egg yolks.
Put mixture into halved egg whites and top with paprika.

title: cheesy chicken soup
directions: Lower Fat Version:
Omit 1 cup low-fat milk and 1/4 to 1/2 pound cheese.

title: syrup custard
directions: Beat egg whites and yolks together.
Add other ingredients. Bake in unbaked pie shell.

title: seafood mold
directions: Bring soup to a boil and add cream cheese.
Heat until melted. Dissolve gelatin in cold water and add to hot mixture, then add other ingredients.
Cool lightly.
Coat a mold and pour mixture into mold and refrigerate.

title: cream cheese potatoes
directions: Boil and mash potatoes.
Add Cheddar and 1/4 cup of butter, cream cheese, salt and garlic.
Mix well and eat.

title: company chicken
directions: Line Pyrex dish with chipped beef.
Place chicken in dish. Mix soup and sour cream and spread over the chicken.
Sprinkle top with paprika.
Bake 2 1/2 to 3 hours at 275°.
Serve with rice or noodles.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: rich white batter bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Blend in ginger and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Let stand in warm place until bubbly, approximately 15 minutes.
Stir in remainder of sugar, milk, salt and oil.
With mixer on low, beat in 2 cups flour, one cup at a time, beating very well after each addition.
Beat in remainder of flour with spoon.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Cut cheese into chunks and melt over low heat.
Add taco seasoning and sauce.
Brown beef and drain well.
Add beef to cheese mixture; mix well.
Serve hot with plain tortilla chips. May thin with water, never milk.

title: bugs on a log(method:  fireless)
directions: Clean celery; cut into 2 to 3-inch lengths.
Place in Ziploc bag and go on hike.
When ready for lunch, fill cavity of celery with peanut butter, also carried in plastic bag or container. Place raisins on peanut butter and enjoy.

title: reveille's favorite dish
directions: Preheat bonfire to 400°.
Mix the first 7 ingredients in a large bowl.
Make sure that all ingredients are mixed well.
Trim any excess fat off the chops and make a diagonal cut along the side of each chop.
Stuff the meat mixture into each chop, filling each cavity well.
Dredge the chops in flour and broil for 45 minutes over a roaring bonfire, basting the chops with butter.
Serve immediately on a bed of "cotton," preferably on New Year's Day.

title: seafoam jello
directions: Drain juice from pears.
Boil 1 cup pear juice and add to gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
Set aside until cool.
Mix cheese and milk together until smooth.
Add gelatin mixture to cheese mixture and blend until smooth.
Mash pears until they are the consistency of applesauce.
Add mashed pears to gelatin-cheese mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into jello mold and chill until firm.

title: apple pie - gool 'ol
directions: Make a
pastry
shell
for
two
crust 8 or 9-inch pie. Pare apples,
core and slice.
Rub flour into bottom of pastry shell. Sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar.
Arrange apples in pastry shell; sprinkle with lemon juice.
Mix one cup sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg;
sprinkle
over apples.
Dot with butter or margarine. Cover
with pastry.
Bake in hot oven at 425° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook seasoned beef; add vegetables and macaroni and season.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter in saucepan, add brown sugar.
Cook over low heat for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add milk, bring to a boil. Remove from heat and cool; add 2 cups confectioners sugar gradually, beating well.

title: deer stroganoff
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in hot water.
Set aside.
Season meat to taste.
Lightly cover with flour.
Melt butter in a large skillet.
Add deer until light brown.
Add onions, bouillon and soup; simmer until meat is tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Add sour cream and heat for about 20 minutes.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Measure 1/2 cup warm water in bowl.
Sprinkle with yeast and stir until dissolved.
Add warm milk, brown sugar, salt and margarine.
Add 2 cups water.
Beat until smooth.
Add 1 cup flour and oats and beat until smooth.
Add enough flour to make soft dough, knead for 8 to 10 minutes and cover with plastic and towel. Rest 15 minutes.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: In medium plastic mixing bowl, place flour, salt, shortening and sugar, if desired.
Put cover (sealed tightly) on and shake again.
Dough will need very little handling.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Cream sugar, margarine and cream cheese together.
Add jello mixture.
Fold in whipped milk.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Freeze.

title: peanut cluster
directions: Mix
cereal,
peanuts
and coconut in a large bowl, set aside. In
saucepan
mix
sugar
and
Karo syrup.
Bring to a rolling boil and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and quickly stir
in peanut butter.
Mix this mixture with the dry mixture and drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Cool.

title: lemon butter
directions: Combine butter, juice and salt in small pan.
Cook until mixture is bubbly and butter is melted.
Remove from heat and stir in parsley.
Serve with spinach, broccoli, potatoes, carrots or peas.

title: cherry coffee cake
directions: Combine cake mix, flour and yeast.
Add warm water.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in eggs.
Spoon batter in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spoon pie filling evenly over batter.
Cut butter into remaining cake mix.
Sprinkle over pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pina colada wedges
directions: Beat cream cheese with sugar and flavoring until smooth.
Fold in 2 cups whipped topping, pineapple with syrup and 2 cups of the coconut.
Spread in an 8-inch layer pan lined with plastic wrap.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Put butter, cocoa and water in pan and cook until boiling. Pour over sugar and flour mixture.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Frost with Texas Sheet Cake Frosting.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Cut up fruit (not too fine).
Mix with nuts in 1/2 cup of flour.
Set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Combine both. Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: fresh vegetable pizza
directions: *Cauliflower, broccoli, green pepper, carrots, celery, cucumbers, olives, radishes, mushrooms, etc.

title: company chicken
directions: Brown chicken in oil (enough to coat pan) at medium heat.
In separate pan, brown mushrooms and onions in a little margarine. Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Pour onions and mushrooms over chicken.
Sprinkle on thyme until you can smell it.
In empty frypan, empty soup and fill can with wine.
Combine soup and wine over low heat.
Pour over chicken and simmer for 45 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: baked apple
directions: Core apple and put in baking dish.
Fill with maple syrup and Grand Marnier or orange extract.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Apple splits when it is done.
Serve with vanilla ice cream.

title: new orleans bread pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients; mixture should be moist not soupy. Pour into a buttered 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Place on middle rack of oven.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, until top is golden brown.
Serve warm with sauce.

title: deer roast
directions: Soak meat in 1/2 cup apple cider vinegar overnight.
Rinse, place meat in a gallon pot and cover with water.
Add pork meat, 1 whole apple, 1 onion and 1 red pepper.
Cook 2 hours or until fork-tender.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions, drain and salt.
Mix the remaining ingredients and add the macaroni.
Put in a greased casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: three-cheese macaroni
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine hot macaroni, soup, milk, seasonings, 1/4 cup each of Swiss, Cheddar and Parmesan cheese and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 25 minutes or until heated through.
Top with remaining cheeses and onions; bake, uncovered, 5 minutes or until onions are golden brown.
Makes 4 to 6 main-dish servings.

title: south of the border squash
directions: Dice squash; saute squash with onion in butter until tender-crisp.
Fold in chillies, flour, salt and pepper.
Place in greased 2-quart baking dish; sprinkle with Monterey Jack cheese. Combine egg, cottage cheese and parsley.
Layer over cheese; sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes until heated through.

title: corn and macaroni casserole
directions: Combine ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake covered the first half hour.
Uncover for the last half hour.

title: pear preserves
directions: Bring to boil. Boil hard for 20 minutes. Lower temperature and cook 10 more minutes or longer. Boil until pears change color.

title: catfish fillet
directions: *Use 1 part flour to 4 parts cornmeal to make enough of the mixture to coat the number of fillets you are preparing.

title: hamburger or venison stroganoff
directions: Cook and stir meat and onion in margarine until meat is light brown.
Stir in flour, salt, garlic, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in soup.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and heat through.
Serve over noodles.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine all fruit, tossing very gently, with about half of the honey lime dressing.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix well and bake uncovered in a buttered 9 x 13-inch dish or until knife in center comes out clean.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: In blender, blend 3 tablespoons flour and the eggs.
In a large bowl, add the flour and egg mixture to 1 quart milk and 1 cup sugar.
Add the evaporated milk.
Stir all ingredients together well, except fruit and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Add fresh fruit (sprinkle sugar over fruit 30 minutes ahead of time to sweeten).
Pour into ice cream container; churn until thick but creamy, about 15 minutes.
For best results, allow cream to set in ice in churn 10 to 15 minutes longer before serving.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add all ingredients except sour cream. Pour half of mixture in dish and refrigerate until set. Add sour cream on top of jello and top with remaining jello mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: raisin nut fudge
directions: Melt chocolate with butter on temperature controlled burner set at 150°.
Remove and add corn syrup, milk, vanilla and salt. Blend well.
Gradually blend in sugar, mixing well after each addition.
Stir in raisins and nuts, mixing well.
Turn into a lightly buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch square pan, spreading evenly. Chill in gas refrigerator until firm, about 2 1/2 hours.
Cut into squares.
Makes 3 dozen squares.

title: chocolate no bake cookies
directions: Mix in saucepan on medium heat until it boils for 1 minute or more the sugar, cocoa and milk.
Remove from heat and add oleo and peanut butter.
Mix until melted.
Add vanilla and oats.
Mix together and spoon out by teaspoons onto wax paper.

title: funnel cake
directions: Add all ingredients; mix well.
Heat 1 1/4 inches of cooking oil in skillet to 375°.
Hold finger over hole in funnel (3/8-inch opening is best).
Pour 1/4 cup batter in funnel.
Hold over hot oil; remove finger from funnel hole and drizzle in a circular motion to form spiral.
Fry for 1 minute, or until brown; turn and brown on other side.
Drain on paper towel.
Sprinkle with cinnamon or powdered sugar.

title: merry christmas cookies
directions: Cover fruit and nuts with flour.
Mix other ingredients and pour over fruit and nuts.
Mix all well and shape with hands into desired size.
Place on well-greased cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes.
(Adjust cooking time to size of cookie.)

title: lemon lime salad
directions: Boil 4 cups water and dissolve Jell-O, cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Add condensed milk and pineapple.
Mix well.
Add pecans.
Chill.

title: mix in the pan chocolate snack cake
directions: In an 8 x 8-inch ungreased baking dish, mix all dry ingredients with a fork.
Add wet ingredients to dry and mix well in dish with a fork.
Sprinkle batter with chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until inserted toothpick pulls out clean and dry.

title: fresh spinach salad
directions: Clean spinach and tear leaves apart.
Add 3 diced eggs, onions and bacon.
Put into a large serving bowl, toss with dressing. Garnish with last hard-boiled egg.

title: orange julius
directions: Pour all ingredients into blender and mix until all ice has been crushed.
Enjoy!

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Cook broccoli 7 to 8 minutes.
Cook rice as directed on package.
Combine all and place in dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in dish and freeze.
To serve, remove and let stand for 10 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: hot cheese canapes
directions: Put cheese,
bacon and onions through a meat grinder or food processor.
In
a medium size mixing bowl, combine cheese mixture, dry mustard, Worcestershire sauce and mayonnaise. Mix thoroughly. Place
mixture
on
large
piece
of waxed paper. Shape into a log so that when sliced it will fit onto a piece of party
bread. Wrap
and
freeze
until
ready to serve. At serving time,
cut frozen
log
into
1/4 inch slices.
Place cheese slice
on
a piece
of
party
bread.
Place on cookie sheet.
Place under the broiler until browned.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine milk, flour and sugar.
Boil while stirring.
After thickened, remove from heat; stir in egg, butter and vanilla. Alternate bananas, pudding and wafers in bowl.

title: aunt chris' cajun beans
directions: Soak pintos overnight or quick method (bring to boil; boil one minute, cover and sit off heat for one hour).

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add taco seasoning and enough taco sauce to make easy to handle.

title: curry crab
directions: In skillet melt butter.
Add onion and curry powder.
Saute. Add flour and brown slightly.
Add milk, stirring until thickened. Add crab meat and heat. Serve over hot rice.

title: gazpacho
directions: Put tomato, cucumber, onion, green pepper and 1 cup V-8 juice in blender and puree at high speed.
Mix pureed vegetables and 2 1/2 cups V-8 juice, olive oil, wine vinegar and Tabasco.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Serve topped with croutons.

title: frosted molasses creams
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Blend egg, molasses and coffee into sugar mixture.
Sift together remaining ingredients and add to liquid mix.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° until done.

title: nectar punch
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Just before serving, stir in club soda.
Serve over ice.
Yield:
1 1/2 quarts.

title: baked german style potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in salted boiling water for 12 to 15 minutes; drain well and place in an oiled 10 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan. In a medium saucepan, cook bacon until crisp. Remove and reserve. Add onion and celery and cook until soft.

title: caramelicious fudge brownies
directions: Prepare and bake brownie mix according to package directions in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Meanwhile, in a small saucepan over low heat, melt caramels with milk.
Stir until smooth.
Immediately after removing brownies from oven, sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Drizzle caramel over top.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in greased baking pan.
Layer chicken, onions, chips, cheese and chips.
Combine soups, broths and tomatoes and pour over the casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: beanie bake
directions: Drain all beans.
Place drained beans in casserole.
Fry bacon and onions until brown.
Don't drain.
Add sugar, mustard and vinegar.
Cover and heat 20 minutes.
Pour over beans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
A good potluck dish.

title: sauerkraut spread
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve on party rye bread.

title: circus peanut salad
directions: Drain pineapple; set aside.
Dissolve jello in hot water; add cut-up circus peanuts.
Let melt and cool until starting to gel. Add whipped Dream Whip and pineapple.
Chill.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on box.
Drain well. Grate Cheddar cheese.
Spray a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Mix all ingredients in dish.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: heath bar crunch candy
directions: In 2 quart saucepan, mix butter, sugar, water and corn syrup and cook over medium heat until temperature reaches 290 degrees on a candy thermometer (this is soft crack stage).
During cooking period, stir constantly with a wooden spoon (plastic will melt). Mixture should boil gently over entire surface.
Watch carefully at 280 degrees.
Remove from heat when temperature reaches 290 degrees and add 1/2 c. nuts, stirring quickly.

title: banana bread(low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly oil an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
In a medium bowl, combine first five ingredients.
In a large bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Add the dry ingredients to the wet ingredients all at once; stir gently to combine.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes. Remove from pan and cool completely.
Wrap airtight until ready to serve.
Can be frozen.

title: one bowl cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add shortening, 2/3 cup milk and vanilla.
Beat 1 minute at medium. Add milk 1/4 cup milk and eggs.
Beat 2 minutes at medium.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.
Use any flavor icing.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix well; pour into pan, then place in refrigerator.

title: green bean and mushroom casserole
directions: Cook green beans and spinach according to package directions. Mix in casserole dish with other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: microwaved almond bark
directions: Melt butter in 9-inch glass pan.
Add almonds and cook on High, stirring each minute for 4 to 5 minutes until toasted.
Melt chips on High for 2 to 4 minutes.
Stir in almonds.
Pour onto waxed paper covered cookie sheet and spread to desired thickness. Chill.
Break into chunks.
Keep chilled.
Melts easily.

title: old fashion taffy
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a small Dutch oven.
Cook, without stirring, over medium heat just until mixture reaches soft crack stage (270°).
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
Pour candy onto a well buttered 5 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan or slab of marble.
Let cool to touch.
Pull candy until light in color and difficult to pull.
(Butter hands if candy is sticky.)

title: crispy potato wedges
directions: Put potato wedges in plastic bag with remaining ingredients. Shake until coated.
Put on cookie sheet sprayed with nonsticking spray.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Layer peaches in baking dish and cover with croutons.
Melt margarine.
Mix with sugar, flour and egg.
Pour over peaches and croutons.
Cook at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: old fashion tea cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add unbeaten egg.
Beat well.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Add soda to buttermilk.
Add dry ingredients to cream.
Mix.
Make a soft dough.
Roll on floured cloth.
Place on greased baking sheet. Bake at 375°.

title: ham cheese ball
directions: Chop ham and onion very fine.
Soften cream cheese.
Add Accent, ham and onion.
Mix all together.
Form into a ball.
Can be rolled in chopped pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Place ingredients in layers in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Do not mix.

title: feta chicken
directions: Place cheese under the skin of the chicken all around.
Rub olive oil over chicken and sprinkle with seasonings and herbs of your choice.
Place the chicken breast-down in a roasting pan. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Turn chicken and bake for another 40 minutes or until juices run clear.

title: turkey-macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package, drain.
Rinse with cold water; drain.
Rinse frozen peas with cold water to separate; drain.
Mix macaroni, peas and remaining ingredients except lettuce.
Cover and refrigerate about 4 hours or until chilled. Serve on lettuce.
Enjoy!
Yields 6 servings.
